Dialogue.C62EF92D4DC0734EE6B068BB4C86CE99_DB7CBEB: Considering my own history, I'm not one to poke holes in a script.

Dialogue.FAC7CEEF43D84E8CFBA2DB9EA62B7F4D_06FC410: Conspiracy theorists, in general, are never good at wordplay. Why is that?

Dialogue.5ED319AE4AC4F212B54EF992FA61BCD5_7D086D9: Cool. I'm going to get back to work trying to extract the world's most complex AI...

Dialogue.2DADD41E4B94027F672B238935017A7F_47CFF90: Copy that. Deploying a team to your location now.

Dialogue.BE0A41274C1A0787650BAC9EC5DBCFBB_47CFF90: Ghost memos. Holograms. Skywriting. Spiteful Gravestones.

Dialogue.CE191002453F238602F598897B814F79_06FC410: Give him a bicycle and tell him to pedal. Next!
Dialogue.BFCFB98E4A296D5B05BB7CBC86C30005_06FC410: Give it a chance. You'll get swept away by holiday romance.
Dialogue.99D0844542290AA421565CAF95266A7E_176484F: Give it a flip and... Yup, it's haunted.
Dialogue.92055CFA49A9FA56B82322A42CD31D81_06FC410: Give me a reason not to...
Dialogue.12580DF14FB6556F5B2D3DBD40F316B5_176484F: Give me your take on things. I can handle it.

Dialogue.B11DB8AB4F673048D6DC32BD8C3BC470_FB122F8: Glad to hear it. We're stuck in crush mode and the sensors are over-analyzing everything.

Dialogue.75C1644344C21503E4033DBC282ECDB0_EC1949E: Go away! We don't want you here!
Dialogue.22D3FF824D66C10E3E79D699698497B0_B25AF7B: Go away. I'm not falling for your tricks!

Dialogue.09187B9748756F09344501A72A348265_861A10F: Good find! This will put the finishing touches on our romantic honeymoon caravan!

Dialogue.16DD8C7A4AEF1AC6A1926FA49B3886AA_7D2960E: Good for the Commander and whatever, but who's the king of the apes? Who's the alpha?
Dialogue.61EDD2204EB53374606895A3022DE029_06FC410: Good job! This is exactly what we need.
Dialogue.239947194958EA1F0C94D5AA5299CB62_06FC410: Good job, collect more car data!
Dialogue.FA6C74BB4FFA439D50015CAB52B45B9B_06FC410: Good job. We've collected all the logs related to Project Tailor.
Dialogue.8E55204A4E591B432311D7BDA453B91A_06FC410: Good luck finding me, Ree. I don't even know where I am.
Dialogue.C77847404F42D6BBC8B5CA901AD51D73_06FC410: Good luck! And please climb that corporate ladder quickly. We are so busy.
Dialogue.D659506A48951EEBAC0A8E8214F5E50A_06FC410: Good news, the samples are processing.
Dialogue.39EA718B4B8B1BC02A0AD99E77426C2E_06FC410: Good point. Let's update that to... "Admiral Echelon responds, 'Okay, but I'm not happy.'"
Dialogue.F7B0CDAF46A8F94EB73F9BAD3FD5C319_9801E98: Good sample. Thank you for the help.

Dialogue.1729090A44B69DFCB8C79BA270B2BD95_06FC410: Good. Because your true love is somewhere out in the storm waiting to be rescued.
Dialogue.37C2F6C44FC8C3AA754ED0ACE3CEA75A_06FC410: Good. Now I am going to need that data. Sorry about the yelling.

Dialogue.27F17B714970E6D1B92D4AAB9CA61C9C_87F0BBB: Got a back up for ya, so no need to call me when the other one explodes.
Dialogue.CAA48E3B499115F50C8EE9BF7BF12749_A96EA86: Got it, it's all coming together now.

Dialogue.B0A615F24F26D201A7D9E58480927943_06FC410: Got some... oh, okay. Got some of that. Okay. Uh, moving on...
Dialogue.F1689935486AFC624981F39EE20AB641_FB122F8: Gotta agree. They are messed up. All of 'em.

Dialogue.473068644EF50124645C9798BA520660_97A9259: Gotta keep the show rollin', Ray.
Dialogue.EFE061814E6CECA65015EAAA8639D25D_FB122F8: Gotta know if what you're looking at is throwing out good or bad vibes, Little Robot!
Dialogue.202DF88B46F5365A95BAAB9F31F3A7B2_AB3C42C: Grab a hold of your vision and never take "No" for an answer.
Dialogue.3F1DA53F40018095747DA1B908F4ED06_06FC410: Grab all the backups you can find.
Dialogue.ABDBA4FF40B323C86B55C1856FA13595_FB122F8: Grab any encrypted radio parts you can find, emergency vehicles probably have'em.
Dialogue.FAF0A8C149A200E52BC33AB6B3F3003F_06FC410: Grab anything rotten that could be thrown at us by an angry mob.
Dialogue.4677057143162A91408ECA9533C74A99_EC1949E: Grab the good stuff and let's go.
Dialogue.7B46375543B075E99A2C3081F4F869A7_06FC410: Grab those parts over there for our rocket!

Dialogue.00D7F05D4763A625E22FAB8FD5B90E08_97A9259: Great. Hold on to that feeling...
Dialogue.10419E53444E7553451C4BA90D193F81_47CFF90: Great. I'll need you to submit a rundown of today's mission by five.

Dialogue.68EDC25C46017AD5E10ECEA4EAEDD60E_06FC410: Ground Control to Major ED-EE, come in.

Dialogue.74922A01464A463C982C3EA2960BCF83_7D2960E: Guess it beats telling my problems to a real person.

Dialogue.2B5C2E8D47D4C97D0458F7BD47BDC990_B25AF7B: Ha ha ha ha ha ha! I am turning!
Dialogue.D3703BB84C4D6F8A0D0BE1AF45D5CF8F_9D00593: Ha ha ha.. me? INSANE? I just love Christmas! Ha ha ha ha... ha ha ha ha ha... ha.

Dialogue.9DA2BDC54A5F8C688F9A2E87F4947361_97A9259: Ha! Love having it rain something *useful* for once!
Dialogue.428C400543BE3C437559C4A0F1C668B1_06FC410: Ha! Not any more it isn't.
Dialogue.DA669D7544BD505D305263A6377D23B3_97A9259: Ha! Okay, that felt pretty good! And as the good feeling is beingâ€¦ replacedâ€¦ yeah! By "Sour-Empty-Stomach." There it is!
Dialogue.822C0BD8413F135431E5A0960B1BF289_72190CE: Ha! She's gonna to be so jealous!
Dialogue.474071334C2375E51FF893AC0D5A817A_06FC410: Ha! They can't get rid of her that easily!
Dialogue.E8A088E04585CE3FB3AA448C1B6BBD5B_724DAF1: Ha! You're more than your past!
Dialogue.E1C6100745EAAFF8E12BD0B48E54C92C_97A9259: Ha, excellent! Time to get to work.
Dialogue.7E823EED4B2696D41915A59EADA525CB_EAAE146: Hah... We found it. We found it!
Dialogue.C9D42F384AFE97029D90808EEA99FFC0_06FC410: Haha! How'd ya like them peaches, husk?
Dialogue.3851B24A4ECD40434B304C9DD9D10584_7D2960E: Haha! I know that pleases the court!
Dialogue.309EE0AD4B095B6F04A5E8A757F9A1A7_D87E161: Haha! It's good to be back.
Dialogue.57CE4DB24B29883B32F8618184F1D724_06FC410: Hahaha! You gotta be ready for anything.
Dialogue.5DA311514A6C446A225C34B09CCD578E_84C369E: Hammers, saws... (gasp) There's even a level!
Dialogue.91FCC0044F848ECCD7A07A81C79CA2B8_72190CE: Hand over the gold before we cut you some ribbons!

Dialogue.6464ED5B4DB19721DE751E9AB4AC7AF7_861A10F: Hang on, someoneâ€™s left a note. In a bottle, naturally.
Dialogue.005E4C7E47E9853902A022A8E878848D_72190CE: Hang on. Whatâ€™s wrong with â€œBlakebeard?â€
Dialogue.5FF0057C4DD900FEEB741D982E1AE81B_06FC410: Hang tight, Commander. I'll figure something out.
Dialogue.9336F7524472CF0F7529EBBFE538293C_861A10F: Happy Christmas! No more bombs, alright?
Dialogue.3F5BF6454B7EB68D6B6F65A5DBB026CB_47CFF90: Happy Holidays from all of us at Homebase.
Dialogue.F5FF5E304C8290851987D6A26C5307CC_B222EAD: Happy Holidays! Here's a gift for you!
Dialogue.42E63E3147271899DAC75994D645921D_97A9259: Have I gone fully meta? Am I in a time loop?
Dialogue.FAE7C51D4FC0AD735A5B6291D8624874_06FC410: Have you been robbing everyone and dumping their things in the garbage?
Dialogue.EE04E831438DE66A46E7ED836DD0950E_47CFF90: Have you considered making the caravan a convertible?

Dialogue.5F8DF8824D7434575D5CA1A3E8011AC2_CC240C1: Have you or a loved one been exposed to radioactive bees?
Dialogue.3F0D250C40C0F01D6007A789AC9CDED7_B222EAD: Have you seen the people I'm around?
Dialogue.B1A6F6F84319CFD10B391EBD51204441_87F0BBB: Haven't you ever heard that saying, "When all you have is a hammer, everything looks like a nail?"
Dialogue.DBD1234C4C54244B96D5DE955F587BEA_47CFF90: Having a range of peg legs that look suitable with a tuxedo or cocktail dress is essential for making sure you're not turned away.
Dialogue.D77ADFC9445FFDA33F56A58A6779856C_06FC410: He also decreed that all trees of a paper bearing age must be burned.
Dialogue.5EE2D5BB45B65CB661A3DEB5AA5A7468_861A10F: He breaks down my fort... I rebuild it, heh.
Dialogue.48ED24D141A0AE4D5F11399B222E4A46_97A9259: He brightens your day, and he curdles your milk.
Dialogue.306BF85C42E5F9CB57085B9D2597D2CF_861A10F: He clips his toenails in the middle of the room no matter who is around.
Dialogue.6F74FE5F4F122687A035C6BCB1ED7725_06FC410: He commissioned statues, works of art, and even created two daily papers.
Dialogue.93E860A147E9019AFD117EB992007452_06FC410: He could build them all into a tall tower and lord his collection of cherry pie filling over everyone else.
Dialogue.ABA86D254B9F52F571493D9062C18A0D_72190CE: He couldn't find it, but we will.
Dialogue.AF9327074037C950DDE1D4B635AA53D3_B222EAD: He couldn't see me... but I was mature about it.
Dialogue.EA3116CD4407B5D57F1131BF8D7BB319_4731F06: He did save my life so... time beggars can't be time choosers.
Dialogue.029F5F1A44A8F771247A9F91D47D8C18_97A9259: He does have a pretty baller cable package.
Dialogue.8ADDD1D148C7069393FD14A8DFFD5C9A_CC240C1: He doesn't know dinosaurs went extinct?
Dialogue.57C5E0BD4422DCC8DDD9D4A82AD8A198_06FC410: He doesn't mean you, Dire. You're not a fleabag.
Dialogue.0DA08CC24182FA3CEB37C5A05615EABC_97A9259: He gathers together a group of his friends... no skills, clueless...
Dialogue.65B5162340C139688291449279AA984E_06FC410: He has a bomb under Homebase, Lars!
Dialogue.3DE6D3ED476F9B1747EB63B449A64CB5_06FC410: He knows about ten thousand rock facts, and he is very literal.
Dialogue.21164C8444AEE515D93A5998FCE084E9_CC240C1: He knows we're all happier when he leaves.
Dialogue.793A50984D7F5D06A78095BDA85D1C45_94F2B66: He left it on the side of the road in a little town way up in the mountains.
Dialogue.142E5233402497FC8E5F1FA29296B2AF_861A10F: He looked at the sporty kids. No, they'd never let him sit down.
Dialogue.7548386B44D5716BA1EAA4A96DA34493_7D2960E: He looks at me and goes, "Says here you can fight. Can you keep your mouth shut?"
Dialogue.6D243877478FD762440E82ABD3AE436A_97A9259: He loves it so much. And, honestly, he doesn't seem to mind being on fire.
Dialogue.AC21B9104B34346667494196CA8020AD_06FC410: He may be a while. Keep up the search, Commander!
Dialogue.F2652B8E4F5D9D89625D74A0167B7C63_06FC410: He may have the Vinderman AI somewhere in his brain.
Dialogue.55A384004C4D8E5D13B8889257900F87_EAAE146: He missed my birthday for twenty five consecutive years for geocaching?!
Dialogue.927177E94F8DB4A34F1730B79E6BEC8D_861A10F: He reached into his machete bag...
Dialogue.D6AC2E1349161459D70BF983854C3F1D_06FC410: He roams the plains, grazing on beans the rest of his days.

Dialogue.F6C5750A490618EA5C0961AF787C3C24_06FC410: He said to say thank you.
Dialogue.2637A65745B6BCB156A53981F5C3843E_FB122F8: He saw me walk away from our friendship just to stay up on that stage.
Dialogue.702DBB5E4E4F5F31DAAB9F8E7B120EE0_CC240C1: He says he's cleansing the hotel grounds of demons.

Dialogue.7F3F777B4BC7BBE145E24BBEBF6606A6_06FC410: He says this is where it started.
Dialogue.6AF63EBB45BD4FF4F31D018F90BF47F5_06FC410: He says yes he is, love is an illusion, and we all die alone.
Dialogue.00A7C7B942F7689356A1DBA95F253C87_47CFF90: He seems to think he is.
Dialogue.490F456847BF8A8764DBBE86A9FB7EBB_7D086D9: He should have shown me the evidence. He was a scientist. He knew better.
Dialogue.6110CAD9402CD7A5FE5AB984D415943F_06FC410: He stopped responding... but I'm sure he has his reasons.

Dialogue.A302CBBC40A7C1044EA669AAF6E9F579_7D086D9: He was a brilliant man but that doesn't mean everything he did was right.

Dialogue.4E61657045AE909CC4BB7DBCABCECAD8_47CFF90: How many more of these do we need?
Dialogue.8D6C5AB74C78283A6985A192995BB331_06FC410: How many slashers are we workin' with here?
Dialogue.C4B88126482ECB05DBAB07A427070144_FB122F8: How many times did he just wander off and leave us without a drummer, huh? Ten? Fifty?
Dialogue.0D4CF0334FD9BA318F259F8D15CE55AF_14FBFB1: How many times must I tell you?
Dialogue.FD6B78BC40B17B7ACCC74A80F6205AE3_9D00593: How many trees do we have left?
Dialogue.1D1C36DA4DF6A48873C116BD9CA18DE3_EC1949E: How much canned nacho cheese sauce is there in the world?
Dialogue.76B653EF4B7833A375963D824E0AFDAD_97A9259: How much danger are we in?
Dialogue.43A6DA1A46B78757ED1DBEA87946646C_D87E161: How to give looks full of silent, crushing disappointment?
Dialogue.3AF9495F42465212E7C391B52681DABD_47CFF90: How would you like to be our Secret Santa this year?
Dialogue.0747336A460C5A3AE5B210A8CCBDD6E4_97A9259: How would you respond to a not guilty verdict?
Dialogue.A63D73F04F06A4880BD9C39165D66236_06FC410: How'd it feel to send that husk to his eternal slumber?
Dialogue.3176091545DCF65D0692D2900F97F8DE_06FC410: How're those stars treating you, buddy?
Dialogue.935010414CD13AE50DB291985F40CE01_EC1949E: How're those tendrils of eternity treating you?
Dialogue.2787EB784D459402AF4121A1B38CDF88_06FC410: How's it, uh... working out with Rarnold?
Dialogue.5E6A10D547EE6AF9EB68CEACF2C6D4FE_06FC410: How's the movie editing coming along?
Dialogue.DDF525AC4754C8CE978EF4B307D63F23_87F0BBB: How's this for anti-love feels, Lars?
Dialogue.871CFFE94553F5DC00A9138EB7FA429C_97A9259: However there is an experimental treatment I just thought of.
Dialogue.09B2108F4DA1CA4E1768B4A642B716F1_06FC410: Huh. I don't recognize that station. Let's check it out.
Dialogue.66CD933E44969916E770B294E92D8E35_06FC410: Huh. I guess I never thought of that.
Dialogue.0D0F38944C8F2FB2634E92BB8BF6728D_06FC410: Huh. I guess he's not here.
Dialogue.A09810E44982345D7CAC30BBE82B16D9_97A9259: Huh. I guess you have to experience it yourself.
Dialogue.D355522D4E549A2FA2DAA0BB28264491_06FC410: Huh. I never thought of Durr Burger as a place that used a lot of spices.
Dialogue.400B815C4487F20B85A45EBFBE9FF407_97A9259: Huh. I'm having a surprisingly vivid fear reaction.
Dialogue.B67671AD4F91B721BF6B22B07F08000F_97A9259: Huh. Maybe I can stop with the beans.
Dialogue.854B24BC4AE1CE1F41F9BF97AB58CB14_06FC410: Huh. Musicians, always got a song in their heart.
Dialogue.6C6631E248877FD3494EBF924575A51C_06FC410: Huh. So I guess we have nothing to worry about.
Dialogue.EFE821464D9FFC58648CA288A2AE3253_06FC410: Huh. This is just a trashcan full of knives.
Dialogue.DF54471A44C3726CBE0B3BA55D15E996_06FC410: Huh. Well... he can't reclaim his throne if there's no throne to reclaim.
Dialogue.039FE3A8476C1E011FCD74B66B5CCA83_181CD3E: Huh...I was really hoping you had some great creative wisdom or ... I don't know.
Dialogue.19EF3AA34AB6CF4120EB95A606474DC4_97A9259: Humanity does not have a strong record of learning from past mistakes.
Dialogue.AF133C794BD9D9AA89379086CF2EDD1E_CC240C1: Humanity must now unlock the secret of the age...
Dialogue.8A5082C54078784164DED8B743A65DE7_97A9259: Hurry up, Willow. We're dyin' out here.
Dialogue.8C6F544B4B6CFFBF79BEE2B1F3E20CBD_06FC410: Husks can't be clever enough to plan things, can they?
Dialogue.EAF82E7E436E2790A0AD4E94716502A0_B25AF7B: I AM SEA-INGâ€¦ LAND. LAND HO.
Dialogue.75FEDCCA4CD179B4EBF0088059EBE2E3_FDAEB92: I DO NOT SEE A THUMB.
Dialogue.3C06F17344EB46BE12505588894D02FC_FDAEB92: I REALLY NEEDED A WIN TODAY.
Dialogue.57F89CC647DA3252F7F240B962CA11C5_FDAEB92: I SEE A BASE UNDER THE SAND!
Dialogue.84675F074C880CAFFB274BBDABFEBFC0_FDAEB92: I SEE A JOURNEY OF FIVE THOUSAND MILES.
Dialogue.DC9B36F943E2BC63AF26FFAA59354CB2_8C46C95: I SEE A ROCKET. A NEW SHIELD.
Dialogue.798B15F64421458928261181D8CA8986_B25AF7B: I SEE AN UNWAVERING DEATH GLARE. MINUS TWO POINTS.
Dialogue.8546697A4A70056F04FBBA9E1892D908_B25AF7B: I SEE DEFLECTION. MINUS TWO POINTS.
Dialogue.FE2849564E26DFD42062CA922EA1065D_B25AF7B: I SEE DISHONESTY. MINUS FIVE POINTS.
Dialogue.70FF5C1D4B6165CC3442C280F8A4EB9F_B25AF7B: I SEE HOSTILITY. MINUS TWO POINTS.
Dialogue.7FAE279248B7155ACE928C84570C4906_B25AF7B: I SEE INTIMACY ISSUES. MINUS TWO POINTS.
Dialogue.BCA2982046D1AEC2D411F3BB09B67C84_FDAEB92: I SEE IT WHEN I CLOSE MY EYE.
Dialogue.87020EAC4873A64150798EBB64DBB8C2_FDAEB92: I SEE MY BLUFF HAS BEEN CALLED.
Dialogue.72A61994451C5116214B5AB204A39BBC_B25AF7B: I SEE SARCASM. MINUS TWO POINTS.
Dialogue.B8F80ED442D760C5FCA11998F51D42A6_B25AF7B: I SEE UNCERTAINTY. MINUS TWO POINTS.
Dialogue.16DC300448FBA83F8E3340ACF5659895_FDAEB92: I SEE WHERE THIS IS GOING.
Dialogue.3456F88A486FD4D0FD985390C7175155_FDAEB92: I SEE YOU HAVE FORGOTTEN ABOUT LAST WEEK.
Dialogue.6661AE2847CA9F092B3E2E974B095C05_97A9259: I absolutely love that we're doing this! But why are we doing this?
Dialogue.8CD8EE9C467BB8A61A3281A67C7AE504_861A10F: I actually found it quite pleasant.
Dialogue.8EBB1D1A4EAA31C4472015B4413F2A74_06FC410: I actually have a history in the theater.
Dialogue.C8CB0BE54B1DCFDBAB2DFAB169A16098_47CFF90: I admire your commitment, but this doesn't need to be a deep cover assignment, Major.
Dialogue.AE6BBA7942D56D2FB9E32A9A3DC976A1_06FC410: I agree with the content of what you're saying, but maybe not the tone.
Dialogue.5C13EF1E433781F4A7B5998D1AF7B0C2_14FBFB1: I almost pity the mist monsters.
Dialogue.86EFD2564A427316405B3C8C1CB53F3A_FB122F8: I already have that issue, but good find.
Dialogue.C338209F43DB77B75DD339B596C0A819_06FC410: I also have no idea what you're doing. What are you doing?
Dialogue.4D32614746BABB57BC09D3A17E4E8D5F_9D00593: I also know if they're naughty or nice!
Dialogue.6C0569344365BCEF0F2696837083E2AF_910A467: I also provide the service of diffusing awkward situations. Would you like me to do that now?
Dialogue.D4DEE6AA4306E685D6B65F96CF807186_FB122F8: I always liked talking to fellow travellers.
Dialogue.A0E14B35419400D910C4E2A8B4E1C292_14FBFB1: I am The Cloaked Star, and I fight alone.
Dialogue.C2326D5545EE747C4DDD828988A7BF7E_AFB40E2: I am a True Love certified master matchmaker and romancematician, yes.
Dialogue.6D56642B4BD2B467BCF85092FF20CE9D_FB122F8: I am afraid that is in fact a keyboard solo.
Dialogue.196D64FE4E97E9A18A7258B3678BBD40_97A9259: I am feeling a lot of emotions right now, Ray!
Dialogue.22454CDA45B189593BDF3BA362CF1555_06FC410: I am further sorry to announce that we are now... enemies.
Dialogue.3A40949C40DF9F789782F7BF4446C09F_06FC410: I am getting the sense, though, that you two may not be the most experienced pirates.
Dialogue.D69CCC1B4AF4EE7DA72BDE8C8EABAF3D_861A10F: I am not in love with the husks!
Dialogue.2CAC4DCE461CDB4C8EE67F970101B6C8_910A467: I am not programmed to take sides.
Dialogue.604E533A4D151B28796C4BA957D70BD7_97A9259: I am now asking your otherworldly permission to read your ghost diary.
Dialogue.06D87255456E747C776CAE9EE18619B8_84C369E: I am profoundly moved by your dancing.
Dialogue.0B7FA4E340F7AD7507D38DBB6FEDF671_910A467: I am programmed to see all sides.
Dialogue.2B22DD1344E7D8B5C6B1CDAAD113B605_47CFF90: I am ready to take charge of Homebase HR and training.
Dialogue.B24EB34E4BEC6BF9F6159798EFE5B7E3_06FC410: I am so happy to hear you say that, Penny, you can do better. So. Much. Better.
Dialogue.F1E19D5043AA1595C26E08B8CFED4B9D_06FC410: I am so serious. Can we not?
Dialogue.F18872F2468E22CC0E3C0D826321F1C5_06FC410: I am so sorry about that. But the good thing is, you're alive.
Dialogue.1024D2C64C6A6AF4DDBA36A3EC1AE505_06FC410: I am sorry, I can't do that.
Dialogue.1E9919BF469CAFC4800B0A9F567DD6F6_21EB734: I am the hero you need. I can uniquely benefit homebase because I can burst into flames.
Dialogue.44CEA4F848DD4D615F624BBB8641FACC_B25AF7B: I am the last of my kind!
Dialogue.5DA76AD14B353DD83E91AEBDC4E4E555_B222EAD: I am very happy. Thank you very much for the husk hunt.
Dialogue.ED4C047247B99EC700D161B4C2FFB194_06FC410: I am... some amount of impressed?
Dialogue.4E797CB24BD4E41DCD88B1915AFEDD95_47CFF90: I apologize for subjecting everyone to something so racy!
Dialogue.17FDBEB7496E18D2E862298B71E40F47_B222EAD: I appreciate Ray trying to help me feel less lonely, really.
Dialogue.5E51A1E043897A9D7E016393CFAAC017_06FC410: I appreciate the ride and all, but keep it business.
Dialogue.2C1825144AB847FE8A04AB8D9CDF306D_97A9259: I asked him if it was okay to go through his files and he called me a "dragon," which I think is good?
Dialogue.32C0DB564F5353C032BFEC8FED68D8E9_06FC410: I assumed this data would be easier to read.
Dialogue.9F171EE0464BF5B63D5C7D867A05087A_FB122F8: I back up my data everywhere I can. Search any server racks.
Dialogue.6E6358174189003BBEB22C878882F6EF_861A10F: I believe I found one who has the potential to be everything I dreamed of.
Dialogue.00DC56FA48A3B009432AFEAEFE5D8B97_97A9259: I bet he got a lot of angry fan letters.
Dialogue.8320EE8A49023764E73B789B991BACD9_7712BEE: I bet he never bothered to return the hook.
Dialogue.34CA213A44565F70E427A3A7AC18207B_181CD3E: I bet he's still in my childhood bedroom. Assuming the husks haven't stormed the place.
Dialogue.6B9523164017DF88C229EA8C65826AD3_FB122F8: I bet it sounds more like ... (Rumble Sounds)
Dialogue.E9634D374A5FC5CB7FADF8B57FE0FA08_06FC410: I bet she was ruffling feathers and they wanted her out of the way!
Dialogue.8048B1AD4124684C484F868E3F9231E1_CC240C1: I bet she'd see you and think, "Well, at least he's not a smasher."
Dialogue.222E10A44412C1E252E51DBB57B16677_97A9259: I bet they have really good food at a werewolf party.
Dialogue.7E1704C94CF10E77C4F9A68BC09A23DA_724DAF1: I bet you thought I wouldn't make it.
Dialogue.5ECA5FB44B316949591D4BBC8AB7ECA4_861A10F: I build a fort, he knocks it down. I rebuild it, he... knocks it down.
Dialogue.6D1E165945B16D4E8028AA95FB079A42_FB122F8: I built a wind tunnel using a stack of box fans and a really high bicycle ramp.
Dialogue.DE635D2842170F7F709F64AC1A0BD25D_97A9259: I can also say with confidence that check-out is at eleven.
Dialogue.5A1B1F42441AE6C3B6F1FE81AC95D697_FB122F8: I can be two things, little robot.
Dialogue.8EEE04F946FBBBD3F9AC69BA2EE25485_CC240C1: I can do that! Let me do that, please? Please?
Dialogue.A8AC95AF4B89DB2F5B4082B37E73BE56_06FC410: I can guess who wrote this article.
Dialogue.B9948B2F4E52FD608385B9A251205212_14FBFB1: I can hear everything you're saying.
Dialogue.60FF534F409AD985A7BDF3B222D9FE04_06FC410: I can make out a few lines...
Dialogue.287305C34F5DE5AF4AE6A3A5A65902F7_06FC410: I can only hope some kind soul will deliver you this, my final goodbye.
Dialogue.8AA46FC240C6F75A14D481960C8A8E97_06FC410: I can own being not great.
Dialogue.BD2340DB42B977B6F9897A84822DE29D_FB122F8: I can see some of the holes in the timelines. On the scale of stable to time-mush, we're looking.. squishy.
Dialogue.452808BA4D11427642E6BF8E8429F6F1_910A467: I can see their side of it. I mean, we found the equipment as well, so they have as much claim to it as we do.
Dialogue.FB4DB9504A9E20A890B03081D7750180_B68F328: I can see your hand, Lars.
Dialogue.3C139B0A4C001250CFA617A54C2694CD_910A467: I can still be the best Chief Conflict Resolution Officer in the fleet, but now... I want to have opinions of my own, too.
Dialogue.01A2E89F4E5305E0D811DE9CF670004A_CC240C1: I can still feel the cold tendrils of eternity wrapped around my wrist, pulling ever onward towards the grave!
Dialogue.23C9383F4F649F5424E04F97A9AE958C_94F2B66: I can take care of myself.
Dialogue.AAB4C5AD4CA57FB92F7CA785D268C40B_06FC410: I can tell from the tiny strips of holes on the sides.
Dialogue.0147F786493F6720581EB1A8E87746ED_FB122F8: I can use this to develop a matrix array to compare to the new formation velocities.
Dialogue.278DE34340365C4016CE45A1B4F80F5A_06FC410: I can't believe I fell for the ol' cursed grave trick again!
Dialogue.73A48CBF46124D1FD15C8DBE08E42C3E_FB122F8: I can't believe I made it!
Dialogue.8DAD3B69424C086591BE569BEB8758E7_D87E161: I can't believe she just admits it.
Dialogue.1D2D35E14BF2F3337C09E48A79189A30_97A9259: I can't believe we have Batquake royalty at Homebase!
Dialogue.2CC72BA04045FE4E7A025F94EE16D59A_06FC410: I can't even work up a mild crush. I haven't even been weird around a barista in like six months!
Dialogue.BF7D08694D4AFEA1AECB869E04224732_181CD3E: I can't figure out what went wrong for me.
Dialogue.9453699F486AE447363875896C1AAE69_21EB734: I can't fly, and I don't have heat vision...
Dialogue.8D2C7B7049B7E99513E9D9BC1717F39D_CC240C1: I can't get through the child safety lock on the reactor core...
Dialogue.168C1596444E68B4478E30BEDE12D81A_861A10F: I can't help that I love Rarnold, but he's no good for me.
Dialogue.3A2535964950E83419E5E9A4E9CCD35F_06FC410: I can't lie to Cap'n Clark! Husks ran off with our headshots!
Dialogue.B4BDC5034264B2245CD8AC9ED6956CFF_910A467: I can't look to myself for the answer. I am built to guide decision-making, not make decisions.
Dialogue.8FD947124F34535D2AA3F1B45806D41C_06FC410: I can't promise that's the last grave we're going to vandalize...
Dialogue.D65371DA4057342E49798195DABF69AB_06FC410: I can't really think of a way to spin this.
Dialogue.E9AA859F4A9BDD82BB744A99E5E4E4FD_9801E98: I can't relate to that, but I understand.
Dialogue.2E6515B34BF2E12EC8C84BB6D3C17682_7D086D9: I can't risk the storm discovering our plan. You have the data. You know where we stand.
Dialogue.DC24123340D01CAD86C70D99D622BD57_47CFF90: I can't tell whether itâ€™s some sort of latent fraternal instincts, or my revulsion at such heinous inefficiency...
Dialogue.64C4678D4804A8EF0A331E8D111F4CE1_1D2FE88: I can't think of a worse place to encounter a teleportation trap. Tough luck.
Dialogue.AD11AD2B44A35373EC384A8051511B6F_97A9259: I can't wait to see what happens at the end! Or maybe I already heard the end. I can't even tell, it's that good!
Dialogue.BF8F891345A27DC1D9DC6EAA0ED5011B_06FC410: I checked and we are roommates, although Lok is seven and that is... weird.
Dialogue.C156383D48A04BFC1F71F3BC8EB196D4_06FC410: I compromised the security of one of our survivors... and he's on the run.
Dialogue.7813807F4DA0AC1F18B8A8AA99B4A6B5_B222EAD: I could confidently say you have way too much.
Dialogue.45B68FAF4B3FD5AD06627C851BC3DF69_9D00593: I could even be in yours!
Dialogue.C48E4D844F528D6C50207E8D11B182B4_181CD3E: I could have done a bit more self-editing.
Dialogue.6B00EF8E426D6F16981B54B8590FBF35_97A9259: I could make my own video channel and then everyone can see my movie!
Dialogue.A44350FF44308C00F8E8FCA6B2577B99_97A9259: I could really use... a burger.
Dialogue.6DC10A9644DA01FC075EB88FF3DEE975_06FC410: I could see it coming across that way, what with the anxious scarecrows standing in for humanity...
Dialogue.0C32A18447026C004EEEC5AD50BD0875_DB7CBEB: I could see that. It's like a metaphor for your dreams... or man's striving for what's possible.
Dialogue.411A6EF04C65E29A65BFB1997A43875A_9D00593: I could spread my merry message across all of Stoneplankentwine!
Dialogue.7C4E3902484305837CD8388EF0676CB3_861A10F: I could use a slash nap myself.
Dialogue.ECEF0E5745C1E3A95112E590904CECFC_14FBFB1: I could visit my vengeance to the heart of the storm, kill a thousand husks before I'm swallowed alive...
Dialogue.4EC80641488E48BE9B6F5FAF21EB0323_97A9259: I couldn't be a vampire. They seem so picky.
Dialogue.579DE3624A533FBC12EF86BE6CA066B7_FB122F8: I destroyed the band? Oh I'm so sorry I ruined everyone's life!
Dialogue.EA3909F84E1CFE5A6400C3A0FF3A46F5_97A9259: I did not set out to host a love advice radio show. But things happened, and et cetera!
Dialogue.FA6313604C9487487658BA99DEFA9C88_06FC410: I did some napkin math and the current cage to human ratio in Hexsylvania is 1.05 to one.
Dialogue.062DA28D4018E3890BB2C0BD506CF298_06FC410: I did some snooping through Lars' things.
Dialogue.7BFE4E15461C328F927248A82D29F8FC_181CD3E: I did the best I could, and you know... the results aren't that bad.
Dialogue.BA54B263424C1A68DFDEB58C367E2190_06FC410: I didn't and I am a... citizen observer of the Steel Wool fanclub.
Dialogue.8AD70AD944DD3E81D01A2699F592B1F6_06FC410: I didn't go down with the ship.
Dialogue.3EE838D04DC2C0460218AD80C4B1ABE0_7D2960E: I didn't know he was a judge, but it turns out he was keenly aware of that fact.
Dialogue.46F945DE44CAE0B8FDBCB6B775848078_47CFF90: I didn't know his application was rejected!
Dialogue.15A2A9DD47113EABBA5FDCBE59F83DFC_7D2960E: I didn't know you were so soft.
Dialogue.B2D2129B4F9E80AF024BD693037615C0_47CFF90: I didn't know. Maybe this isn't the job for--
Dialogue.EAA5CAA2467A612A0EFCD18A5606ECF2_06FC410: I didn't make the rule. Movies made the rule.
Dialogue.BC498CC944D5B58160C0F0A073F04000_97A9259: I didn't really need the antidote after all.
Dialogue.B317073A4F8875AAC6BC36A1497A1432_06FC410: I didn't think I could like Steel Wool any more than I already did.
Dialogue.B2680FB94C686AC0B6223CAB5D3E9C09_06FC410: I didn't think anything was gonna cheer me up today, I really did not. But there's you with the photo finish.
Dialogue.466E40BC49AD3001D307AD9C464FFC54_06FC410: I do feel a little bad about this.
Dialogue.7216BA3C401BBD6826F1F28F74BE43EA_94F2B66: I do have that going for me.
Dialogue.0D0F8A414B47AE36F5CA4197BD46E2BE_06FC410: I do love a good statue toppling.
Dialogue.C0143D6D47DE79EC68B44D86D33116ED_94F2B66: I do not believe in curses... except for a case like this. Sorry, soldier.
Dialogue.E4230A4F41D823299AB1A6A1E024BBE1_B25AF7B: I do not need to be fixed. My primal scream therapy module is still functional.
Dialogue.C00BDCB44B68D22A9E74F5A9F7B8A420_8DEFB9E: I do not understand the command "shut up."
Dialogue.10CBD60D4811E6C71B150F8791C03301_9801E98: I do not understand what's going on with these rocks...
Dialogue.B2A7DF44470A51C74DEB068D00F6832A_7D086D9: I do not understand why this isn't working.
Dialogue.039C239A4B4AFD9FA597B2A8073849C1_47CFF90: I do worry that once I turn, you all may not be safe.
Dialogue.A91D393D451D25A15D88ED80359972BA_06FC410: I don't care for your inflection.
Dialogue.0E45157540873E3F5683A1B777B0425E_EC1949E: I don't do the past. I like the now.
Dialogue.B55A50CB4B98E238C878D99CA507E967_FB122F8: I don't even know what to say.
Dialogue.9BA17A894D03C8FF3959AC92CF1CB5F9_47CFF90: I don't even want to read the Table of Contents!
Dialogue.D2A3C1DB4870EB4D64AB9CB1E9BABCC8_06FC410: I don't ever understand anything. But it's nice to know I'm coming across as confident.
Dialogue.3D0891CE4E065535DAF13C8169089A45_181CD3E: I don't exactly see "Insecure Depression Man" flying off the shelves.
Dialogue.2D78169647CABD108128ECA3A2CE65BE_B229E47: I don't feel compelled to listen to you when you're wrong.
Dialogue.707ED31B4828F79A5F4C40B6AC95CBAA_14FBFB1: I don't get a lot of mail, and I got excited.
Dialogue.B8B889F94ED9A6A39421A48D5F30CF7D_EAAE146: I don't hate this plan. Yet.
Dialogue.2C8A4D5A42B5374310BEFCAC9C848984_7D086D9: I don't hate you. I honestly never even think of you.
Dialogue.720C0DA24A87937A1A0978B1A922322C_D87E161: I don't know and that's a huge relationship red flag.
Dialogue.883935D34F314C226BDDABA6EDDC0C95_97A9259: I don't know any of that! All Dennis Jr. is getting from me is an encyclopedic knowledge of movie monsters.
Dialogue.D844DD7446B5E2A7E61D97954D1CB9EB_94F2B66: I don't know but I've been shown.
Dialogue.CF12A066449D394C673547A4AD0E496C_84C369E: I don't know but I've been shown.
Dialogue.AB0DADFD47A629A95AFF6197D6D7F481_C9708CA: I don't know how much time I have left...
Dialogue.1AACCE2D45A0805F18C1A48EB8321D81_06FC410: I don't know how much time we have, but we need everything Dennis Jr. can give us.
Dialogue.914F2FDC4F6BB226CBF5D787B96404D9_06FC410: I don't know how, but the storm seems to know what we're up to.
Dialogue.D3A00D954F3A683C74CAD0BDE98CEF2C_861A10F: I don't know if I can ever really overlook your past.
Dialogue.1D3A5BB4492D32C954CFC081B76F8D85_97A9259: I don't know if I can.
Dialogue.737570F44B1CB6DE9A9644AA0AE5167A_06FC410: I don't know if I understand what I'm looking at here.
Dialogue.A4187E6F44ED2D29F12664AB77E35588_06FC410: I don't know if she would have wanted you to keep fighting...
Dialogue.0E1CEF064A3A7243DF8E549A2342EB78_97A9259: I don't know if that's a good idea.
Dialogue.207185D64D076FBB00192D9A645B427D_06FC410: I don't know if the world is ready for pure, unfiltered Dennis.
Dialogue.64C3C688483769FBBC338FAE26BD58C2_910A467: I don't know if this will help your search, but normally it's found just below my head.
Dialogue.BDF481834004E38154397C8EDD106067_B222EAD: I don't know what I am.
Dialogue.E53561B045DA9551A7710582EAD79AA8_97A9259: I don't know what that means.
Dialogue.1657AFF04592DC30C844B8B47B73EAB0_B222EAD: I don't know what to say!
Dialogue.1A926C0E4B7B32B189FB48B9C192E061_97A9259: I don't know what to say.
Dialogue.75833D2644F8A39D04A6B7823090C52D_97A9259: I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue.CA059E0B4E686ED59D65CD9B807C71E2_7D2960E: I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue.5EC8154848D8A1931E3226AC541D284D_06FC410: I don't know what's going on.
Dialogue.0BEE5B1F404DE4E98D0C84B8F14C9BC4_06FC410: I don't know when he's going, Dennis, but there's probably still time for awkward hugs.
Dialogue.D1C5A1C846EF7C6F65669382A0CA3E82_7D086D9: I don't know when you go so into torture, but this containment design is beyond inhumane!
Dialogue.60687549418F978CEA697689982E53F6_4731F06: I don't know who Summer is, but she's not my mom.
Dialogue.F50B99434BC90F06645678BE2B8C3433_724DAF1: I don't know why either, buddy.
Dialogue.C325D5B742136F9C18D01690C76B1EDB_06FC410: I don't know why everyone doesn't make a movie. This is pretty easy.
Dialogue.05000952442990F352368689609AF928_06FC410: I don't know why she's being such a jerk.
Dialogue.2FB7B39F42D5A7A05DF8528003DACC8F_06FC410: I don't know why the SEE-bots are so nervous about this mission.
Dialogue.CB5AD0F6449910E04E9F5FBBA38B1A6C_97A9259: I don't know why. You just make me feel bad.
Dialogue.955FEDC446AEBFFDF147D7998CAF3D1E_EECA944: I don't know you well enough for this.
Dialogue.D06F3A2541B4F189C4423A89412F2C4E_CC240C1: I don't know! But don't let him get you, please!
Dialogue.780E180D4A1676A16DC414BCC8D3EC6F_D87E161: I don't know! Maybe you could... read my love horoscope?
Dialogue.45B400154F3AABC03485A6901B3B44DC_06FC410: I don't know, but apparently Kevin does.
Dialogue.B829A6C749F4A86B7D5930BCE1E4D9C0_06FC410: I don't know. But you'll be happy to hear we're readying a stagecoach fleet.
Dialogue.0FC64889421E92598B6B35A6E2752A3F_06FC410: I don't know. Haunted is just such a weird place to start from.
Dialogue.278A69B74A02218E1CF4898B36F6E206_DB7CBEB: I don't know... Actually, I'm starting to wonder...
Dialogue.7DE8172B4F2037B7456480B3B4503FB5_84C369E: I don't know... I feel really awful. All the time!
Dialogue.E0F9AE0244DDB13F5C1590A2BBFDEC1C_97A9259: I don't like sweet, Ray! I'm a salty kind of guy.
Dialogue.FCA25911459803254BFE49BC1EAEEA84_47CFF90: I don't like the sound of this.
Dialogue.ACE8DBC24A7C0AF1DF62C7AFE0ECFB36_97A9259: I don't make the rules, Dire. The book says you're supposed to be on a leash.
Dialogue.0335DD154A55184F8BB695937989AC59_47CFF90: I don't mean to be critical of your process, Ray... but perhaps you could move on to Robotics Manual Volume Two.
Dialogue.D6CB24C54558B77207A8A4AB38A0EEAA_47CFF90: I don't mind it. I know they're going to a good home.
Dialogue.623E883D4196710A976E2D9266719904_FB122F8: I don't need sleep. I need star maps. As many as you can find.
Dialogue.230051024FFB48A7153F9BB10971B1B3_97A9259: I don't need your pity, Ray.
Dialogue.F781F49547D828CA56CCF1AB1FA3B17E_176484F: I don't see you marking anything on a map.
Dialogue.D9746AEA4B9EACEC4052C99E4AED1F37_06FC410: I don't think anyone else is coming.
Dialogue.2E14FCDE4D71BE4325549CA5B98FE05C_06FC410: I don't think anyone will notice the confetti.
Dialogue.4A4627BD4EE50C58FE3574A6A0D59AF1_06FC410: I don't think he heard me.
Dialogue.6674C89649E97D4808152FA82D584DEE_861A10F: I don't think he was aware of the etiquette of the situation.
Dialogue.DA8EB4D64F7731F89C2BB08B823F6771_06FC410: I don't think one present's gonna cut it man.
Dialogue.80060FAE42FB1343A2A48DA40C3BE991_94F2B66: I don't think she'd be too excited to see me.
Dialogue.CB2F1A1042635F8BD2ACE29329A2412E_181CD3E: I don't think that will ever happen again for me.
Dialogue.DE539B41440DEC21174B81885779E744_B222EAD: I don't think the husk hunt is working.
Dialogue.88A021EF4103757AA6664588DB8E9DF9_06FC410: I don't think throwing another robot at the problem will fix anything.
Dialogue.CE811BF34CAD7992899B20BC86B5A74D_9801E98: I don't think we'll be driving limos just yet.
Dialogue.BE675D4148E59393175AB4BF1E3A0CB9_9D00593: I don't think you understand. This is not nearly enough cheer for a respectable Holiday Kingdom.
Dialogue.F0C284504F06D7E8A53EDBA92EC848F2_181CD3E: I don't think you want that.
Dialogue.2DCCA86647F6A748A66BD197C802862D_06FC410: I don't think... oh, yep, there it is. Ooh, that is a gut punch.
Dialogue.EFFF57174EFF36D5095CC49FB60C7C08_06FC410: I don't understand that at all.
Dialogue.4CF344E7402433D0A60B4288539051EF_06FC410: I don't understand that at all.
Dialogue.C08E731D45C1DD9582E0C0967362F6D2_06FC410: I don't understand this stupid game we're playing.
Dialogue.0372B3E44FB7C0234E8D50912004E705_06FC410: I don't wanna. It's... people are gonna expect it.
Dialogue.1ABEA259459842BDFAA13782768B0790_CC240C1: I don't want anything from you.
Dialogue.7F6E1AF54A794789E8FC6E95F089F7FC_B25AF7B: I don't want this sentimental garbage.
Dialogue.D086F7054AF259AF69149E885D395BEC_4731F06: I don't want to be here anymore.
Dialogue.882B7424410AEC43DFA641AB2F839819_4731F06: I don't want to be here.
Dialogue.D254740740F7DD35324413A160F9E74F_CC240C1: I don't want to be mean, but Ray did leave me with a couple of house rules.
Dialogue.0712FB5F4D3AAEB0470FEB865A6C9BAF_B222EAD: I don't want to spend eternity with them.
Dialogue.8E3AB7CC496C99BD5030D794A86C4FEF_97A9259: I don't want to talk right now, okay?
Dialogue.505683C24A648E65D862A3ADE672755F_A96EA86: I don't want you or anyone else coming near me.
Dialogue.D35B003B4DB8B02F3F27B4AFF44800EB_72190CE: I don't-- Why would you slap a parrot?!
Dialogue.25640FE941362D596187179A679CDA67_FB122F8: I dunno man. Trying to fight mass nihilistic despair? Sounds way too hard.
Dialogue.37EC837843CC09B26B65D284F433F91A_724DAF1: I dunno. Something good to look at?
Dialogue.6197F48E4D94B1BBEBB86AA41AFC3856_47CFF90: I explained it all in the memo. Remember? The one you totally read?
Dialogue.5D957A8C4C944E181CE814B20C4A3DFF_06FC410: I fear that I will never again hold you in my arms, and never again see your kind eyes.
Dialogue.8B9CBDA348563BC4CD2202AB5E47D898_FB122F8: I feel as if I've unleashed a great evil upon this world.
Dialogue.05B40EF149A28F623AF22184D173CA32_06FC410: I feel kind of bad rummaging through Lars' stuff.
Dialogue.073D8E334535F8608EEC979B1D55F319_06FC410: I feel like I'd remember saying something like that.
Dialogue.C3B2383A4493C106DE885F9255A76159_06FC410: I feel like I'm learning a lot about Lars.
Dialogue.7CBF3B024C17FF731FDE8FBA214E9545_06FC410: I feel like we had so much more to talk about.
Dialogue.060501B149ABE535E9CF2392AFED4779_06FC410: I feel more like myself already.
Dialogue.70ED5DA2449E93D62849C298035C714F_861A10F: I feel my forts getting stronger already!
Dialogue.FF7BDC024D6D4FBAD72B37AB4AFD549B_06FC410: I feel so guilty. I'm just such a screw-up.
Dialogue.7C546DB844A41229A5061085FAE36ED8_CC240C1: I fell in a puddle, sir!
Dialogue.9A8989A8418219EDD0B5E5957D58BC21_06FC410: I figured we'd never hear from you again.
Dialogue.9A4C604746832C7BB950F8ABD73C79DF_06FC410: I figured you'd never approve of the risky procedure, but as they say,
Dialogue.44F2A71C487CB0853B71EFA284329629_97A9259: I finally finished reading all the parenting books and I'm ready for... um, what was it...?
Dialogue.9876C2F24595F47BE5EB26975A4DCDC9_06FC410: I finished the Soldering manual and only started three tiny fires.
Dialogue.1D09EF734D3E921F80B778B8FF4C9798_06FC410: I floated the concept of the mega-bed back at Homebase.
Dialogue.032700CA479353602977F4BABCC37A61_06FC410: I found a copy of Soldering: Diodes for Days and I think I'm really getting somewhere.
Dialogue.FC2785834157A43F4EFBD893C4FB5261_14FBFB1: I found your little tracking device. So I guess this is goodbye.
Dialogue.C94CE74A4DB64EBC9CF47CBE42DA8FEF_724DAF1: I gave Dennis a hard dose of the truth.
Dialogue.08B00F7340F6F00EBE1D9C8297660C56_94F2B66: I gave the boy a firm handshake...
Dialogue.E9261E0341E091B1482E92A7C6A29808_06FC410: I get that you're so mad at me, but I still don't understand what you want with a broken SEE-bot.
Dialogue.4F713A3D47EE5A30691134AA8C4108EB_87F0BBB: I get the sense we'd better find this monster before it finds us.
Dialogue.617FD0FF45DFD2BA6802299A7D954758_0ADEFA4: I go all the way back and all the way forward.
Dialogue.68E69E6E4CE2DC9186F22DA641525022_CC240C1: I got an apartment in the Canny Valley storm shield. Gonna go hang up my shingle.
Dialogue.CF6A433F48E3C6014B28DFBF3F350831_7D2960E: I got another one for you, Ted.
Dialogue.DE2C21FB4097111D147D098374F1802E_EED9CD8: I got like four pounds I'm looking to unload.
Dialogue.414D4C5D42B7C02BA9E1739B1B58C4A3_0A979DB: I got shot. In the arm. Remember?
Dialogue.4C83D9524ECCD18278356AA03E1DAF73_181CD3E: I got worried that the tough talkin' tea partier I designed wasn't enough.
Dialogue.88DA106746433FCF84010D9790D7678D_47CFF90: I got wrapped up in the moment, but that does not change the fact that he has to go.
Dialogue.9CE6E9B84D424EE98A1B94AB14793634_1D2FE88: I got you that trap you wanted.
Dialogue.9BFD40FE4D43B86F40E7A890A8A5F15F_97A9259: I got your letter so... let me know if that changes.
Dialogue.0FD1C3E441CAE2CC5C43D58D2AFEAC76_A96EA86: I gotta ask, and I am sorry, but I really have to ask -
Dialogue.1388BA2443BC6CB694F26A91B0DA4813_06FC410: I gotta disagree with you here.
Dialogue.5ED80C974F4FA02940A97589F21B6167_FB122F8: I gotta say... wasn't expecting you to be the one to have my back.
Dialogue.00FE499D4C588AE66E96BD81DF63A8B5_7D2960E: I gotta tell this guy to move.
Dialogue.45B9D7F74F9F876462FEE488BFE1F514_861A10F: I guess I should tell you all... I had a nightmare, too.
Dialogue.E3FA20774955BE152E0434A66576B3B7_7D086D9: I guess I still don't understand what you were trying to show me.
Dialogue.2E0D8A684425B02BEB20ABB586BED6C3_B222EAD: I guess I'm feeling a little bit better after all.
Dialogue.9B271BF144B903601EE9AE8756467B7A_FB122F8: I guess I'm just not easily fazed by relationship drama. It takes a lot to make me angry.
Dialogue.197769BB40B4299221F7C9A6A325B57D_FB122F8: I guess he's not having spooky visions.
Dialogue.623527EA4FC5CA6BE6D8CE937DB3BE3E_97A9259: I guess if you can do it, I can do it.
Dialogue.A71796354774E5B83978A7B164A24D82_06FC410: I guess it can't reach you up there! I need a clear head to get me a view of something happening down here.
Dialogue.B64FE7A8411712103A322195EAA3A870_06FC410: I guess it's just nice to think about something other than the end of the world, you know?
Dialogue.A432F76D4F86E314D88B36A9DFA10170_7D2960E: I guess now I'm afraid of letting anyone else in.
Dialogue.2FC6A8A541BA51E9EC49C0AF0D09742A_7D2960E: I guess staying here at Homebase...
Dialogue.B343AED44747B086556AA0A0185EFEED_06FC410: I guess that's Dr. Vinderman's old research partner.
Dialogue.289BED8444B9F6CD690FA1A51D8635E3_06FC410: I guess that's one way to store an axe.
Dialogue.A79858F04BD2A7D4EB0254BE1FD41E16_181CD3E: I guess the first toy I ever made.
Dialogue.675518F6454BE803E0E04EA425A411B5_06FC410: I guess we could bury a big ammo cache and put a sign on it that says, "Hey, future! Look here for ammo!"
Dialogue.EB4ECA9D498B058B7B8C18B01C4526AC_97A9259: I guess we have no choice but to pack our bags and go.
Dialogue.1FCECC694F8429C6199CC28393C58E14_861A10F: I guess we're having an afterparty.
Dialogue.611DC163434520413EC3628E6EC36F50_CC240C1: I guess we're pretty lucky that meteor came!
Dialogue.9D86701345E0EB462C6594AC4BAD66EE_06FC410: I guess werewolves don't really do plants.
Dialogue.F76150B5447CD9851FF64B8377BA6F1B_97A9259: I guess you'll have to figure that out yourself.
Dialogue.7F16550A40847D46971D5EA61936AFE7_06FC410: I guess, but what if I was actually looking for old socks?
Dialogue.66CC35504E9A48C7C7CE07AC977BF519_EAAE146: I guess. But I was sort of expecting it to feel more... special? Like I would just know, yâ€™know?
Dialogue.127A28BE43CA237F0BAE51AFA172E64C_9F725B6: I guess... I think about how I'm feeling.
Dialogue.859C1CA641CB9B2BE4CAC2AC750A88D7_06FC410: I had hoped we could learn to live in peace with the bees, because honey is great.
Dialogue.3327AACD4F21A4DCC282309A46FB9F23_724DAF1: I had some great plans for this secret track, but like I said... I'll getcha next time.
Dialogue.4C7962604A5146D02607D79942D7CFB9_06FC410: I had to listen to Vinyl Dave explain why jazz is the only honest music to get that record.
Dialogue.B41CD7174D96A5F4737747919643EDFF_06FC410: I hate to ask, but can you send your data?
Dialogue.BCE4B1BE42B57F585658498949967414_21EB734: I hate to be a bother, but I come callin' with a dire warning!
Dialogue.1F013197463BF4B44BAEF9842B14CD8C_89ED452: I hate to break it to you, but Plankerton is a deathtrap.
Dialogue.7C640F374C5ACC97F03242B8D3273423_06FC410: I hate to break it to you, we're not giving up just because it's a deathtrap.
Dialogue.915E9E0E44BFB82292BC12B36FCC6718_97A9259: I hate to say it, but I'm starting to think that vampires are jerks.
Dialogue.27871BB142014F0EE0C80CB8D3237CCC_176484F: I hate when we get one of the billion-year-old time-crazed Neds.
Dialogue.C71BC9BD4445D1AF421630BB06518CD8_06FC410: I have a meeting reminder to come bring you a suit?
Dialogue.FC41EB2A43F84DA8AAF839A085EB9D6C_06FC410: I have a proposition for the two of you.
Dialogue.E40295DD40614DAE1DC09B806CF85486_06FC410: I have already told you both multiple times.
Dialogue.6720D10142F18E45C8CCFD9DB86004D9_FB122F8: I have better things to do...
Dialogue.77E015BC4EC85CA9162D7F9FF64078A8_06FC410: I have discovered Vlad's true weakness! The sun!
Dialogue.E7C1B42A4DAF1C6B980B69967B9EA059_06FC410: I have discovered more monster weaknesses. Here goes.
Dialogue.1F025C4A410BDCC0B29CC8BF87C3DEE3_97A9259: I have done all I can for you my son.
Dialogue.2812CE09425ADAEBCD2511B651BAEB43_06FC410: I have good news and bad news, Carlos from the past.
Dialogue.DCA991774AFE8553CAE8D6893BA0DD57_AB3C42C: I have his personality backed up on a drive.
Dialogue.0BFCEB5C46EA3DB599DF5FAEBB3611A7_97A9259: I have no choice but to attempt contact with the spirits themselves.
Dialogue.DBCBF06B4D4BE66234286AB09FA94014_D87E161: I have no clue what you're talking about, Riggs.
Dialogue.FE05C00449CBBAECF39D24AA56DE1765_97A9259: I have no idea what that was, but it sure sounded like L-O-V-E.
Dialogue.CEA9B0E84F7EBC6777F862946D8D176B_D87E161: I have no idea what you're talking about.
Dialogue.22B0BFE64C4132999DC31EB791D78D37_D1275FF: I have no quarrel with you, good toys. But the deed must be done!
Dialogue.CA6BDA0442A9CE4D48D0C89861EDBF9F_C9708CA: I have reason to believe that the people who built these bases are still alive.
Dialogue.35F8479C4FC7381DCC27EF9738A60005_97A9259: I have resting Dennis face. Maybe you're reacting to that?
Dialogue.0C5AB5ED4BD9409A01D6BB9025F72259_06FC410: I have returned to my perch above the fray.
Dialogue.16F491B2436C19D505C15BB1AF876B04_CC240C1: I have taken the shards to the lab...
Dialogue.A4BB895D49896BD91761789B7F33E698_06FC410: I have to admit, I'm less impressed with fire than I was before we arrived here.
Dialogue.46A66F894BEC451138D1EDA627591709_06FC410: I have to go for a minute.
Dialogue.0F8A99054D8CA3709FE0B7A65E6E6BFB_97A9259: I have to upload my order to the Taste Wizard Prime unit. It's the only way.
Dialogue.5712C0B144D2C5D87E3DB291A34987C2_06FC410: I haven't rolled out any kind of battle plan.
Dialogue.DABB1D7D4525D567D55A168F49DF7512_051E656: I hear someone calling me name earlier?
Dialogue.DBE76358465B2601F6305C9AB6C47EC8_861A10F: I hear you're ready for the biggest scares of your lives.
Dialogue.1B2DDE234B069A577554B898DCF26739_861A10F: I heard "Rarnold"? Heh, maybe? Yeah, let's go with that.
Dialogue.48FC869744684A3A16C26394BEB6B601_06FC410: I heard Desiree uses landlines to avoid the storm listening in...
Dialogue.D50C05BF442F9E3EC50EC388F1446BF1_06FC410: I heard you and him fighting.
Dialogue.4A59525D4BB9C9C66D3503BB331378AA_06FC410: I heard you on Dennis the Love King.
Dialogue.452B061E4FB483E799741EBF3D50587C_7D086D9: I heard you say "Here we go."
Dialogue.907ECE954ADBC38D043807A0A2CB69D6_21EB734: I heard you was in the market for a bit of closure.
Dialogue.04F1246045EE3780CB369FA46B15038C_A96EA86: I hope that wherever she is, she can find her way back home.
Dialogue.91B64DF64D8B2037AAB38DAFEB094203_47CFF90: I hope there is a bridge, because we won't have a boat.
Dialogue.032EB49D4381D8B2B13DBCA412FD83A0_06FC410: I hope we can find one with the little car attached, Lok can be my sidekick! I'll get him a bandana.
Dialogue.E08C2DE94E600383B9F61CA5063977F6_06FC410: I hope we didn't all go soft.
Dialogue.4DB4536B445EC92E8DE1C69CB04257F1_47CFF90: I hope you can understand that we have to think of everyone...
Dialogue.2FD903AA479F23D98A44268886174FE8_724DAF1: I hope you like what you see.
Dialogue.543BECBF47EDA86C09A1929CE228AA95_72190CE: I hope you're not! This should be very easy.
Dialogue.A983CDA04D338620B699FFA384A6C082_47CFF90: I hope you're taking notes, Commander.
Dialogue.A482190D452FECA0C79BAFB3924A7998_EAAE146: I just expected to look around and be like, â€œWow, thatâ€™s where Jack fought the cannibals!â€
Dialogue.D7DC256A4C4097EF68BAF59AF30F2A52_B222EAD: I just got sick and didn't get better.
Dialogue.F6EF0CD34619C98EB080168A7F9BF760_06FC410: I just grabbed an old butter tub.
Dialogue.EA4D501541069533C08B3495F3824510_06FC410: I just had a bad day.
Dialogue.55A550C9455610CC49292C87302D3822_0A979DB: I just killed a monster. No, I am not soft, now.
Dialogue.8281427744F28BB07B934FA3DD07B192_861A10F: I just learned a few new husk-fighting moves is all.
Dialogue.CE69DD3E4B24AC9F04ADB3A094D38423_861A10F: I just meant... would you like a teddy bear?
Dialogue.627F158F48D018D376323BA6AD33D004_97A9259: I just need to be alone, I think.
Dialogue.B26F7C864704B363B41AB6BD173D24EF_97A9259: I just need to craft the most perfect grilling machine known to man.
Dialogue.12D6A0D749F481C436AE0481074F3B5A_861A10F: I just needed a few more supplies. This spark plug was first on my list!
Dialogue.6B8B10864551BF755865238CFD2D1D80_97A9259: I just realized I should ask you for advice, Ray.
Dialogue.BC720CE647134FFC8DBEC8BB7D215E74_CC240C1: I just thought that was how you normally dressed.
Dialogue.724894BC402F7FB3D068148E40CA172B_06FC410: I just want to make a show that makes people believe even for a second that we have a future.
Dialogue.F7A99EBA4766B1A786A4B795E912465F_B222EAD: I just want you to know I'm not proud of what's about to happen.
Dialogue.F42D7AF54AE7C0260EC879A9F976C959_47CFF90: I just wanted to thank you for your help with all this.
Dialogue.F0BAE42D4E1F0B1AB0D81AB0AD7A4E81_9D00593: I just... I just love the holidays so much.
Dialogue.D34A01384156BABA1D392DB59AC65068_FB122F8: I just... really like cause and effect. Ya know?
Dialogue.F27C61B844FEEAD86B0CBC8379642E81_97A9259: I keep finding evidence of other ghosts...
Dialogue.38F60ADC408E1C0561B48A85DD3C320F_1D2FE88: I keep forgetting to mention the traps. We have traps now.
Dialogue.A8461E8F490E67EEFFB43CB9990939CF_06FC410: I keep forgetting you were in a real band.
Dialogue.A6696D8B463A785C6E28C395D0AF0BC1_06FC410: I kinda got wrapped up in your theory, but that is not what's happening.
Dialogue.26C566464FCF96B6CC2CEF92774E0F2C_06FC410: I kinda want to check your math on this... but I also really do not at all.
Dialogue.7D0C31D64ADAD0AB40A1F6B7708BDD87_D87E161: I knew he was a flight risk, so I locked the outside door.
Dialogue.F76D3A1D4A4A5D8EB307F4A70725D02A_97A9259: I knew it was trouble from the day we switched it on at the Durrburger HQ.
Dialogue.D9EF1DC34143A90BB63B6EBF80B46E11_06FC410: I knew it! Lars, could we use this chart to launch someone into Hexsylvania?
Dialogue.CBAD0B1A407528EB742EF0947292196E_9D00593: I knew you wouldn't invite me to your Homebase parties.
Dialogue.2B24D76D43D8539BF39C38A7A0A7A67A_97A9259: I know I'm dumb, okay? That's just how it is.
Dialogue.3E05C4A9426B22EB81313EA34A732DDE_06FC410: I know Lok has been working hard on becoming a lawyer, but I just don't think this is the job for him.
Dialogue.10E33CDF43188BF5524FE897A0CD213D_21C1927: I know about the Morpho Gear Gang, Ted.
Dialogue.EDBA7A6A411E5D199EDC689D3AE8B514_14FBFB1: I know an enemy spy when I see one...
Dialogue.770C580046817B4462A18D94133EF5CD_06FC410: I know emotions are high, and Cuddly Bears are locked and loaded.
Dialogue.CB45619342F218F27ECE4AACDD2A5E05_7D2960E: I know fear, and this ain't it.
Dialogue.767EF20644D339647818509D09FA9D58_06FC410: I know he's a little rough around the edges.
Dialogue.541F5F644046C0C6DC6F5B9CC6778435_CC240C1: I know how to cause a leak in the reactor so I can make radioactive beehives!
Dialogue.D6E5515748A674EBCDC1C8A7D2996B7E_06FC410: I know how to decrypt what he's saying.
Dialogue.812ACA3A4955D0192BB8ECABB5A9CB20_14FBFB1: I know it said not to open it until you died, but...
Dialogue.22DEFA2B44CD94EB570B769B87D46934_C9708CA: I know it sounds like some crazy conspiracy... but I have proof.
Dialogue.338ECF1A4365D659B9752F8AAD4CBC66_0ADEFA4: I know it's a lot to ask.
Dialogue.C07E42CC4F60B044194CFEBF82A47CA9_0ADEFA4: I know it's a lot to ask.
Dialogue.EBCE7E5043F58F2CCF06D78DCB15FF4F_0ADEFA4: I know it's a lot to ask.
Dialogue.F4BE324F45F9F126AAB925986204D553_0ADEFA4: I know it's a lot to ask.
Dialogue.F8DE84E34586B8AF2684DA8E20704528_0ADEFA4: I know it's a lot to ask.
Dialogue.C696D71C4AB6717E9D06CEB93B25D47A_06FC410: I know it's the last place I would check.
Dialogue.6F4E703F4431BB8DC3F1CD8443B722A5_06FC410: I know it's the old west but did no one use paperclips?!
Dialogue.C34BF6A54ACE9DF50911EAA9EA1D6470_06FC410: I know making friends can be hard.
Dialogue.510F9B5B494B299C728F3392269114CA_06FC410: I know that sounds bad, but I have a backup plan. According to my annual "Getting to Know You" Homebase survey...
Dialogue.63A1D5194D5F20AE75DD49AE31316C48_97A9259: I know the dude from Batquake!
Dialogue.64DCB32649B2B8634B86A49041F81B58_06FC410: I know this isn't much... and it certainly isn't enough.
Dialogue.BD51A589446E6E68093FDE80AEE27059_97A9259: I know we're getting cans, but I packed Dennis Jr. a lunchbox for the trip.
Dialogue.BDFC29954E9B7611E9A9A48CEA38EEF6_7D2960E: I know what I need to know, you go through life with perfectly normal thumbs.
Dialogue.2AFE9C074D781D2B1C0EFB8153142CAF_06FC410: I know why you hate me, Desiree.
Dialogue.A553C4A74C445E93DCAB18AD0E442929_9801E98: I know you two always seemed to think so, but I am not the band therapist.
Dialogue.34E8478F42826FCA895294A50337C804_AB3C42C: I know you will. And the response is, "Aye aye, Captain."
Dialogue.74D523584D87DD54475050A62C437770_97A9259: I know you're afraid of screwing up.
Dialogue.8A98487442619CE1346F998F5644E9CB_47CFF90: I know you're anxious about finding treasure, Ray, but trust the process.
Dialogue.F6719FBC4EC77CF242F6FB964CA71F24_87F0BBB: I know you're lying to me.
Dialogue.BE8FCAF643B883C1F1CAB5B0BF3FC946_06FC410: I know you're not in love with Kevin because Kevin is unlovable.
Dialogue.D14995CC4C5D3B373ABCED8680207516_06FC410: I know you're stuck in time, Ned, but don't be cryptic.
Dialogue.9F2D6FDB40128343424A88B87D4AA63E_72190CE: I know! I just keep thinking, what if dad could see me now?
Dialogue.3A3A781B4E3BBD627D5CA58094133C7A_06FC410: I know! I've read all of your papers!
Dialogue.5A4F4D6342714DF6713D40B07C46FC42_06FC410: I know! Maybe some romcoms will kickstart my heart!
Dialogue.67982F824D5DDA31C06003B072BF6C32_06FC410: I know, but it's okay it didn't work out. You guys were under a spell.
Dialogue.22A8327942DEDA001ECABFA49FFF87FB_06FC410: I know, right? It's really weird.
Dialogue.9535FE7A4F3539691E7D7188E45D84AC_06FC410: I know. I mean... I guess maybe I don't.
Dialogue.F642D3AA4F680CF00149A0ADC40E89EF_06FC410: I know. I'm looking for a solution.
Dialogue.D90813CD4CA9A54BC653878576B2658D_861A10F: I learned a lot from our slasher friends.
Dialogue.0A1EA5194AB8F0848976A8BF65C281A0_84C369E: I like dancing, even without love. What about just dancing with your friends?
Dialogue.D437A5414FB3FD6F227A32920D0131B6_CC240C1: I like him. He's got a great attitude.
Dialogue.4C390C2A4FBAFB4E0DA577B9EE8E2B80_FB122F8: I like redundancy. The more the merrier. I want a backup of a backup!
Dialogue.465AFDC147E082DF6DE913AF1D73A524_9801E98: I like that one. It's called "Brain Feels".
Dialogue.6B86E9FD40FB23FC8D094CB671B1058B_FB122F8: I like to think that the storm doesn't know what it's dealing with. Us.
Dialogue.25E39FAA41871CA7A7BA19ADBC7EBC40_06FC410: I looked into sending us all into space and, let's face it, that path ends in 'splosions and tears.
Dialogue.A941FFA3487D817F31F5B48DEAB5A0FB_06FC410: I looked into the homebase blueprints, and oh wow.
Dialogue.6B3CB8394F2D264DCA95069B15941ABC_06FC410: I looked it up. Jefe is a card game with no rules and also somehow a lot of rules.
Dialogue.4F94F713454A40871C638095E3FA99A5_861A10F: I lost count. Got distracted by those magnificent floppy head puddles.
Dialogue.3BDF66B84EAC2478FF1E349F2BD8AC0A_0A979DB: I love it when you save turtles.
Dialogue.CEA6B181434136B0EFD769814DFC5088_97A9259: I love my buddy Ray. And if you hear my voice, I probably love you too.
Dialogue.644FF9A04133A21E0A255484B6AD30BE_06FC410: I love when dudes communicate by making weird eye contact and playing very important indie rock songs at me.
Dialogue.2D060C00425E9A535FA341AA57C14A4A_97A9259: I made a sign for the honeymoon wagon, Penny!
Dialogue.DB213CC147B923164F34DD9A3ECCEFF0_9801E98: I made the mistake of looking away and then... You know. He wandered off.
Dialogue.985606E342BC5340994BCEA64DF25E48_06FC410: I made this armor for Spitfire. What's it doing here? In a hazmat barrel.
Dialogue.111D23BA4D309331ED44C4A746F2B4CA_97A9259: I make burgers. I love movies.
Dialogue.CFB700BB42CD3DD6995392A9CDDD63E8_47CFF90: I may be just an intern today, but keep your eye on me. I'm gunning for the Director position.
Dialogue.2C17316047914B2FA68579B486C587DE_06FC410: I may have installed some ransomware on the Homebase network which will delete all of our files... very soon.
Dialogue.1E57C0D24EB38271B84F15B8E9BD2609_7D086D9: I may have made the wrong decision, but I stand by it.
Dialogue.29BB488344D113A36B5CD0B45665F914_47CFF90: I may have oversold the appeal of peg legs. I won't do it again.
Dialogue.4FCBE2FC4C6E24506450EE8E397CDB22_FB122F8: I mean I guess that makes sense.
Dialogue.1C0141394181C01461C8A2A59946859B_97A9259: I mean I was... but then I just-- I suddenly lost focus.
Dialogue.16661CF645F65336E208FA8AA3D932AA_06FC410: I mean it. People will panic.
Dialogue.553534734F64A77314752F80CEC53B61_47CFF90: I mean like â€œLook out! Itâ€™s the Dread Pirate ...Blakebeard.â€ â€œOnly one pirate could be behind this reign of terror: ...Blakebeard?â€
Dialogue.3018DA1347CE059C8A9B03938EB6B6BC_06FC410: I mean, I am aware and conscious of what I'm doing. Thank you very much.
Dialogue.D900E81343031A006E32A79EE13BC553_97A9259: I mean, I broke time last week.
Dialogue.20841CB4474BBFDB196FD98FC743E43D_D87E161: I mean, I really, really hope so...
Dialogue.A5F43D174CF9E9C035E11697F3828580_97A9259: I mean, I'm not not getting the appeal.
Dialogue.0C70D3AB46C8C73DABB195AC450EF0F1_06FC410: I mean, clearly they're not from the future and on a mission to stop Dennis Jr from leading the resistance...
Dialogue.49D48C51453EB57CD92F85BAD7B7989A_06FC410: I mean, do not take pride in this.
Dialogue.1A9D592A4E3BAEE1C9B71A98719503D6_B222EAD: I mean, dying is one of the critical steps.
Dialogue.4F80F6554BEA03D7EE22A794F15B9DED_97A9259: I mean, if Darwin were here, he would be very upset. Because this is not what survival of the fittest looks like.
Dialogue.A43145D44686BBF7332B72B1F683DD30_06FC410: I mean, if some were big and others were small, how do you choose who sleeps where?
Dialogue.0577401E4EE46CC65D3553BDF2BD08C5_97A9259: I mean, love's a nightmare, no doubt. But, you know, you can't knock it 'til you've tried.
Dialogue.0AE1E67C47A09B9139CE61932EAD734F_06FC410: I mean, specifically in this instance.
Dialogue.2516D7124612670B5A5D1A94E15FBBEE_06FC410: I mean, sure there's a new chapter of the guidebook about Vlad's return to Hexsylvania.
Dialogue.0EC15DBE4F50FCD182AC239918225136_B222EAD: I mean, the whole "sheets are a ghost" thing went out with gaslamps and chimney sweeps.
Dialogue.F011C27E426FCC5F6C2C40B66CED7747_72190CE: I mean, this is so good it makes me regret stealing so much stuff from Homebase.
Dialogue.978E350541A6D0C365CCD39733963B5D_06FC410: I mean, we all knew I was going to tag him before releasing him to the wild.
Dialogue.4FC53F084B0DEFCE8D382DB790B1B333_06FC410: I mean, who am I to talk about decor, but I can't imagine buying one of those husks paintings...
Dialogue.7DFA551A4C82BB924CA5BD8297524F6A_06FC410: I mean, why haven't we thought of it before?
Dialogue.0DCE62FC44A4D82E35025CA6E8FFBF12_724DAF1: I mean, you know, It's still early access. But, uh... you know, point made.
Dialogue.518C88F341874EBFCBE32F97DBCE92DD_97A9259: I mean. We're the good guys.
Dialogue.D28882494F7F6BA5747B52ADDEDFBA88_06FC410: I mean... I don't know. The endless parade of horrors kinda threw off my barometer.
Dialogue.0A9A05A34CEE159BB0ABF790E7D956EB_06FC410: I mean... I even... I- I bought Lok a voice pack.
Dialogue.08CD60754AD6749E0EF8F289B4CE8268_06FC410: I mean... If I didn't know better, I'd say this was the work of Dr. Vinderman.
Dialogue.549633384056191692D0D1B721ABD742_47CFF90: I mean... if you agree to stop attacking us, roar angrily.
Dialogue.2E7BAA434AD29F4B46BF59B83E05B4BF_47CFF90: I mean... why are you collecting freezer parts?
Dialogue.F8F3DCCD4C864DC3387B5B8697FD7219_7D086D9: I mean... worry about it, but don't do anything about it.
Dialogue.6100242F49CA0479931A929EF9A888C3_06FC410: I met Cap'n Clark. The real Cap'n Clark. She is here and I met her. Get me episodes!
Dialogue.B6D073C6434B29241A1DE9B8AF08F66F_97A9259: I met a really cute doctor.
Dialogue.F49BDC9444EF03CBC4382C9CF8F3EF3F_97A9259: I miss my mom so much, but we can't end up in the same afterlife.
Dialogue.59EE20C049146E0766C1C79ECE51143A_FB122F8: I miss the days when we were only worried about monsters.
Dialogue.69681AE949F7D3FF827199BA44ECEE82_47CFF90: I must insist that you've collected enough ornaments.
Dialogue.760D5F794290A5B23AE037A3E9A884BC_97A9259: I need clocks. As many as you can find.
Dialogue.AC9366994E2F8B9BE05BBB9CD48AFFE4_97A9259: I need teddy bears and stuffed Quackleses!
Dialogue.149D36DB486C2EC1E94B1982AB7EBC79_06FC410: I need to find a way to listen to this.
Dialogue.4A78144D4FB7B3BE1475EAA8E0842F1F_AB3C42C: I need to get back into character... Do you mind if Cap'n Clark takes point?
Dialogue.A138F02C41CFB94F459DCE97832DE45D_FB122F8: I need to juice up multiple sensory sectors, plus give the pattern recognition pipeline a kick in the pants.
Dialogue.DF7B9010459FE024257729A326751EFA_7D2960E: I need to know for my mental health... Are you busting my chops right now?
Dialogue.A80F35824196E1CE9B6BC48A724A92AD_FB122F8: I need to think about this.
Dialogue.D8C4FFC54EDC340EBF6E14A01EB76B3C_97A9259: I never knew a werewolf could have social anxiety.
Dialogue.26DF641145F54324419A8B8103894289_9D00593: I never went to bomb school.
Dialogue.C87E627F48C74C3E4A7DC9AC4D988252_B222EAD: I only made the shower head pour blood once. Okay, twice.
Dialogue.284A8A3E43167F9C01B0CFAB4E87FDBB_14FBFB1: I owe you an apology. And a thank you. So I made you something.
Dialogue.7DCDE56C4FE4178E8859639C147DEE95_FB122F8: I owe you one Little Robot.
Dialogue.B1CA7C7C478D8E075C331EA9E138639A_06FC410: I paired you two for a reason.
Dialogue.4E3456E74221598FCAF48FA812239451_06FC410: I picked up some of the work she left behind...
Dialogue.BEB83C4E4FC791718F3CA2966E463D78_47CFF90: I prefer â€œwhatchamacallems.â€ But, yes, your point still stands. Eagle Eye? Send the next coordinates our way.
Dialogue.D56CB0D84519B274A63712B702021892_A96EA86: I probably don't need to tell you that the hero community is not happy about those fliers.
Dialogue.C14B8FE045455178CDA27CBB2BE5C123_06FC410: I probably shouldn't give anyone ideas.
Dialogue.531BAC9247EAC0329463F3BB80313552_06FC410: I promise I wasn't trying to bum you out with this mission.
Dialogue.D4E9B0454BDACB12D970C293AEE351B1_06FC410: I promise you, this isn't the end.
Dialogue.33666A854CAA68DB63C44AB2E76281DF_C9708CA: I promised you some good news, and I intend to deliver before the generators die.
Dialogue.BE16AAB84D8540421D254D87075820EA_06FC410: I ran some simulations and Carlos's chances of surviving in that region of the storm are depressingly low.
Dialogue.40789BE145E37DEBA9FC1FA346E56EBB_861A10F: I read that cover to cover so many times as a child.
Dialogue.2E7E5CB0407A106F978E29BF3833CA23_7D086D9: I read the letter you wrote me.
Dialogue.15BC9D5D4378A53749DD74B6FF53531B_9801E98: I read through the research the... other Syd completed and it is miles beyond me.
Dialogue.4DB415AD4A94926CB07E00BAC0FBF50E_06FC410: I really am working on a better plan.
Dialogue.B8379AA5458C3E5D622EFF92E4CA28BF_B222EAD: I really appreciate you trying to cheer me up, but it's just a little... old fashioned.
Dialogue.158DF53A4C6E18E0069E13A963B710FA_0ADEFA4: I really can't leave without it.
Dialogue.9564F716437CC48F94DD7EB3CA1BD841_0ADEFA4: I really can't leave without it.
Dialogue.5BAD52154311ED097FDADD99E7BC67D4_0ADEFA4: I really couldn't leave without it.
Dialogue.2E454FED4490096B138F7A90B3BED1BD_06FC410: I really mean it this time!
Dialogue.3AF4FF334A112B10E64B9883C9523B1D_7D086D9: I really need to get back to work.
Dialogue.A14BB5A64307A6412F32B69EFEC2B7E9_861A10F: I really tried not to. But, yeah... guilty.
Dialogue.D0AE1EAA46F73F1494EFB8AD9EC782D5_21EB734: I reckon that right there is the truest of heroes.
Dialogue.25A1763F4481A2914B6F77849F4CBC2B_14FBFB1: I refuse to fall in love! Do you understand me?
Dialogue.A77D4DF3408192B2ABD537BF8BF70B04_EAAE146: I regret burying everything we stole!
Dialogue.CD0B0C8D41927A7724AE3FB9F55380CF_06FC410: I reversed his circuitry, and let him unattended in the mist...
Dialogue.4152CCFB4E2D75F2FDCC7ABC8E111BCE_06FC410: I rigged listening devices on... what were probably telephone poles.
Dialogue.E7CD048F4E52832D133CF1A657A8A717_A96EA86: I rounded up all the searchlights I could find.
Dialogue.7F3A91AD4EB952C05217B8873EE89778_FB122F8: I said no. Any chance to be stubborn and wrong, you know? So. That's that I guess.
Dialogue.07575A48432495221C652786E30306B5_06FC410: I said, "We should stop talking, then," but it occurs to me that you're on that, so... Okay.
Dialogue.6AAACBF04DF96DEF217A6EA7A30E00D6_06FC410: I saved everybody I possibly could, but I didn't die. So... that's that.
Dialogue.5348419C4528E4470B6940B0D3DCB39A_0A979DB: I saw her across the battlefield and thought, "Man, she's the worst!"
Dialogue.4230F8E649D67AEE487544A83B468C81_8106785: I say "No more!" This... is war. Take up your muskets, patriots.
Dialogue.0640243D45894AD5C33FBB85C5213E36_97A9259: I say go for it! Keep the calls coming. Dennis the Love King is on the line.
Dialogue.AE40FFE340B5CB3D421598850F88EF0F_4731F06: I see dad outside. He's fighting the husks.
Dialogue.0825247F4EE66018880ECF9BB9766510_7D086D9: I see you're as blunt as your creator.
Dialogue.7682486A408AAFEEEA2FF68345015FE9_FB122F8: I see your four of hearts...
Dialogue.D7E12FA647AC3A47729737B1113F43E0_910A467: I seem to just be a head.
Dialogue.2104F7EC4E839FBAEB41649E7F72B0AE_7D2960E: I should be out there doing something important, not stuck here with you!
Dialogue.F4FD5DCA4A7DF480A80710B90EAE95FA_910A467: I simply find the most efficient solution to the case at hand, no matter the size.
Dialogue.F7A589014252197F1849E5BEE8092CBC_9F725B6: I sit down and I start.
Dialogue.F291BDC04C82E8EDB367D29F2FCE42D0_0745BDE: I spent a year in the hole. I ain't goin' back!
Dialogue.DB0E8E6C483CFBE308731ABA1D0488EB_94F2B66: I spent four years in Plankshank infiltrating the Harbor Cartel.
Dialogue.EC3E1712421A91E299E5AD8F0B363114_97A9259: I spoke truth to power, and I got a write up and two Durr-merits.
Dialogue.0AC7B4D2436CBDCD93EC79AED822852C_94F2B66: I still don't know if I'm even the man who took that job all those years ago...
Dialogue.59182F984A48FCD22BCC91BFD9F0E13C_06FC410: I still want to hear what he has to say.
Dialogue.8414207C4AF64C98423EA3836B9DCBA1_CC240C1: I stopped drinking juice. It makes me catch fire.
Dialogue.DEBE3969453A0A85FF0CA3BCB444A203_FB122F8: I studied unique storm formations, my buddy Carlos was a star stalker,
Dialogue.A335722C4357618AEFDA4DA4627E3249_97A9259: I suddenly feel like this is a very bad idea... like I'm messing with forces I don't understand.
Dialogue.1BAC2C4D4FB8567098828E86F0CC4A1F_94F2B66: I suggest you kiss your loved ones goodbye and make your peace with your creator.
Dialogue.DF2FCB4D4EEFA6944484B68BA69C8FC1_06FC410: I suppose I'll be seein' you again this evening.
Dialogue.C507F5C54F977A65963254A51FAA16D3_94F2B66: I suppose he did. And I suppose there was.
Dialogue.D6D90FAD4F0C031BFE002080CD450038_94F2B66: I suppose he spent his life fighting so it just made sense.
Dialogue.DA2B3A8D498265E3D363F6B8CE8235EE_47CFF90: I suppose, uh... Letâ€™s keep looking for parts.
Dialogue.1AB9C1FA447A2FCBD84662991156C817_06FC410: I think I can build a lie detector, I'll just need medical equipment parts. Let's get started.
Dialogue.FE14779944AD2372AB1315AA54290EC4_B222EAD: I think I have writer's block.
Dialogue.E37CF7B543DD25DA32A478988762DDD0_06FC410: I think I know a way we can help Spitfire.
Dialogue.D779683043B8E4342BD7A0B0C62D8C68_861A10F: I think I psyched myself out.
Dialogue.8803B0A743D269770CFB8EBC828551DD_06FC410: I think I really upset Lars.
Dialogue.304866384C0281A7F5BBBF8B6FBFF696_06FC410: I think I'm gonna review the satellite footage. Something's not right here.
Dialogue.7C0B1FC140B35AAB9A68D4A39E90D9C3_97A9259: I think I'm in over my head here!
Dialogue.B1EBA4214198C1D35AD80DB0F6EC597C_06FC410: I think I'm starting to see why the storm would settle down here...
Dialogue.AE4C123E4AD88432912718AA8E4B0F2F_181CD3E: I think Jilly could use something new to wear.
Dialogue.5091A4314F4E79AD3665A18434821611_861A10F: I think Rarnold and I are settling into a nice groove.
Dialogue.2614B1E645610692B1778B90BDC1A88B_9F725B6: I think Ray sent me here to tell you you'll find your way.
Dialogue.7A311C7F45376C4E8AB8B29C27017C2F_06FC410: I think even a good person can step into a puddle of evil, but you wipe off your boots and you keep moving.
Dialogue.560625E74BE5519E8077D5BEE3BEF511_47CFF90: I think he's fine up there in his van.
Dialogue.955F97D14DDBDCE1F20CCBA0FE467594_9801E98: I think it's safe to say if there were any people down there, they probably were driven off...
Dialogue.54858FC54F3C4C042E2BA0941E99992B_06FC410: I think it's some sort of letter.
Dialogue.5BA5FE3847E27333E7E2B0BD9655F083_06FC410: I think now you may understand why.
Dialogue.783807B34501987E5D304596CEB07171_06FC410: I think practicing the dark arts is only one of many ways a good cop can go bad.
Dialogue.F359171C4E154119FA3EF8827DF3D68F_72190CE: I think she really wants to use those peg legs we picked up.
Dialogue.96454903483B24080D4930B56AB90D86_7D2960E: I think so. I think I'm really starting to become--
Dialogue.959269E74C6241DA33CEC7835D1DB643_06FC410: I think some tea and conversation will do you both good.
Dialogue.B0DDC0F54E699FDC7FD79BAFFA6A78B7_06FC410: I think that's a dog training manual.
Dialogue.7CF115454C9EBFF66E960BBDD97BEA64_94F2B66: I think that's the last of the rings. So, that's the end I guess.
Dialogue.9A3FCAA84E554F9FDE9AC08CBCB179D1_06FC410: I think that's the last one.
Dialogue.D542422D4A21C5D38A83D9908431A74E_06FC410: I think the Storm King is targeting human brain waves,
Dialogue.1FFD037448866FF7E59E60A3495DB268_FB122F8: I think the disturbance at the end of Canny Valley is weakening our reality...
Dialogue.8B3D64104ED8F2692ED11F907E3BACF0_06FC410: I think the fliers are working! We have reports Lok is nearby!
Dialogue.50E3AF734F4A0DFA6F0613922BBE7A84_9801E98: I think the shortest explanation is... I'm a science based dirt psychic.
Dialogue.3871FE0B414FBE450BB2FBB72CCFEA86_06FC410: I think the survivors are going to need a little encouragement to come out of hiding.
Dialogue.CF91954E44083EEB7A180BB68E367457_06FC410: I think there was an accident!
Dialogue.37A8AAE84263063D2C5A0A953E3EA436_C9708CA: I think this is it. I don't know if you can hear what's going on outsideâ€¦ but it's not good.
Dialogue.4A4826C84BBD533C54694A827AA027F6_06FC410: I think this is the last note, seems like the trail's gone cold.
Dialogue.353214D94B39E974271FD0A7759DD0BC_B68F328: I think those albums might be the real deal.
Dialogue.C8E37E5E4432C25D8483BEB51724C9F6_FB122F8: I think those days are over.
Dialogue.523E1C034D3794472F417EB6190F3975_06FC410: I think we have to worry about Lok.
Dialogue.BEC9F1C443FF2CF1C05E7E959F3588D5_97A9259: I think we just found what we're looking for.
Dialogue.E26FB3634F21E36E8BE1ACB92CBB48EC_06FC410: I think we're heading into a dangerous time.
Dialogue.26B01EAD476365C78A04C69F46DD1493_06FC410: I think we're running out of time.
Dialogue.71EDC2F94C01F88CEBB31A8518BC83BF_47CFF90: I think you know what needs to happen.
Dialogue.E775634F4FC0BFB55ACC738360D1D53D_910A467: I think you'd like me to say, "Yes." So, for sure, yes.
Dialogue.4CDCE4CB4BD43A34C6CD39B782534A2E_181CD3E: I think you're all overreacting here. You're not that bad.
Dialogue.D1A434C847F292584C19D694BACC957B_DB7CBEB: I think you're lying, but I'mma go with it because I want a pizza party.
Dialogue.997048BC4F0FF60DDCC044A1974A6F49_7D2960E: I think, due to the nature of my work...
Dialogue.F8A66F4C42CA51BB1D81F08916198D91_06FC410: I think... he's pitching a show.
Dialogue.B7B7455F4D664B1BC5119EAE8DA8DAB1_06FC410: I thought I could jump much higher than I can jump.
Dialogue.532686E543A5AB03675D1EB208D57249_14FBFB1: I thought I needed to see her face, but what I actually needed were her words.
Dialogue.84A894E443282BA9FCD617A8983B554E_06FC410: I thought he was doing a bit.
Dialogue.32B900704EAD498B4679B2B2EA7E9B0E_EC1949E: I thought it was a husk! It's usually husks!
Dialogue.683AC7EC45EB52F40BC1EFAF82A62DEC_724DAF1: I thought it was fine, but Anthony hated it.
Dialogue.86C6FC1741E23E4FE70760ADC12B372F_861A10F: I thought that was the one!
Dialogue.1F1FF7644971F97B724E5C976425842F_06FC410: I thought they were being really, really insensitive...
Dialogue.0EF421784F3506EAEEF8B2897DF733FB_06FC410: I thought this plan was gonna be my magnum opus, my Morpho Gear Gang.
Dialogue.F768FCA749B31778D2D2F085400431F9_06FC410: I thought this was going to be one of the silly ones.
Dialogue.3A76CA32475CCD85BE641D8AF6EFB8A8_14FBFB1: I thought we were done with this game.
Dialogue.A03F87C94249E6833171D3888772833C_06FC410: I thought you might enjoy smashin' em up a bit.
Dialogue.B10A59284FD33DB10B57058E27DA725B_06FC410: I thought you wanted me to read your horoscope.
Dialogue.C93DCF4544B06FA5966B5EB456E945D9_06FC410: I thought you were doing a bit. So, what's your whole angle?
Dialogue.821CD5EA4CD2AB127370B18433160F66_06FC410: I thought you were my best friend.
Dialogue.1C0A5B9B4B002244F7D191BD7DC9CDE2_FB122F8: I thought you were sending Pop.
Dialogue.AA200657423EF8905514EEBCF777630F_47CFF90: I thought you would, Keelhaul. These are your Club-Steppers. Perfect for a night on the town, and guaranteed to hold up while dancing.
Dialogue.9F2BF3DB4F4EBD0BBAFBAAAB906CD7EE_7D086D9: I thought you'd be happier about the action figure.
Dialogue.66F211C44F73307320138F9A1292B2DC_87F0BBB: I thought... that would make you mad.
Dialogue.692A7A2C4C5A0E48EEE68BA06D9AFC93_97A9259: I told my manager Craig, predictive burger technology isn't a recipe for a good burger, it's a recipe for disaster.
Dialogue.36CB89ED4449B4F2167A59AF58EF3362_21EB734: I told that little robit, if you shoot off cannon, you best be ready for the buckets of mail.
Dialogue.ED3DD4D4488780C877F91882D9B6511D_47CFF90: I told you not to give him your name.
Dialogue.73F7AECB42BF3B766E286786458501F8_724DAF1: I told you this was a bad idea!
Dialogue.4E72D3B3429EC2F7B8C62EB764669FA0_7D086D9: I told you to delete the files!
Dialogue.2FAF3A7040CD927CCBCF2C828788C523_B229E47: I told you... I don't know.
Dialogue.165350D04D9BEDFAA0F1B78BB8868D68_06FC410: I took my stand against that infernal outlaw,
Dialogue.589DB0A143834255C23A618DCC838552_CC240C1: I tried not to say that. I tried so hard. But I had to, Ray. I had to. Why?
Dialogue.BFF072B74B05FDC2CDF983B43BD9AE07_06FC410: I tried talking to Raven and it was very confusing.
Dialogue.6CBAA7AB47140E0E518DA28159B0998E_97A9259: I tried to lie around in bed all day, but I think I have Restless Dennis Syndrome.
Dialogue.D4FC2CA8454A870722308A8FA09491D6_97A9259: I tried to run, but then I knew I had to turn around, come back, and be an adult.
Dialogue.93621FAA428F587520E6C9A1709BD1F9_06FC410: I uh... forgot to tell the hover fleet about the storm and husks and they did not enjoy the surprise.
Dialogue.0C034C804F0D0001EF05C7924E1E0DFD_06FC410: I understand Lars wants us to stop looking for his friend.
Dialogue.BD589E3548862A029F8CFCBD5784DDCD_06FC410: I understand plot structure. Thank you, Dennis.
Dialogue.D2A1A7B146411328092ACFA751C85E9D_B229E47: I updated the plans. I think you'll approve.
Dialogue.442946494112E53FDDB1CCA7D91566E5_FB122F8: I used the souped up van's sensors to investigate the formation in the sky.
Dialogue.B14CF2004A53516673D768A2013E394A_7D2960E: I used to be afraid of something happening to the people I love.
Dialogue.F9C96886456713FC60585CA48158A1C3_CC240C1: I want to be haunted by existential dread like you guys!
Dialogue.D12564C540755C1443EDAF99A140DCCA_14FBFB1: I want to be the man who rids the world of love once and for all.
Dialogue.B673BB294FBC8316C51C328503D49D57_9801E98: I want to hear the top three rock facts you've got.
Dialogue.426DBD294C3D9254AB56719DD4107ED9_EAAE146: I want to hold on to those memories.
Dialogue.CFDF9FEB4EA3EF5496E30C89ED8953B3_9801E98: I want to know every rock fact you've got.
Dialogue.8220AC204F846952E46C3A990588716E_CC240C1: I want to know why the major is fighting husks.
Dialogue.A100043D49A337A45542CE9AA6EE93D8_181CD3E: I want to tell you about Jilly Teacup.
Dialogue.FDE7F26948603A24C5A02DAA6D9191DA_7D086D9: I want you to delete the Project Tailor plans from the network.
Dialogue.313EB4CF486F4B1E4A5144B9A153AC6F_06FC410: I wanted to find a present that says "your boyfriend is sorry...
Dialogue.36BF7155444C5CD59A721EA246FDD9E8_14FBFB1: I warned you not to follow me.
Dialogue.2665811B43168E597807F6ADA8CD4C2E_06FC410: I was able to analyze the missing pieces, I know which letters he took.
Dialogue.E629B8C046B9382832865C8A6DB6E80D_14FBFB1: I was about to administer my unique blend of vigilante justice...
Dialogue.FF7E2E3B452EBB21896D0AA48719617E_72190CE: I was actually referring more to the efficiency and excellent use of momentum but, uh... yeah! â€œSplatteryâ€ is good, too.
Dialogue.2F9165B4461F1DF53FDE36915D8B5A30_97A9259: I was binge-watching that one channel that's all about the hotel's unique accommodations and services...
Dialogue.AD27E9D8456A5D819480D89CFF3FB2E9_06FC410: I was faking it pretty well.
Dialogue.8CF00C874F7148986F4E3B90F0C4040D_9D00593: I was forged in the cozy crucible of mall Christmas. Santa Town made me who I am.
Dialogue.A702CEB04106D90A2DCB6C8AB81F117B_94F2B66: I was given five minutes to draw up a plan of attack.
Dialogue.82E0A7B54056E764E4AC75AB041BF57A_97A9259: I was gonna ask for a trade, but... never mind.
Dialogue.05A7EA92496825156E389BA72F87CED1_181CD3E: I was hiding from not being good enough any more.
Dialogue.3A3F3BB04CF9D0A19F0BBBAFCCEB295D_06FC410: I was hoping Pheobe's columns would encourage you to... open up your world.
Dialogue.77BEEC384A0AD4E1F87B49A9407A7723_A96EA86: I was hoping this day would never come...
Dialogue.4B7E96A94B4E4A0306E06690BFBB6794_7D086D9: I was hoping to have my feet a little more firmly on the ground before I brought everyone on board...
Dialogue.07CB3E4B456A219868B32CB8D8C37878_9D00593: I was just a dumb kid with a heart full of nog... I wasn't prepared for the darkness.
Dialogue.3985D1184527E57F373A6A977D1D5336_06FC410: I was just going to say that.
Dialogue.E2AA915C42C5286D54E02096E99E2F71_06FC410: I was looking at the recipe and you should have had two drops!
Dialogue.63DC778C4EBAC52E4B4F729ABD41F247_06FC410: I was not impeached and anyone who says so is a liar.
