Dialogue.CF39F3D447A112869D24F0B5CADCA4F5_CC240C1: I was not supposed to say that.
Dialogue.2EC8A4CD495ED22FBF5FFDAAD212F4F0_94F2B66: I was prepared for a battle to the death.
Dialogue.E0E972014BF09FF3B4570595765C6D75_84C369E: I was raised to value honesty.
Dialogue.533C83E54BAE4528A1DA0F92BC708574_06FC410: I was such a nerd back then.
Dialogue.A95D2B014BBFF2A203CC82A1D9285E74_06FC410: I was thinking you could throw one of your legendary Dennis film festivals.
Dialogue.8E42006142DE36F6C8C0219911DB2174_CC240C1: I was told there would be a story.
Dialogue.FFE636E049C8939A0F5DEDB8646BEC2F_FB122F8: I was wrong to try to stop you, little robot.
Dialogue.DD919C4C4A274A5B4BA861ACDA6183DB_06FC410: I wasn't crazy about that engagement line anyway. Let's try again.
Dialogue.460680344F2AAF9D959E749ECE6213B8_B222EAD: I wasn't tormented by some ghost.
Dialogue.FFFF7B7447189CB8A45E2A8BC868CCDF_FB122F8: I wasn't whining, I was trying to cheat.
Dialogue.76F894E64CEACF14825C72A175B8C71E_06FC410: I watched all of the movies from the Dennis and Summer time travel film festival.
Dialogue.46465C1646C713B4A04C52AF13F0362F_724DAF1: I went through a personality shattering retreat.
Dialogue.6B3962C547F317422C9ABAB1626E303D_AB3C42C: I will be leading the headshot recovery initiative.
Dialogue.2B9FB65648EADB2C0A2FA4AD35A004DC_97A9259: I will conquer the world with my alertness!
Dialogue.0B4A0C764ADBE1F4D9D08EA7AE2681FD_06FC410: I will haunt your family for generations!
Dialogue.7C9E96D14D464D59445B1293B0E0849E_06FC410: I will make a note of that.
Dialogue.5481B8D448FBE6296EAFCE9636BBF48D_14FBFB1: I will try to move on and keep the fight alive.
Dialogue.2C132FFE4721286232F690ABF91F4CA2_87F0BBB: I will. We're risking human lives to find a... thing.
Dialogue.0567034F48302ACA6937569136769195_06FC410: I wish I had gotten more time with Des.
Dialogue.3562F8AF47697E267E9D5EA10D4C4E8A_EECA944: I wish I never fell in love with you.
Dialogue.10EBCEDA41FFA7365487E0B68A6C040E_06FC410: I wish we didn't have to leave...
Dialogue.F9D1F3DC42AC33A5A40B6E81FCC3E8C9_AB3C42C: I wish you would have stopped the trolls, ED-EE.
Dialogue.2E7D0D374190333257363794140A295D_06FC410: I won't lose my friend to a relationship with a husk.
Dialogue.35C2D3BD436F8C0DC243538ADA608451_06FC410: I wonder if she ever got the message...
Dialogue.99F56F7E4EE26A6B8E4291903BE7AD14_06FC410: I wonder what he's studying. Storm effects on Husks?
Dialogue.7EEEA5D843257DB01BA13EBCCEE09194_06FC410: I wonder what kind of scientific research the Hexsylvanians were up to...
Dialogue.A63AB173407CE971C84EFE857927978B_861A10F: I wonder who the lucky fella is who caught her bloodshot eye.
Dialogue.822B57F442960EB8BFC108AC194A3FEC_06FC410: I wonder who threw the first rotten tomato?
Dialogue.5F195CBB4A33A17B324F71952ACE1E6C_06FC410: I wonder why it stopped here?
Dialogue.384EBD0A44AACD90F4CD4ABBA23486F9_7D086D9: I would be happy to hear you were reviewing his trip itinerary.
Dialogue.53156AA2492435D3767F71A1A62E0569_97A9259: I would be... less sure of that.
Dialogue.ECB2B24848517599F52FEDB2BC0C0961_06FC410: I would love to say yes...
Dialogue.51AEA16F4719884E96F26FB2A0AB20C0_FB122F8: I would never have left Homebase.
Dialogue.64A889B54C3DB993216A5FB019557F1D_06FC410: I would never hoist your mast.
Dialogue.C902D366452A1654E0EBFBA6D8D0C81D_06FC410: I would prefer it if they were crying out for trees.
Dialogue.BC1A70CC4DF531CCE1BC7EBFFB0E2060_94F2B66: I would stay away from that twister if I were you, soldier. Nasty business.
Dialogue.F56D3570427AE53AAA5D97A6F6EE45F1_9D00593: I wouldn't be the man I am today if I let signs tell me what to not drink.
Dialogue.3FA8183A447733DA44F728BC451EDF42_FB122F8: I wouldn't have told you if I didn't think you could help.
Dialogue.62E7924D494EEDBE6BCCD389FA2D9057_47CFF90: I wouldn't have wanted to go anyway.
Dialogue.FDE25FAE443A7848281D2A96E1AB9686_9D00593: I wouldn't put socks under that tree.
Dialogue.5E25C59440047560112517B8D21E7A17_FB122F8: I wouldn't read those if I were you.
Dialogue.001521744E44F7996A0AE6A68E515491_06FC410: I wouldn't want to be a werewolf.
Dialogue.3229C0044591ACD927BF01ADAD6FDB4F_06FC410: I write you this letter with a shaking hand and a broken heart.
Dialogue.20CECBE84F81DA6415AAF08A4BCE2DBC_FDAEB92: I'M SORRY? DID I ASK FOR HACKY AND OFF TEMPO?
Dialogue.13A1793646D96BDDC1A39F9DA322C8AF_910A467: I'd like to arrange a debate where both sides are represented.
Dialogue.6BCF76E347266421E7081E891EC30E93_47CFF90: I'd like to remind the heroes of Homebase, I would have spent what little time left we have preparing for the pirate invasion.
Dialogue.CD3D1F974B95DC0C7C3A83BD266C406A_06FC410: I'd never give your job to anyone else, Riggs. Or should I say, Director Riggs.
Dialogue.89BB752F489A9C6502C117A6127E53C8_FB122F8: I'd say this is what Desiree's team was working on...
Dialogue.81EAC16141158764AFA77094FE53D6B0_06FC410: I'll add it to the list, but not at the top. Or the middle.
Dialogue.C55A5478442F7FCD834CC4BB70785E6F_97A9259: I'll be honest, dancing never leads to love when I'm involved.
Dialogue.8AE6D289449DBE4DA615A094E36EF132_97A9259: I'll be honest, though. I'm not looking forward to it.
Dialogue.CF3573E54C14D596014ADBBC6E337075_06FC410: I'll be honest. Wasn't expecting many of your kind to be here.
Dialogue.932ACF3441E83416E0639F8A3A805A94_7D086D9: I'll be out of your hair soon enough.
Dialogue.3070CEA24B6E300CA6A58BB8CCBB3702_06FC410: I'll be the one to face Crackshot.
Dialogue.EA725A044A0F0B9DE67C4F8B5B33B083_06FC410: I'll clear it with Captain Clark first to make sure it won't be weird for her.
Dialogue.0D061815466D4AA34D2A60BEDF079933_861A10F: I'll explain when we find her.
Dialogue.C32F44074EAAB8B95297168221CA75EA_06FC410: I'll figure it out. You keep collecting those star charts.
Dialogue.D39178DD4D42F5A741A326BF2CC827BC_7D2960E: I'll find someone who needs my skills and get back to work.
Dialogue.ABAD71B3400D78AF2DF5AD93195A08EC_06FC410: I'll get back to you on that. Right now, I have some studying to do.
Dialogue.583B35D84FDB3972B4B72280F965DDDF_FB122F8: I'll get started on the head.
Dialogue.D03795DC406732198DDB9FA11AF48444_B25EA52: I'll get to work on the supplies, thanks!
Dialogue.B1DBD578462C46E74F92DDA82FD40C00_06FC410: I'll give the storm this... destruction is really satisfying.
Dialogue.8B2F88754DB3CD99F631A6BBA0CD90D9_97A9259: I'll give you some privacy. If there's anything you want to say to him, you should say it now.
Dialogue.347DE5D346ED60A9A6123CAD8EB3F8BF_CC240C1: I'll go turn myself off now.
Dialogue.23A77DE44948EF40A37071828D60F16E_06FC410: I'll handle the samples, you search for Pop.
Dialogue.307E47FC4592FB46B32A949026FBBC99_06FC410: I'll keep reading, you look for more circuits.
Dialogue.3E95973B46E9239333E6F8B143DEA826_EED9CD8: I'll know it when I see it.
Dialogue.521BDB734155C711059192A8A9FF9DFD_06FC410: I'll let them know you're disappointed.
Dialogue.B45FA42149D2FF46A19798B0F2ABE78B_861A10F: I'll miss these kinds of trees and plants. We just don't have this back home.
Dialogue.865D11704241CCFD3EAD2ABA0B99DE3C_06FC410: I'll need more consoles. Keep looking.
Dialogue.5AC3F69744D89DB717E2DD9A958F6EDE_97A9259: I'll never get to drop a game changing mixtape, or watch the sunrise over Mt. Copper.
Dialogue.7A9B3766446AC4826E4A479F9FCFE8EB_B25AF7B: I'll never know what it's like to have a friend, or fall in love...
Dialogue.714B7C384EBE8B79437D698EED888AA4_06FC410: I'll read up on this so-called Vlad Resurrection.
Dialogue.AB5E055B4D9D3F5CEA7CBA86AE85784E_7D086D9: I'll save you the question. I did, technically, abandon Dr. Vinderman.
Dialogue.7C163BF649E79F7D33FF1AB917542E6C_06FC410: I'll sort things out with Lars.
Dialogue.F484C48743FC138C99824E889905DA01_D87E161: I'll take ghosts over... the world just... breaking.
Dialogue.FBFD9503462FF1F896FA6B89D891CD11_CC240C1: I'll take that new TV and then I don't want anything from you.
Dialogue.E2E569B54BC6CFE81A8C2CAA88566D8C_9D00593: I'll tell you when we're done!
Dialogue.563A5C7947C65B111F2A75B2DB9BDEBF_06FC410: I'll, uh... file this away for future meddling.
Dialogue.6592E233433CB08D5F3EE1B62C90FEBD_06FC410: I'm a Bad Ray. I enjoy non-cooperation.
Dialogue.097DA898405DE089188ED39A10AA2CD1_97A9259: I'm a creative spirit at heart that can't be tamed by bureaucracy.
Dialogue.BDF269094892E0D848A9EF92586851FC_06FC410: I'm a failure! Just like Ted!
Dialogue.0E92FB19483D44AA175C71B5B153EABC_FB122F8: I'm a storm chaser and he's an astrophysicist so it wasn't as cheesy as it sounds.
Dialogue.1A6EA3C1454A95C57D665980C3D02796_861A10F: I'm actually having a delightful day.
Dialogue.E83F69AF4D2982FB094192AAE5625972_47CFF90: I'm afraid it's not up for discussion, you signed a contract.
Dialogue.97A6C0AB4298051762A504B25F73822A_97A9259: I'm afraid of doing this alone, and I want your help.
Dialogue.69415AC84FBC88DB8F437FB979A75A71_9D00593: I'm afraid that's a di-no thank you! Authenticity matters.
Dialogue.4D9CC5464EFB396E4FFA3B9B16C08CAB_06FC410: I'm always up to something. That's my raison d'etre. I assume. I'm not looking that up.
Dialogue.4803213F4EFBFD279DC5F08A2F7F0BD2_06FC410: I'm beginning to think Hexsylvania's economy was entirely cage-based.
Dialogue.0F4CFFFA47FFBFC7263A4F86ED0088E0_CC240C1: I'm being brave. I'm not even hiding under the blanket yet!
Dialogue.70325EAB4F8CA76F514940B0E6BBFC58_84C369E: I'm confused. Why is this happening?!
Dialogue.0AB6827B42EEA72A1491858FD422297C_7D2960E: I'm done! I don't need this and I don't need you!
Dialogue.ACD797A348102AAC7E3CB8A35AC72664_97A9259: I'm feelin' lucky. Play that tape!
Dialogue.550472E549192FE9E9E2CC996365E20C_89ED452: I'm feeling really blah lately, and that's just not like me.
Dialogue.6C85A3BA422FFAB0F7FCED8CE68E5AF6_FB122F8: I'm flying over sand, Little Robot.
Dialogue.B9DF9C22480472631502AE96424655DA_06FC410: I'm frankly shocked we had so many to begin with.
Dialogue.E5C2B79A4C7F4026520080968160BDB2_06FC410: I'm frightened with notes of insulted. Very nice, Keelhaul.
Dialogue.15CF5920481C25971DA77488FB4EEF30_06FC410: I'm getting a lock on the signal.
Dialogue.FC5A6C714088B9106A34F59B552FADAD_861A10F: I'm getting... so much building practice.
Dialogue.E89A06784D06A50BB956D3A071E20E01_06FC410: I'm glad everyone is having so much fun with this.
Dialogue.77F3C8344EB4B23F922118AEEA02502A_06FC410: I'm glad she actually did find some good out there.
Dialogue.4AE2147342E683B828E70DA5FFD94EAF_9F725B6: I'm glad that makes you happy.
Dialogue.43FBEC71467499EF5381DEA1B1A2A998_FB122F8: I'm glad this thing has airbags.
Dialogue.8737C3894969029506D9549C503FD8CE_06FC410: I'm glad we could spend some time together.
Dialogue.B9C4F04140DBA90F9021F88E89C81E96_861A10F: I'm glad you want to be a part of my project, though.
Dialogue.288F177240FF2DBBB0BA1D864D3A7F90_06FC410: I'm going right past him and locking up for the night...
Dialogue.EAE3490A4A7B7E657DD83BBBA5551749_724DAF1: I'm going to blow it as usual and everyone's going to laugh at me.
Dialogue.68F3FD71456779415C852094AE774853_06FC410: I'm going to get you through this, but could you please send us your data first?
Dialogue.52185241487A928423478AB17A68C18E_7D2960E: I'm going to hit you now.
Dialogue.3307B4D04EA75995E49333AB1A2154E8_47CFF90: I'm going to put some tape in the wagon... just in case.
Dialogue.4FC2D6D147D713DA1793E88A2548768C_97A9259: I'm gonna be a dad so obviously.
Dialogue.FA01403E434B8033CF32A3938FF8A001_06FC410: I'm gonna be straight with you. I forgot roads maps existed.
Dialogue.53FF3C0649081E996AAC73B9710C3979_84C369E: I'm gonna go... sit in the dark for a while.
Dialogue.D453BE8A44658293A9D14E8D0C64A78D_06FC410: I'm gonna have to give you all the credit for that...
Dialogue.FBA4E7CF44B8D97374C610AAD7478679_06FC410: I'm gonna need to, uh... commandeer that Steel Wool box set. Official Homebase business.
Dialogue.5A995C074EB7880135111A81542FEB76_06FC410: I'm gonna slowly become not bald anymore and then invent... renewable... solar... squirrels? And build them schools?
Dialogue.5C2C6B384D892512F4F8FF9E3413C890_FB122F8: I'm gonna upgrade the rumblepack sensor module.
Dialogue.D8A590B94272B73E54D52E967D032408_06FC410: I'm guessing that while we're getting these bikes, someone else is off finding helmets.
Dialogue.72C09D2F4CBE8E34069835AE5F12B782_06FC410: I'm guessing you found the hate potion?
Dialogue.07DCE1BA40D388F012972CBC25A6A78E_724DAF1: I'm here with one of his biggest fans,
Dialogue.D21DA9784E11E91569745090941A0AD9_06FC410: I'm hoping for some classic Steel Wool, but those skinny ties say, "Temper your expectations."
Dialogue.8F71F64944AD29ACF4D02D88722D9E0E_9D00593: I'm in so many family's homes and they don't even know it.
Dialogue.288A372F4C1CF0F0758998A59CFD4D1D_97A9259: I'm just a man who cannot afford a new phone.
Dialogue.31F6C81F4ABB1B469590E8802DFDFF5A_47CFF90: I'm just a normal director, maintaining operations of Homebase and trying to keep everyone on track.
Dialogue.6D2C930646431C9445DB648EAA87BD23_D1275FF: I'm just curious if I'm a spaceman or a robot.
Dialogue.C7EC9CD2483901889C419BBD3EC03EA3_EAAE146: I'm just excited, Blake. Can't you feel it in your veins? We're getting close!
Dialogue.0C26C639480AB93327C105B8798796B9_FB122F8: I'm just floating here! Its- it's not good.
Dialogue.F6E2F3574B0D451357F81A84F3884527_06FC410: I'm just going to gently disassemble it so I don't forget everything I've ever known.
Dialogue.0EE489534B046A76646F4A86CB71F32F_97A9259: I'm just not ready to be a dad.
Dialogue.5F15EE9F48FCF0C3E98584B2F7F4B02E_97A9259: I'm just under a lot of pressure, okay?
Dialogue.ADE103A1480BEA25AD4F38B1E742EA46_97A9259: I'm just worried I won't be there for Dennis Jr.
Dialogue.4752114347964721C5F043A424DF6EB6_97A9259: I'm kidding. I know where you were going with that.
Dialogue.EFFFF48D421B1406A031869B2A1353C1_06FC410: I'm learning so much about ghosts.
Dialogue.B072BA55480CE9318D4AB781C4B19F33_97A9259: I'm listening to the entire script and I still have no idea what's going on.
Dialogue.ACE4FE7D4E517CE4D4E1E7B26C7D55AC_06FC410: I'm looking for the suit, still. I promise.
Dialogue.494B039C4ACA8618E1487999256F47FA_724DAF1: I'm looking to go to series real quick...
Dialogue.C655775E486D7E68A2A01DBB7048F601_06FC410: I'm mad I'm not on the cover of this album.
Dialogue.6D3A31724F0FC39E0D4B1E802978483F_861A10F: I'm more a hammer and nails girl, not needles and thread. Why take the chance?
Dialogue.110A207449D2DB58317DE7BE3728C2BB_06FC410: I'm more curious about why Desiree wants to create and stabilize a rift.
Dialogue.BA54782B4D32551B0C84DBA1BD6501EF_14FBFB1: I'm not alone. All my enemies are here.
Dialogue.DF81CC7C4D4CA7D95C8F6C9F4E4911A6_06FC410: I'm not an expert in this sort of thing, but not much can be solved with juice and cruelty.
Dialogue.8E5B68EF4B5F892F5FF60EBCAFFF9D15_B25AF7B: I'm not anatomically correct? Why not?
Dialogue.5BB3982C40FE3577DEDD24B80AD90CAA_97A9259: I'm not crazy about what's happening here.
Dialogue.A25E7D6743323DB4DE679BAE9A051424_724DAF1: I'm not even sure if I know what this is.
Dialogue.B9C6F19B4061A59A9691DC83772748A5_97A9259: I'm not going to hate you.
Dialogue.1B588371410006A2CFC63C859EAD4060_06FC410: I'm not going to like it!
Dialogue.8B3E2835494B86F998773585039613BA_06FC410: I'm not looking for hate here. I'm hoping we land up somewhere around mild tolerance.
Dialogue.8B247D8D44907FF83AAF9EB31B4C1EE2_AB3C42C: I'm not saying this is bad, but... it is not my show.
Dialogue.6DD6628940790A6C8D8A7CAA88F181AA_06FC410: I'm not saying we can do better...
Dialogue.5E9608D244182B49D4125BA861DD8012_06FC410: I'm not siding with the slashers...
Dialogue.29D383184C0FB65EDC6D6898D9EFF24E_FB122F8: I'm not singin'. It's more like angry yelling.
Dialogue.98B8B0A446A393C8122D96878EFE3302_06FC410: I'm not some art house visionary.
Dialogue.4B8B366C4267D8E11423E08CA1E498AA_06FC410: I'm not sure how I feel about this.
Dialogue.A18D05564F0C4AD6546136807C38C159_C9708CA: I'm not the only one saying this! There are reports coming in all the way from Stonewood of experimental Vindertech gear - Storm Shields. Homebases!
Dialogue.28AD5FEE43EB0B52D990449CA746DA45_EAAE146: I'm noticing that when you hit the monster guys... they... die?
Dialogue.378CC776403899AB3FB541A6787CF3EA_9D00593: I'm on it, boss. Trees! Ornaments! Homebase will kneel to the crushing spirit of Christmas! Hahahahaha!
Dialogue.885872174F1837B9E293FD88527314D5_B68F328: I'm on my bike. Gotta go convince Syd to give the new album a listen.
Dialogue.F86B733A4AB632AA5A4BDEB30C47BDEE_47CFF90: I'm only going where the spirits guide me!
Dialogue.B69713154BFD277FA5A23190556A430B_06FC410: I'm picking up a lot of crowd noise... but yeah.
Dialogue.15D8F31F4D704AE142205ABD29178EDE_06FC410: I'm picking up evidence of a major husk termination event nearby.
Dialogue.93AAC9DC4E4E27021A8AF2AF38BB03E4_FB122F8: I'm picking up what you're laying down.
Dialogue.9333121A4225C4D8264CD48161F44F1F_910A467: I'm programmed to resolve conflicts and see all sides of an issue.
Dialogue.7F0CDB814387C813BE208F83C5AD030D_06FC410: I'm putting the hype train back in Hype Station.
Dialogue.67416F754691E77C40EAC9822A22896E_7D2960E: I'm reacting to you telling me your man Lars lives in the sky!
Dialogue.969467B64C2D3C3FC9F5599BDDE05C94_CC240C1: I'm real sorry you never got a chance to follow your dreams, mama.
Dialogue.375A9D654178752A58FA91BE55930F1B_06FC410: I'm really starting to dislike this Blackboot Ayers creep.
Dialogue.7F9CA26641A98C3553E657817EABE8EF_06FC410: I'm really starting to take this personally.
Dialogue.BF15E58A4B398CB1D489188FAAD6F1E5_724DAF1: I'm repped by The Dynamic Blast Agency.
Dialogue.6070778241360561BB18A89F5219C3E6_06FC410: I'm seeing signs of the people of Homebase starting to come around!
Dialogue.6203C255467E6CD0174B3CB5453263B2_06FC410: I'm seeing some strange electrical patterns across the map.
Dialogue.D651994A42A1DE2E97D99CB645EF9FE7_06FC410: I'm sending a MED-Bot just in case.
Dialogue.B8DC8BFD4E5CB71470B9FC9D1E43F3DD_06FC410: I'm sending you back up above the clouds. Go take a cold shower or something.
Dialogue.A4B3DCBD4F1900414B6C60AD4C0D9C7E_724DAF1: I'm serious! You have got a heart that is, like, bursting with desire to make things better.
Dialogue.9B867BEF499C492DB70F809FC54CA679_97A9259: I'm setting up a movie marathon. I put the movie on, and on the screen I see...
Dialogue.82F4C12C44679A56C2C7C09F7D633F02_06FC410: I'm so sorry. That's not what I meant.
Dialogue.357E2EE1415771C44D7D39904047C453_06FC410: I'm sorry I hid the truth from you.
Dialogue.1886CA9B49476217280946BFE654AA7A_06FC410: I'm sorry I never got the chance to meet her.
Dialogue.482066524D7D72933CD17B95D01DF8D1_72190CE: I'm sorry we ransacked Homebase, buried your treasures, and stole all of your copper wiring.
Dialogue.2A8EFBE448C04D33EFDDE3837B0705F8_47CFF90: I'm sorry you feel that way.
Dialogue.526960F4483B9F6C5C28A98A3FA5BF3A_181CD3E: I'm sorry you're not happy with my work.
Dialogue.CBB5CDBA4F8FB396ABC579A513F9F4EC_06FC410: I'm sorry, Commander. I can't do this.
Dialogue.81B5A6A04E60313A1F5F50AA61E85ADD_06FC410: I'm sorry, I didn't know we're friends.
Dialogue.A0A650FC41DAD93F4FB7AF8C01FA1712_8DEFB9E: I'm sorry, I didn't understand your question.
Dialogue.F0764F8148965C227351D3AC3D7FB5B9_8DEFB9E: I'm sorry, I didn't understand your question.
Dialogue.57CBFA194D6B15EAFC1301A2B22A5310_06FC410: I'm sorry, I'm still trying to understand how Homebase could hate the greatest show ever made.
Dialogue.D25C18F44E6AE1561FA4198AB13991D9_06FC410: I'm sorry, I... I don't think we're going to find the cure.
Dialogue.F224522F44DF876E64E83C9D8BF2E61D_7D086D9: I'm sorry, I... I really don't.
Dialogue.C976AE7844659CACA1E26AB75021FF07_84C369E: I'm sorry, rhythm. I never should have denied you.
Dialogue.2B9912AE446D8D6057AF9896BDF73D3F_8DEFB9E: I'm sorry, the transmission to Desiree has been blocked.
Dialogue.A76BA2A14927B89FCDCADD95B43CA5FF_8DEFB9E: I'm sorry, the transmission to Desiree has been blocked.
Dialogue.C0EE878B48EAD322C5EC54A0506C91D5_84C369E: I'm sort of infatuated with this girl, right? But we also hate each other.
Dialogue.BD6ABCC1412564D8734142B1D8C4EFFA_9801E98: I'm starting to see why Carlos won't talk to you.
Dialogue.68646A834F09C4151C564ABF3D0D226C_AB3C42C: I'm starting to understand how the budget got out of hand so quickly.
Dialogue.E0B23FD2459B65C9BBCED5A84B9B63D4_06FC410: I'm still getting a faint ping from his locator hat.
Dialogue.FF75476C4CA8136A87B099BB90971CC1_861A10F: I'm still not ruling out Husk-Bombs. (gasp) Or Bomb-Husks!
Dialogue.5BD079BC4DCA5B2B993E6A8C9152565E_06FC410: I'm still not that worried. Are you behind the... very graphic husk attacks?
Dialogue.4881B6ED4335AB91EB811B9096587EA1_06FC410: I'm still really, really sorry about that, Lok.
Dialogue.C28C56D54663E8E71F9A6896BD943E77_06FC410: I'm still working on finding the final Project Tailor design.
Dialogue.D3D32CF74D988D5C744BBC99F44675A5_06FC410: I'm such a lazy jerk. I'm sorry, Pop.
Dialogue.B51C816941AD92A1223203902CF19A2C_910A467: I'm supposed to have two legs, but maybe legs three and four know something I don't.
Dialogue.2BB8A8EE4863644E69252EB4041F237E_06FC410: I'm sure she's under a lot of stress. Once we find SEE-bot, then you'll get to meet the real Desiree.
Dialogue.98230F1C4E7C9F1DB5E4F9BAA152DCF4_FB122F8: I'm sure they have their reasons.
Dialogue.976FF26D49A4781C8C2281B6AE78909A_06FC410: I'm talkin' meteors, planetary rings, disgraced former planets.
Dialogue.45E433B4402A0EC94D88C2A4382F1B8E_B222EAD: I'm terrified of what's down there...
Dialogue.ED1ACA814B993F53C234A9B553FF47AB_06FC410: I'm the one who buys him voice packs. So, yeah. It's just... he says so many words.
Dialogue.D7A2EEFF4EB74874EC0F429CD85D0DDA_06FC410: I'm the one who changed my name, okay.
Dialogue.BF2D639F464568F70B649BAF87DD0BCF_06FC410: I'm the one who steered us into this amoral arts and crafts nightmare.
Dialogue.B1FD5B294BA96A44416D52B9EA7F5FEF_21C1927: I'm the worst thing you ever made!
Dialogue.DAC064084510D74C962380AEF57762D0_4731F06: I'm there. I'm even younger this time.
Dialogue.9492A8AB43452FADDE287F8BBD9DB1E2_06FC410: I'm thinking to avoid any.. you know, weirdness, we just push all the beds together.
Dialogue.CB9C9C3144A8CF049FBD2EAA59262986_06FC410: I'm thinking we smash some cages just in case.
Dialogue.DBA5BDC7434CB0DBC371A0926AB2F45D_861A10F: I'm tired of rebuilding things he knocks down. It's like he doesn't even care about the mess.
Dialogue.E136ACDE4B3EEFE0300F149B44D59B10_FB122F8: I'm tracking multiple low flying craft heading south west.
Dialogue.2BBC72364095D283D8CEC0803269FFC4_FB122F8: I'm trying not to take it personally.
Dialogue.21BBF1104F747737DA0815AAF2E72B66_06FC410: I'm trying to figure it out, but my memory is so... fuzzy.
Dialogue.687EDB3349FDFBADEB4DBD949BF60615_9801E98: I'm trying to use the fossil record to learn about the future.
Dialogue.70EE802C4347CC60DB8EA688194A62EE_47CFF90: I'm uncomfortable with that idea for a variety of reasons.
Dialogue.275133A546781C63E8F9608F701D41FF_97A9259: I'm uploading the Dennis Combo to the Taste Wizard mainframe.
Dialogue.3E047DEB40A673567F97659C87446530_9D00593: I'm wherever Christmas is found, Lars.
Dialogue.42D4C0D24F45B896A662EE9A25C403F5_06FC410: I'm worried this is a Reality Hiccups thing.
Dialogue.2AC8A8C344CFB83DE98A5E8BBA59A89E_06FC410: I'm worried we'll be facing down a storm-fueled Vlad monster.
Dialogue.E858D2924235031671807AB61DFC9579_06FC410: I'm, uh, b- building a bot to help me sort some things out.
Dialogue.CFC9A9D040A2069AA5649F9345232ADC_47CFF90: I've already taken the liberty of scheduling checkups for you both back at Homebase because this conversation has been... alarming.
Dialogue.28A169874AC6CA6BAD081DAFFC65E142_06FC410: I've always dreamed of going on a road trip.
Dialogue.E56B48654BAC274CB4CE77857F720D14_06FC410: I've always wanted to say that, and it was exactly as great as I imagined.
Dialogue.2AFAEEBB40798C2FDDBC498CAD29874C_97A9259: I've been crying in public a lot, and that's been great for my self-esteem.
Dialogue.A91AFA4843A65036CEA2EBB76E7063B1_861A10F: I've been doing some diagrams of ways to integrate these supports into our forts in the field.
Dialogue.C0AC93D94ABB979A8CCCF798E30FCFD9_181CD3E: I've been hiding from you for years.
Dialogue.F73C92124E01110B655A1C96096F0558_C9708CA: I've been intercepting radio transmissions for the last few days... and I believe these are the real deal.
Dialogue.F4ADC55F41B52AF037FA29B69B80D873_EC1949E: I've been reading... and I got my head around the science.
Dialogue.B53AA25A42A0E7E658737E9A8544EF8B_7D086D9: I've been running an analysis of these rolls.
Dialogue.72557B3344BC707BCAC4BFA74E0B6700_EC1949E: I've come to terms with getting dragged by the sweetest baby robot alive.
Dialogue.AF19F3BF43862C92A538DBA22B7600E7_724DAF1: I've come to the desert in search of legendary gunslinger, Blackboot Ayers.
Dialogue.7942C37644551F57AA7600AD07523AB6_06FC410: I've found a solution to our problem.
Dialogue.48A1D676479A1B044A427EA2E23681FF_72190CE: I've gone through all of dad's research. He's real.
Dialogue.A98CA24F4A6AC52A14C3B1B720C3AD2B_06FC410: I've got a good feeling about this hover fleet!
Dialogue.2BD029E647EBEE50C5AB01A4B65E6EBF_06FC410: I've got a plan. You need to trust me here.
Dialogue.33A216DC44DC1B2952534E8B111BBA67_FB122F8: I've got a rough landing ahead.
Dialogue.C304227A4DB3FB6DACCBF1B62FEBC7CF_97A9259: I've got a whole new thing to worry about at night now.
Dialogue.70FA1B36460DF0DD1660E0AB284F50E8_06FC410: I've got eyes on Lars. Let's let him sleep.
Dialogue.6FB25828496217D80F82B0A2725345BF_97A9259: I've got it! We put you on a leash and we can go for walkies to help you run out your were-energy.
Dialogue.2C51C7CE404CA7D59E69079F94F50595_06FC410: I've got like six more pages of this. Keep taking out those statues.
Dialogue.D3424E4B4B355A165CA9FDA18EC455E0_724DAF1: I've had that my whole life, man!
Dialogue.B4296CE54C1EF91B6025C49E88756621_06FC410: I've heard people say that, but never in that tone of voice.
Dialogue.2C3A6A1C4356FC82F6B847A5E1BBBAF5_06FC410: I've made some Missing Posters. Everyone split up and spread the word!
Dialogue.45B424054D7BAE008075559DEF1F8F9E_06FC410: I've met werewolves, vampires, um... a merman, I think?
Dialogue.DA1583E7475AF4692B29E5B61C32CA71_47CFF90: I've never been one for carrots.
Dialogue.8E1EBE7941CE3920F7EFF4B96A1879B7_97A9259: I've never seen Ray that angry.
Dialogue.AAD8444043F67441C1A84087C6CD2DAF_9D00593: I've never seen a doctor and I'm not starting today.
Dialogue.3EA30EAF4104C75EB841D78E5B4CCD49_06FC410: I've never seen a map to Hexsylvania, but that doesn't mean one doesn't exist.
Dialogue.8BB69C6041FF3C7A7A7770A5B15A1939_06FC410: I've noticed a high degree of storm corruption in... some graves.
Dialogue.0A2703284AEFC27D229CF0A4D638F0BF_21C1927: I've only been tracking you for six months.
Dialogue.14EF80354B365E2948C78EB99993AD47_B229E47: I've placed telescopes throughout the zone.
Dialogue.83E745A94F34C6D01A9CE89E069AE539_14FBFB1: I've read all of her columns. Many times.
Dialogue.C7DC493942D1C1CC0F5C79B34E4E1D8A_06FC410: I've read every road trip book, seen every movie, listened to every wistful song...
Dialogue.250C2B41456CE05F990D5699E60F42EE_06FC410: I've recorded his movements, let's see what he's... been...
Dialogue.DED2C6EC4DA03C4B0DFAA290E69CB6C1_06FC410: I've started a new life where no one will ever find me.
Dialogue.7F5AC1784F9A4C0C9F1E82B1C7DD37B8_0A979DB: I've traded love for truth, and I can truly see for the first time.
Dialogue.1EC0BFC24D7AA3D97E12CFAABD069607_06FC410: I, uh, did a little more research, and the manual was talking about shared goals, not... shared nightmares.
Dialogue.E920C3ED46479177F6D1CBACBFD63C8E_06FC410: I, uh... could have done better. But I didn't.
Dialogue.77373A4740B493DEF343B8A8D2F97899_06FC410: I- I saw your box copy said you can never turn down a good tea party.
Dialogue.421CD0E84F620C40C74EFDA83AE00A6B_47CFF90: I... I suppose you're right. I've been on the defense so long, I've lost sight of our real mission here.
Dialogue.59B48C964CE3CF1098B9A9A4C73112CA_CC240C1: I... don't know. I'm sorry. It's my first day...
Dialogue.521571C54784BF546F43ED91C2A7C5E2_9801E98: I... don't understand what you're saying at all.
Dialogue.1C59856348D443360F91589BBF33C77F_B25AF7B: IF IT PLEASES THE COURT, I WOULD LIKE TO BURST INTO FLAMES.
Dialogue.01E90F8E4406350DC31BC0A6CA879F64_FB122F8: If Carlos is out there, he needs our help.
Dialogue.2F1F1E184FCD7892CD99F386B67E3029_8106785: If Homebase's lies have you hungry for the truth and thirsty for enlightenment, Dennis Burger is there for you.
Dialogue.8D7CD8544C38C9ABB7A51AA318211F32_7D2960E: If I ask you a question, are you gonna do that "figure it out yourself" thing or are we past that?
Dialogue.606402404EF9F7C3925C2DA9CE31AB34_7D2960E: If I didn't know any better, I'd say you lied to me back there.
Dialogue.9D1741234763EB9F6826A8809131ABCC_06FC410: If I didn't know better, I'd say this was Director Riggs.
Dialogue.303CF896425CD8C9C4DAB4B8B03A07A4_97A9259: If I do, will you promise not to eat my soul?
Dialogue.CC59A5024D2461E51C7957BADB8F4A91_AB3C42C: If I don't get photographed in this dress, I have to pay for it.

Dialogue.422AE3BB41811F560723ACA0572A7710_9D00593: Lok taught me a valuable lesson about giving...
Dialogue.E4DA46664264AE8250CF08B63D9D8EE5_94F2B66: Lok was found unresponsive, possibly facedown - but it is hard to tell - in a puddle.
Dialogue.F35BA5DA4ED4018EDDAC2E934A1EF5AA_06FC410: Lok, buddy, can I give you a little shake?
Dialogue.39C795BE434F24D2724D058782CD341D_97A9259: Lok, buddy, want to watch me feed this teddy bear to this dinosaur?
Dialogue.3AA57955427565526A685596236ED8BA_06FC410: Lok, buddy. I can't help you unless you tell me what's wrong.
Dialogue.E32BA83F4D29CC7B81C1DAB8B28E78C2_06FC410: Lok, buddy. I'm sorry, but this is not something you can help me with. I need legal representation.
Dialogue.AF031B344B36E8E494E139A450DE67B0_87F0BBB: Lok, is this what you saw?
Dialogue.791C69874E59ED487EFC15869837B484_A96EA86: Lok, my man. What are you doing right now?
Dialogue.78904A024C0DD5130B2F3AA352492443_97A9259: Lok, say goodbye to visions of horror and endless nightmares...
Dialogue.C0B67FBF4AF5ACF96ADEAA8044196DBF_B222EAD: Lok, you're the first person I've spoken to, not just haunted, in two years. Of course I like you.
Dialogue.CD54929E4EC3DBA85E13658C3D407623_06FC410: Lok... I'm so sorry we let you down.
Dialogue.B1969EBD462F3F35A35B56B2FE3BE107_06FC410: Lok? Buddy? I have some bad news.
Dialogue.CC5A2870466CEDFE5B6454BE3924D3EF_97A9259: Lokâ€™s present is almost complete. I just need a few more key components.
Dialogue.A73C6756407DED8386CC6C88F3F211D7_97A9259: Long story short, there was a meteor and now there are birds.
Dialogue.A4086CAE4902FD1D9FECE0B4364D7ECE_94F2B66: Look alive, risotto! We're gonna find that monster of yours!
Dialogue.4F4A043948DA3BCE43DB169D81CBBCFA_84C369E: Look at all of those people, just waiting for us to bring them home...
Dialogue.49210CD644F695F3A79E9BA992DF6171_72190CE: Look at me in the eyes. Do I look like a man who honors contracts?
Dialogue.05288CA0419B61C7B3A945B83E4CF4DA_9D00593: Look at me! Why in the world did you think I needed clarity?!
Dialogue.01D573A842C222A34B171A92CFDB78C7_21C1927: Look at me. Who wants to tea party with a murder doll?
Dialogue.E9B6219F4E5EB2D259C58A980AB30109_FB122F8: Look at the author of this file.
Dialogue.ED6986054234BE25EF29549BFD057C2B_7D086D9: Look at the land from the perspective of a billionaire.
Dialogue.ACB31D3C4123257060CA659A873E4CC2_724DAF1: Look at the staff photos. How much corduroy do you see?
Dialogue.DB1FDAF445E1722E25D83E8F90183FD4_9801E98: Look at this! There's a glyph.
Dialogue.8D43BC9C4704F117769BB28A7347435E_06FC410: Look at you getting involved in the community!
Dialogue.74FAE98347396615550E608AD1B5BC73_06FC410: Look at you, master bed finder!
Dialogue.F452BA9348E05FF7E4603BB3AD08CFDE_87F0BBB: Look closer. Someone wrote "Cheater" all over it!
Dialogue.CAC16CE742B0EAAA04F461B29D9CC9BE_06FC410: Look for any lenses or telescope parts.
Dialogue.4C33DC044D7D1F4F4B34EFA2BECE247D_06FC410: Look for anything you can agree on. Anything at all.
Dialogue.FF01ED59483C1B7687C5E4A2D194FB84_06FC410: Look for more beds to add to the mega bed!
Dialogue.823C88874052FF96A391DEA6C771E3C0_06FC410: Look for more. He will be the king of cans!
Dialogue.6D4F8FE74AE46B65E82ED8A711E08493_06FC410: Look for some more troll holes.
Dialogue.E6614A2B4EE7E11451EE5193503EEC64_94F2B66: Look out! Those creeps spawn more monsters when you destroy â€˜em! Nah, I donâ€™t understand the science either.
Dialogue.7D0D17FE4299EB5DF94B598C42504260_06FC410: Look sharp, Commander. Vlad is a known lunatic, suspected vampire, and history's eighth greatest monster!
Dialogue.95F0449B47E329744E98FC854F7DEA61_910A467: Look! Over there! It's something else!
Dialogue.0C3300F9461EEE685D251E9DB1249460_06FC410: Look, I get what you're trying to do.
Dialogue.036738C24A7894951995DAAB32DCE5A2_FB122F8: Look, I screwed up. But I'm working to fix it.
Dialogue.613AD5A047E1CE6768CDD2AA6179B49D_06FC410: Look, I'm not stopping until we find your friend, and I don't care if that makes you mad.
Dialogue.9815FD8943700C54A08CFAAE097B1F04_87F0BBB: Look, Lars! Someone was done so dirty they tore up all their memories!
Dialogue.35336E9E42399858CA803DAA18C1345A_CC240C1: Look, Penny! The next item from your list.
Dialogue.9D6983E94BCF87207FB59891E8B0DED0_FB122F8: Look, Steel Wool had our time in the spotlight. We faded. It's over. Can we just leave it alone?
Dialogue.038A1D48451EC04B0419818C94819D69_7D2960E: Look, dude. I'm not one for games.
Dialogue.20B79A9949FF38F2992E8CA56207B21C_7D2960E: Look, dude. That's two "really"s more than I want to hear from my maker.
Dialogue.B308543846330C4DACDDFA8A419D5853_B222EAD: Look, if I find some sort of proof, can you convince your friends to leave?
Dialogue.5883272C4A2C5B3B92B4B1BAFE32497D_9801E98: Look, man. You can always get time off for good behavior.
Dialogue.95CB6E1A45E9CCF42DECC9B9DE6877C3_06FC410: Look, this one has clouds in it.
Dialogue.C5FD11C9452EF68164DAFD9C50DDEC2E_7D086D9: Look. I don't expect you to understand... but after I left he programmed you to replace me.
Dialogue.DA41D54246683282C52B0CA44AADAC37_06FC410: Look. Lars is coming for you now -
Dialogue.0E01975E4787D0956E007DBB5801CB6A_FB122F8: Looking at the night sky really makes you realize how small and insignificant you are.
Dialogue.1D8FD29E4728B9A6A433709F4CCCE6E8_06FC410: Looks like he recognized it's you...
Dialogue.B6391EA3437D84144C97588AB394F746_7D086D9: Looks like it, but it doesn't quite make sense.
Dialogue.7F631AB640D3263A00F5B2A1D5484F66_FB122F8: Looks like there's a full on Category 5 Love Storm brewing down there!
Dialogue.8C1366BF41300161AA7892930717BD5B_A96EA86: Looks like they're rolling out the 2018 husk lineup.
Dialogue.7ABE018B416830B3B1D5BAB4156045A4_06FC410: Looks like they've all been looted now.
Dialogue.9411D3BB4E7F0A6CDEA8B693A90CC095_06FC410: Looks like we're getting' back in the grave robbin' game!
Dialogue.7F386DF249198BED89563B9B94F54D88_06FC410: Looks like we're in, uh, uncharted territory here.
Dialogue.9EC6A93A446AC577BF08D6B4BC4E0F44_06FC410: Losing control like that... I need to know what I'm doing.
Dialogue.564821FC470283391B8D92A7A7EED7EB_06FC410: Love has made a mess of our lives!
Dialogue.F8541FEE4BC4AAF0AAF3AE840C540294_97A9259: Love has ravages? Why wasn't I warned!?
Dialogue.36588C7945A49E497982B3B9C2CB1366_0A979DB: Love is an illusion crafted by the media...
Dialogue.C3A5FDFF49C3366DF8016888373DB687_14FBFB1: Love made me the man I am today.
Dialogue.01A6A3B949E9FB90D9AA0CB6C2C9DC42_06FC410: Love makes fools of us all.
Dialogue.D043A203488FE2B98349D2A9CE246888_94F2B66: Love's a lie and we die alone.
Dialogue.86776F04471C529513E4C7B251288720_97A9259: Love's vision is based on movement.
Dialogue.26DDB85A446C74B662571E9A0B914203_06FC410: Luckily all the beds so far have been the same size.
Dialogue.928FE96C42709965F14673861789F088_EAAE146: Luckily weâ€™re back on the open sea again, raiding the husks and pillaging the storm!
Dialogue.7BED52A045CE8A033E49EF99BF7C0499_87F0BBB: Luna loves you, that's for sure.
Dialogue.B737701446F2E4CAC6A05C9855165907_8DEFB9E: Lunch is here. Everyone is walking away from the table. I will put lunch on the table. There is lunch. Lunch is sandwiches.
Dialogue.D79AEB1F4272800C2E226BA30E955C91_87F0BBB: Major, their society was more into farming, storytelling... that sort of thing.
Dialogue.35F6381A4B47435C39F1D7988115828E_9D00593: Make my memories warm and bright, Lars.
Dialogue.8B53BF88447F395663BA9EA2811D42F8_FB122F8: Make sure Syd listens to it.
Dialogue.5842F9F443E5324D44FCEDAEF5490A27_861A10F: Make the eyes a little beadier...
Dialogue.3CB8B9FE4386EC1C0F93689D11138F3A_94F2B66: Make those spirits bright... or die trying.
Dialogue.0DE63DAE4F7141811381978F0D74FD53_97A9259: Makes real life feel like a bunch of films you just saw.
Dialogue.6542D43547F33509C33F7784A93400BD_06FC410: Making progress. No audio logs, but I did find some early schematic plans.
Dialogue.AC426C694B6696121C04959E3F665240_861A10F: Making these construction supports is really lifting my spirits!
Dialogue.76A83FE042D31F5F8AE12DB5A706DC7F_FB122F8: Man. Hard to believe this is it. No more Steel Wool. We won't even get the chance to embarrass ourselves with a reunion tour no one asked for.
Dialogue.DDC18BD34A132844C4C293A0088ECA89_06FC410: Many of whom he himself killed.
Dialogue.5F333F654ED7E4A87E32DEA6CA0C53DB_06FC410: Many of you feel that I am hiding things from you, and... I am.
Dialogue.2BE42FAB4340323CA50433BA4CBEEB90_06FC410: Mass Extinction? Oh yeah. I get it.
Dialogue.AE9B8BAE42CECF985A5288AAAF163848_9801E98: Mass extinction's basically all I think about.
Dialogue.A07EC5344478FE99CA8ED6BE5FB16921_C9708CA: Mass layoffs, stores shuttered, no one from the company speaks a word. Remember that? It was weird, right?
Dialogue.1D7550954BA5924584D3A6A03C21EB29_97A9259: May or may not be equipped with a rich, sonorous voice.
Dialogue.CF0D28614CABAD367693C18FE29C620B_06FC410: May the wind rise up to fill your sails, Blakebeard and Keelhaul.
Dialogue.49C5B71141EABBE73FE5D5857AE251D4_7D2960E: Maybe I missed out on learning some things.
Dialogue.4FA8E9CD42E38C4DBE1082B8ED46B0A6_89ED452: Maybe I should take some time for introspection. Really figure out what I want out of this world.
Dialogue.BD8110404456F70F757A7889C7AF7968_9801E98: Maybe Lars isn't the problem. Maybe we didn't release Mad Science because we couldn't.
Dialogue.E2306EAD43C1B9EC43B340B78EE7A91A_06FC410: Maybe add a little pitch correct while you're at it?
Dialogue.6A52ADD64488450B60F5ABBCAB4929D9_97A9259: Maybe for the average team of adventurers...
Dialogue.9400867F4BDE3A25B7EDC8AF9C2BE9D8_97A9259: Maybe give me the PG version.
Dialogue.805FB6AE4060ADAABDAA62B0FEE832FA_97A9259: Maybe have some respect for your audience and dig a little deeper?
Dialogue.9DD96F0D42021199F124CF929602CB34_06FC410: Maybe he's making some kind of Husk repellant.
Dialogue.C4493A1B4ED60D0A28072E8F62A84324_B222EAD: Maybe instead of daring, you could summon me?
Dialogue.626A948042BEAC9D7DECD3806CF490F3_EC1949E: Maybe it's time for a little self-care.
Dialogue.F930B074426511C84591C58FA0141496_06FC410: Maybe just open with a joke?
Dialogue.2EFD655C482758D12DCD3D85A9F16958_EC1949E: Maybe one of those hats that go up on one side? Or maybe some really nice boots, ankle high!
Dialogue.1068639046E87B713DB869872888192C_861A10F: Maybe one of you should have a go.
Dialogue.10E479874A7C3575FA180FA88D3B6697_97A9259: Maybe she saw something in him we don't.
Dialogue.066FC985440DEE0586CDAD9E2F7CC3A1_FB122F8: Maybe she was trying to make her own Homebase.
Dialogue.2D6BD67B4F9E2B40E20188959485F163_06FC410: Maybe she was... catching up on everything she missed?
Dialogue.8819D6F84A409246525D028CACD7190E_06FC410: Maybe some vampires should learn to be nicer!
Dialogue.1A44CCFD4CE5BE5C77145BA722B48900_97A9259: Maybe that's why they call those things "wolfsbane."
Dialogue.4D2A5C724956E1F4D226EC9CA1058EB8_9801E98: Maybe that's why we're all stuck in this terrible reality. Maybe this is the loser reality.
Dialogue.62EBAB814D313CF63D4EB9B4AF6277C1_06FC410: Maybe there was an ancient tribe that gave offerings of fruit and nuts to a benevolent robot overlord!
Dialogue.C917443B43068A9DA77BB79404FF7BC1_06FC410: Maybe there's something about it in the Homebase manual.
Dialogue.419074CD400DF849063C00B2EDC4C7C0_861A10F: Maybe we can convince them that Arrlene and Rarrnold aren't monsters!
Dialogue.D2E110044DEC7C8C6995EC8AB6BD0652_06FC410: Maybe we can just take a teensy peek in a grave or two.
Dialogue.DDC116A047970F6A17CE1BB69A0597FA_47CFF90: Maybe we can see this not as a failure, but as a chance to do better.
Dialogue.58BAA246493A2006A5A323A004D4241B_A96EA86: Maybe we should collect some shards for analysis.
Dialogue.B58A1C3C4F3F652AC1413FA35A414D97_06FC410: Maybe we should stick to happy stories, about bunnies or marshmallows, or marshmallow bunnies.
Dialogue.C1231D944357C21CDB857C80B80C3984_06FC410: Maybe when we return there'll be statues of you everywhere.
Dialogue.954CCD43430642A962C358AB8F71CF8F_06FC410: Maybe with Dennis' movie, we'll be able to help people. Movies teach all sorts of good lessons.
Dialogue.F17C93E144F3FDF0FBA5119FF64A52EE_06FC410: Maybe you could explain it to us.
Dialogue.FFFDC0074CD04FDBC7F0DFB5EFFD6FFD_4731F06: Maybe you just call me "Dennis Jr."
Dialogue.6D98765646A624B9FC342B97B93C658F_FB122F8: Maybe you should just admit you don't always understand everything? Okay?
Dialogue.0B164C444A16F90CFBE8849A7A148150_FB122F8: Maybe you should stop while you're ahead.
Dialogue.630CA6E046AC1999192CD584BA3E0666_CC240C1: Maybe you should try transposing it to the key of C.
Dialogue.2303F29C43E318DB16B708BEDF155B41_06FC410: Maybe. Or maybe we're breaking new creative ground.
Dialogue.3D707BE649683477D224CFBCF7ECB1DB_7D086D9: Maybe. Or, maybe I'll surprise you.
Dialogue.0EEE27D444581D5D665DDE9AD8E6A74D_9801E98: Me and Lars were talking, and we're not on board with drum machines.
Dialogue.218DEBF64CA1573FA608B78965C3F89E_72190CE: Me too! At least... I assume thatâ€™s what that taste is.
Dialogue.6B0B1FD14BA0C180D275A09CA7F29E7E_EAAE146: Me. I had a great time stealing it.
Dialogue.E26534DB42926406B33BD598E9526A79_97A9259: Me? I'd be a casual vampire.
Dialogue.AED63D984749D9C8D2C57BB627436D84_97A9259: Meanwhile, Dennis Jr. is over here bending the spacetime continuum! I can't compare to that.
Dialogue.DCFF3DD948B55A819F872FA0A6EAAF0E_EAAE146: Mhm. Honestly I should smack you in the face.
Dialogue.3FA3042E4E3EFDBB5084EC9CABF05F86_06FC410: Minor warning, the crew is potentially different from what you're used to.
Dialogue.C765763A4446EE9E6322BFA557D926DE_97A9259: Mixed correctly, this will call upon the vampires.
Dialogue.0AD927CC4C06C800C5D63A8AFF3A7B80_47CFF90: Mm, perhaps just start with the ornaments.
Dialogue.2D1CA3E24F602DD29D03E0908FB7A03C_CC240C1: Module Report Command 10. Multiple interactions with Dennis
Dialogue.DB4DA4FD4A16B45159E10895CFD7FC5A_CC240C1: Module Report Command 20. Exterior indicators online.
Dialogue.7A9705134042948789A30095077FDCC4_CC240C1: Module Report Command 30. Core temperature low.
Dialogue.7612FCFA424425D8DB34278994153A70_CC240C1: Module Report Command 50. Unknown object appearing nearby.
Dialogue.E00D507A48167179858295AEF8BC290D_CC240C1: Module Report Command Purple Carrot Playground.
Dialogue.4FDDE91140601D1965DD2FB09A2E2963_4731F06: Mom can't come. She's needed in Twine Peaks.
Dialogue.BF5BBB4F4CCBF479CE77FF874C9E6D10_06FC410: More candy! Oh, I already feel the sugar rush.
Dialogue.C722AD114464BA25B7BB95AF49BB31D3_47CFF90: More like when youâ€™re boarding a ship whose crew has a reputation for being very full of blood and organs.
Dialogue.86C4D3554334A8F62791A59E49D707F7_861A10F: More of an avoidance of a terrible Christmas crime.
Dialogue.AC6099BB4C74271E111FCFA108D49BDD_06FC410: More parts for Clip's super weapon!
Dialogue.0BF5A91D4C7D395D663A9F9B8ED1B2E1_CC240C1: More than I have ever wanted anything in my entire life!
Dialogue.C08092D149ADD4CAE6D1BA9336C393D0_9F725B6: More than half of the songs I write are pure trash.
Dialogue.D8A7C02F4B507898E1C353802E6965C9_47CFF90: Most excellent! You hear that, you salt-covered scamps? We found you your treasure!
Dialogue.57392C32450DDF1228853885CBE8A76A_06FC410: Most monsters have some sort of weakness.
Dialogue.10676EBD4C483689D079E9A4ED506850_89ED452: Most people I knew before the storm thought I was some sort of psychopath.
Dialogue.2AACF64D49FDEE33D4CE5EBB09586E24_AFB40E2: Most relationships are doomed to failure within the first six months.
Dialogue.8149D63048336ED31E4A988989DD8A9A_06FC410: Mothmen hate light bulbs. Lankyman hates carbs.
Dialogue.99984F4442A853E77503D2A061F14CFD_861A10F: Movies, concerts... maybe a romantic picnic in the park...
Dialogue.91176BC545437F200C2F349648BBFD2D_06FC410: Mr. Moribund's Elixir of Everlasting Li...
Dialogue.7219C59341D0C3B777B8708386119E0E_06FC410: Mt Copper has been on fire for a year, so, you know that's somethin' for ya.
Dialogue.4282885040D78045FFB821A18D336BA0_47CFF90: Much better. And very, very quickly. I cannot overstate how much we need treasure.
Dialogue.3ADC2D7E46089BE184D97493A553697B_FB122F8: Mulberry... eggplant... sangria.. amethyst... porple. You know about porple? Its pretty cool.
Dialogue.1D4896304E8225BAB1AB8D9FA15CF7CC_06FC410: Mummies hate fire. Classic vampires hate heart stakes.
Dialogue.6564E20F4F6CB26DF27E099C899987E4_7D2960E: Must've made a name for myself or somethin', because one day some guy with an agency badge shows up...
Dialogue.B20033B741934A96BACA458C98CB826C_97A9259: My EARS can hear my HEART and my BRAIN is SCARED.
Dialogue.43D234CD43F38BA9EDB97B80E52F197D_97A9259: My buddy, Ray, thinks you're gonna be great and that's enough for me.
Dialogue.DF832B084F42B2199E3D25A8132DE182_CC240C1: My circuits are still quinoa'd up...
Dialogue.9D7C1D0248971DD75D8256BC0404118E_72190CE: My contractual obligation has been fulfilled. Bye forever.
Dialogue.E7DDAE36460EE222ABA70FBF99D9F580_B229E47: My core started to melt down two hours ago.
Dialogue.AA534ABA4C2DEC3B35F86EB3280841B7_97A9259: My dad and me didn't really get along...
Dialogue.8D4AD03248C1EE0FCB1153AAA3A70A8E_181CD3E: My early stuff just caught fire. It was everywhere.
Dialogue.0EEC1F6A4647C40A3A136C85D2407EA3_861A10F: My equipment is all set up and almost ready to go. First, grab that lightning rod!
Dialogue.EB8520C84426346C1053378CF88C7CF5_72190CE: My father dedicated his life to that treasure. Whatever it is, it'll be worth it. Trust me.
Dialogue.698A4EF548854A44873EC69CF965BB82_72190CE: My father was Blake Jennings Sr.
Dialogue.7D833A36458BF2DF4FDDB8A9464C701D_7D2960E: My friend Jilly could use your help...
Dialogue.7C32B4E745124153183F988F03AC38D7_94F2B66: My god, do I love a good paper trail.
Dialogue.CB218CFC4E724C54DF09BDB0D7C280C0_06FC410: My heart is heavy with anguish to think that I may not, in fact, reach our home.
Dialogue.0782EF9047D435E45A1000B05B7FC00F_06FC410: My heart used to work! But now... just nothin'.
Dialogue.291D418440FB9543083367B718595B04_06FC410: My love, my dear and gentle Sophie,
Dialogue.C0999B114796D1B4FD796FA5FBF73AD4_FB122F8: My man Syd was into dirt stuff, and Anthony was a Chemist...
Dialogue.65436DE049CDE50DD62598AF161B6974_14FBFB1: My memories are all I have left. I refuse to let anyone else into my heart.
Dialogue.BA512EF94A8AE270A6C23290D53DB235_9D00593: My mission as a one-man Homebase Holiday Committee is to spread Holiday cheer.
Dialogue.92609BC24AFF841F5507A3BE8D6247B3_724DAF1: My name is Anthony, but you probably know me as Lil' Anthony Dynamite.
Dialogue.131BD72F4C66DE310E6EC3A628E65A94_06FC410: My nameâ€™s Ray! I run Homebase, the premiere human settlement around these parts! We'd love to rescue you!
Dialogue.49435A60439501C89599BD98E2326305_14FBFB1: My next warning will not be so kind.
Dialogue.790A0A1448AE7D79C1D0E694511565E0_97A9259: My parents knew, but they took the risk anyway!
Dialogue.C4008E6945C2DD9849EA88954E49DF93_06FC410: My passive aggressive approach got me nowhere.
Dialogue.B30A02FE4AF4BAC4604EC2A28A74D1B0_97A9259: My research is coming along nicely.
Dialogue.9992DBC04967745FB933FEBAEF002FB4_FB122F8: My results came back.. kinda funky. Not a good bass-y funk, either.
Dialogue.9189540742D2E63406D0A1AE2FE998DD_FB122F8: My system works for me, and I am not changing it.
Dialogue.A1C9F361487E3927B4CE569975DA2B4A_FB122F8: My touring days are far behind me, so let's just say scientist.
Dialogue.176D68F7474C291E031D75B797FC1CFF_97A9259: Myself! In front of the screen! Putting a movie on!
Dialogue.254632044D4A2A78F488DE85E4BC9D95_97A9259: Myself. In front of the screen. Putting a movie on... And on the screen I see...
Dialogue.75519C8747A1DE5DA689729D77A47219_06FC410: N- no more! Ma- magnet, no more!
Dialogue.F1C3BEF946D1970721B9C281AB74E35E_FDAEB92: NO ONE WILL EVER LOVE YOU.
Dialogue.C434C0704860239300ACD0B40C1B3286_FB122F8: Nah, back then it was all about the music, and the science.
Dialogue.201FF74D4FA5D998CE41DC924A4BBCA3_9801E98: Nah, oh, but he is down with the Steel Wool reunion...
Dialogue.AD717DA644B373DE8D57BFB17E8183DF_9F725B6: Nah. You're too in your own head.

Dialogue.9524014A4B895FFF7EF7FCB17EFD1CBB_97A9259: No Dennis, no Dennis, no Dennis, no Dennis... YES!
Dialogue.0DB45789438135A48B16FEB743F5670D_9D00593: No branch goes un-glittered. Not on my watch.
Dialogue.B94AAF334642D1C0A64F2F9E8D0B6D39_94F2B66: No building zone is active! That means no building! Oh and you can't use your pickaxe. Good luck.
Dialogue.E054E93A434F4AF3EC26F0AB66FFC0C5_9D00593: No can do, boss. I swore a holly, jolly blood oath.
Dialogue.C86EB78A45C38174879BA18A6E0DFEED_7D086D9: No guarantee they'd end up together. In fact it's extremely unlikely.
Dialogue.73F8B1B64A16A45251791DBA4C8B10C4_EAAE146: No idea. But once we're done with this, we really gotta get you to a doctor.

Dialogue.13E5EBE346936CF1EAC3F29EA71A951E_724DAF1: No matter how grim all this garbage fire nonsense gets, thatâ€™s your superpower, man.

Dialogue.3FE8D419401CAF072928A89950B9ACBD_97A9259: No matter how hard you try to hide from love, it will find you in the end.
Dialogue.57EB2CA94E70978D7956858055CE9825_06FC410: No more TV for the kid.
Dialogue.689895EE4AEBB6BD3B3F9587338B03AE_97A9259: No more TV for the kid?
Dialogue.B34653FB41D1D0BD7B2CE5AAC4C9A831_06FC410: No more burgers until we get our stuff back.
Dialogue.5982B53740008CF7FE6BF1A00D33A601_06FC410: No name. No return address. Then I'm circling "No." Heh.
Dialogue.BDC264AD4A0518B793D549AAC1F626FA_7D2960E: No need to think, just punch.
Dialogue.2AB3D81A498D9679A3C357872483D41A_06FC410: No no no no no no no!
Dialogue.85E75F0843BBC131064D52A1D9C43EF6_06FC410: No no no. Something's not right here.
Dialogue.B00445C641697AEDABC89BA46786DEF4_97A9259: No offense, but that is the least cool time travel method I have ever heard of.
Dialogue.64C009584F6E7FFA1AF740A33745652D_CC240C1: No one answered our want ads!
Dialogue.A87589C7443265698AAA83B5734C5AD0_9D00593: No one cares that Crackshot's head doesn't have enough air holes. (gasp)
Dialogue.F41082BA483E41688BE9ABA58F55A035_06FC410: No one did. But it only ran for a day.
Dialogue.42A1B33A40AD2AED0FDFDAAB4EBF91FC_06FC410: No one does. No one ever does.
Dialogue.73C0D91D4BACE6437C72D7A6E777CD9C_89ED452: No one ever said "Oh you make guns? Let's be friends."
Dialogue.F80E6F2C442308FFFE3C3EA6B7568417_B222EAD: No one has ever gotten this close!
Dialogue.AE429DB34473985EEF95DA9709821757_910A467: No one is truly bad. You just need to see things from their perspective.

Dialogue.F204A3194DDDE16C10F273909B4CB351_181CD3E: No one would want to play with a toy based on how I'm feeling now.
Dialogue.4E77FCD74B2C11D6FB7FDA960461E48A_97A9259: No one's too happy about losing to you.

Dialogue.5110DD7845328C062E15D3A85F478197_06FC410: No pillaging. No looting. No reigns of terror.

Dialogue.C0FBF3854A73086886F1AC954A6BBEF2_CC240C1: No! He was an original monster!
Dialogue.820F933D42AD1B059F517C9D78FB40CD_861A10F: No! I was embarrassed I hadn't invited you to our wedding yet!
Dialogue.529163EB4DA4DA07F024CFB6546AB71C_97A9259: No! Never well done. Always medium rare.
Dialogue.19B48B4C40A7D98401E2AE9CA2571AC7_176484F: No! When he's old enough to understand language and has object permanence and stuff!
Dialogue.731425C843FB79A14A61108DC84343A6_06FC410: No, Business Wolf! That's a bad Business Wolf!
Dialogue.D07F3CFF44FE1AB1B2F235B49072911C_EED9CD8: No, I really need a gift that says "I'm sorry I sold your brush and bought you all that hair."
Dialogue.C2CFB3744C4834922B44FC9520291936_9801E98: No, I'm embarrassed my solo album tanked, I'm bitter you destroyed the band!
Dialogue.34C18C91488D7E77FAD147A0AEFB0DAF_861A10F: No, Lok, I'm creating a person. You know, stitching her together and then waking 'er up.

Dialogue.807B30994EDBBF5362FCFA88F5DF4CEF_FB122F8: No, it's not. We're better than that.

Dialogue.C8A005354DFC9D483F9EF7B2C4ACED40_47CFF90: No, no, no, no, no! No one do that!

Dialogue.591DEA1C4596A0383ADC77BEE2F2FEAB_B229E47: No, no, no. If we don't solve this problem, they'll be too preoccupied with dying to even know what went wrong.
Dialogue.02F9B6D74F3E892AA841338B14082645_97A9259: No, no. I think that was an N.

Dialogue.891354F7410D2E08CD5749987C0F1744_06FC410: No. Dennis! Stay where you are!

Dialogue.87604A8B45C9DD8E09E0408E6C6F6490_06FC410: No. I use positivity because without it, I'd never be able to force myself out of bed to face the horrors of our world.
Dialogue.99397F994BA52F37B0D2959FA294154F_7D2960E: No. I was not aware of this.

Dialogue.F292E4104EFCC6820807AD86C27196A3_06FC410: No. I'm sorry I gave up.

Dialogue.AFEF107842B136C50500EE83D2A2F1A5_FB122F8: No. You need to find Anthony.

Dialogue.4F33B5E84F729A8E1A0327BAFA8468EA_06FC410: None of the missing items are in homebase. We'll have to search the zone.

Dialogue.2FAE91494F7FE467DAA35EAB7F8A7192_97A9259: None taken. I do have hair and thumbs.

Dialogue.FA767BA3480CCCBB32908D8D049912F0_7D2960E: Nope. I've had enough of toilet paper talk and enough of your front mullet to last a lifetime.
Dialogue.FEDEE37A432B545A26ADE6BD3E615D96_A96EA86: Normally I'd take care of this myself. But I've just not been feeling like myself lately.

Dialogue.6640339D4A45BEE0E947989B5E0D1F21_FB122F8: Not good. I honestly have no idea what I'm doing.
Dialogue.AA19A33844F22503908F38A3115B2CD3_06FC410: Not great. But it's a start.
Dialogue.8A680F5249175D337184A38627B46E8F_94F2B66: Not in front of the troops.

Dialogue.38AD710B4E2ECC163FD4398FB3359CB4_861A10F: Not really. Everything back home is lush and green, filled with animals and gentle breezes.
Dialogue.F375D1AC4E49E502FBF06887C9C01AC1_06FC410: Not so regal now, are ya!

Dialogue.C2AF16E84D6704C0361FD59EAB094896_7D086D9: Not that I don't appreciate your effort. But we can use the honor system, here.
Dialogue.A2448BB64246EEE521AB1BABFAE2A564_176484F: Not the answer I was hoping for.

Dialogue.D8F3B5354F568CC3DF9C978E7D7DC9F1_47CFF90: Not the reaction I was hoping for. I thought clarity might bring you some sort of peace.
Dialogue.C99541A74B87D8441F2830A232352968_AB3C42C: Not to backseat direct, but you might want to find some cameras.
Dialogue.F58237CB48E59909E6EFC385D5FFFA08_06FC410: Not to give you advice, but nothing you've stolen here is valuable.
Dialogue.3C61BB0247AC16457B87CEBA696A5FA8_06FC410: Not to pressure you, but we really need to find SEE-Bot.
Dialogue.CE32B68A4EE12426C28AEFADC722752E_FB122F8: Not until the run is complete.
Dialogue.B4DE7C634725F91636BC64B45F06393A_47CFF90: Not... precisely how I was going to put it, but I suppose that logic scans.
Dialogue.13D0A5B84E0CF52F092B00A716632514_06FC410: Nothing about Storm Monsters loosely based on historical monsters.
Dialogue.7E78102A44B828A1BF6C1EB541B8E70B_4731F06: Nothing brings them together and they can never combine their skills, so...

Dialogue.72DB44A64580AD8568BAAF88B7387607_EECA944: Nothing like someone being chased by a husk. Ready, aim, and...

Dialogue.ACDE9AA647B804EFE49091915DFA25CB_FB122F8: Nothing unusual, Little Robot. I will always love my music and helping the world through science.
Dialogue.65EE1517445CCF891337B989278E4D03_D87E161: Nothing will make me feel better ever again.

Dialogue.29F6B64449079E551AFA74947E0969B6_97A9259: Now c'mon. It's time to roll out.

Dialogue.516EAF584B6132086604ABAC66A6737F_06FC410: Now it's time to pick up the pieces.

Dialogue.B46185FB4C63295DA433A3A5FADA185F_84C369E: Now that we're clear-headed, I know for sure she likes me!
Dialogue.5EBC4DC34EA1730B2031BCA5F59E3646_47CFF90: Now that we've all cooled down and agreed that no one is killing anyone...

Dialogue.81D6E4A54C497DCDC4189B8D6EC15674_97A9259: The trick with kids is you gotta realize they are crazy bonkers out of their minds all day long.
Dialogue.B541E7254BC408E7D21881A9CB6E076C_06FC410: The tumbleweeds do seem to be moving in the same direction.
Dialogue.7C69E0A64BA7DC74BD870596442DF252_B222EAD: The very old, the very young, the intellectually... eh... how should I put it?

Dialogue.8E08CB8D44EC7AD10CD6DFB4B6E155DD_861A10F: The wedding is over. Let's bask in happiness for just a moment, shall we?
Dialogue.CE3E32B448152799EAFB4B91FFACE8E7_47CFF90: The werewolves will be forced to move on.

Dialogue.DE7177104BE7E0DE4E8F0B82201A4ECE_94F2B66: The, uh, top brass has clarified our mission.

Dialogue.4CAFE89042E442F1B36D02A2D5977F69_7712BEE: Their parents sent them to spend the summer in the spooky woods.
Dialogue.4081A9EB44881CF7EBEC84ADCAE78306_B229E47: Then Desiree is right. This is a dangerous and irresponsible use of technology...

Dialogue.4D4485C842D91D47A92570A0C6D68A55_910A467: Then again, who am I to question my own programming?
Dialogue.F4BB0C6B4CFA46620340CDA43FD4D1F8_97A9259: Then become jittery, paranoid, and unable to control the volume of my voice.
Dialogue.E754B2764ECF5D3FA537828D9DA1E749_EAAE146: Then don't tell me how to pirate!
Dialogue.21F5D69A4ABE77C3A6F406BB3E81B657_7D2960E: Then give me back those points.
Dialogue.CBB9E8AB4D8AA236FCBEAAA8AA9C3C86_06FC410: Then half of Homebase would be homeless!
Dialogue.AE9C04C84A5CAA2BC3917E991C81ED52_97A9259: Then he can take a good long look at the monster he's become.
Dialogue.4C3475E74674D2E833AF8DBCFFD3F059_CC240C1: Then let me take your case.
Dialogue.913320914E82F1CC786C478206827C10_06FC410: Then maybe I can fix this.
Dialogue.868C5EFD4B1CCD7B4D613EB523E296FE_72190CE: Then maybe they can help us find the map to Rowdy Jack's treasure.
Dialogue.5905386948A26BD8A13DD28942EC71A6_97A9259: Then napkin up and prepare for round two!
Dialogue.D8E447794FD62CAAAB872F8F9BD78BBB_06FC410: Then suddenly he's in all places all the time, all of the times.
Dialogue.0CE63CCB43108385EB6D2AAB88E40235_B222EAD: Then the shadow beast in 270 gets jealous.
Dialogue.945B7AAF442051B34BC565BF3801E197_B222EAD: Then the vampires catch wind of the situation...
Dialogue.B75ABD97486AF6FE6F60E4B2FB66ABC8_9D00593: Then we all stand behind the family as they sit on old Kringle's lap... then...
Dialogue.D703C9AB4BD78CC41C76568E47425162_B229E47: Then we have everything we need to finalize the rift stabilization device.
Dialogue.07C9F15042C3B0158A6ADBBE72C445F7_0A979DB: Then we learned that love is meaningless.
Dialogue.96CC9AD14CFFCA6689D5E28D1111C68F_4731F06: Then we start giving up. Not all at once, just a little bit every day. By the time we notice... it's too late.
Dialogue.4DD8DB804AA3FEB46603EAA0F053C5C9_84C369E: Then what are we waiting for? Let's go!
Dialogue.DEBD8A5741E6994396610288911CC103_7D2960E: Then why are we out here?

Dialogue.082A28F84BC07D70F5579AAF154CA660_7D2960E: Then you are on your own.
Dialogue.3340A52E4D489E47D04AD495A9D64B33_47CFF90: Then, it hoists this flag, announcing its piratey intent!
Dialogue.18888A3444C04982E64BC6AE3CA2D708_06FC410: Then... there could be survivors down there!
Dialogue.047932044D4CE16D54B9D78FDFE3ED6F_72190CE: Therapist Brian was right! Our family is a toxic garbage barge!
Dialogue.18279D674F230BE30862F78AC150B761_06FC410: Therapy bot, a cloaked vigilante is smashing up husk hordes... and tombstones.
Dialogue.F491C5344052E9AB956A92B06E7FF698_CC240C1: There are a lot of bones out here. What is that noise? Vroooooo.
Dialogue.155F466B4745DBD1865EECA3DB40F6E4_B222EAD: There are a lot of restless souls in these rooms.
Dialogue.6CC5DA044B614B5AE74AE09C2B9859F2_06FC410: There are a lot of steps to this whole Vlad returns prophecy.
Dialogue.4CA3A98E478A4C830ADF10AF56807EC0_06FC410: There are more encrypted radio parts out there, let's find them.
Dialogue.A9092B3C4D3ACE7F699BE6946BA1AFC2_47CFF90: There are no fireplaces in Homebase.
Dialogue.3799B9B54DB8B4841DC50D9F295E2A6A_47CFF90: There are several Vindertech-approved methods for Beyond The Grave communication.
Dialogue.E2FC290C4B7D6361B1010AB235464CB9_06FC410: There are so many travellers through these parts, and they're always leaving stuff behind!
Dialogue.70FA14D94C7962DABACB68AA64E8BBB0_7D2960E: There are survivors this far out in the storm?

Dialogue.E41AB01640766D870C8D98860F1E6A6B_181CD3E: There has to be more to it than that.
Dialogue.F3DE85464B49E7CD9C4D26B331EBADD8_861A10F: There has to be some way to prove that Arrlene isn't all bad... Oh! Look over there. Someone's diary!
Dialogue.04C95EDA417A92CDA2891DA3319C1BD2_06FC410: There have gotta be more maps around here.

Dialogue.36E6B07B48AB03341A6F80BDBF54583D_06FC410: There is no excuse for slashing.
Dialogue.B6C09DBE4F6F0745208AF79D6CCC328F_06FC410: There is no number for that.
Dialogue.663BDFEB4B1CCCD713B29EA047C18700_8106785: There is no storm. There is no such thing as a husk horde.
Dialogue.4B8A56B9411A68A51FB91A9227F6EA26_06FC410: There is nothing that could get me to care about their feelings.
Dialogue.D1F270E1409C691EF2BD9392B9AD7223_EAAE146: There is, uh, just one problem...
Dialogue.DF58E49B40C22BAA96E6E69C10235AF8_FB122F8: There is... a lot of Vindertech research in these files.
Dialogue.E54891E74E2F93077EE06EAD27AFEAAD_181CD3E: There was a bug where she wasn't engaging in tea time consistently enough.
Dialogue.50982E404ACBA86C4E5C43AE4FB16CE0_B222EAD: There was a psychic writing convention...
Dialogue.49C0D77842783E4A39BE42B6FA760D5F_06FC410: There was some sort of Reality Hiccups thing.
Dialogue.717D10A940E16810204C6B81A74BCBB1_06FC410: There was... some drama in the fandom. And I chose to step down.

Dialogue.B266857C4EC5628DECF6E28A2CA7F772_06FC410: There will be a next year. There will be a next decade.
Dialogue.E00DDE104C5BBA8F042D108083D84B0C_06FC410: There will be a space fleet and I will get that husk!
Dialogue.CB5CFAA04FBF3CA05D46FF983F79B47F_06FC410: There will be no cracked skulls on my watch!
Dialogue.B5BC8B464B34BC8B6D2D1DA3B2FD1394_06FC410: There you go! First one down. How's that feel?
Dialogue.BA1018694FBC6842380796AFB64D5683_06FC410: There you go, my time-challenged friend.
Dialogue.31BA8C4B439F9097E5D8B5BCFBDE9AF6_06FC410: There you go. You're coming out of your wolf shell.
Dialogue.1BB11E1D4F2C4FAD48C1BDA887F2E94B_FB122F8: There'd be no one to tell us what happened.
Dialogue.F2D0A81D423D8CA99D374E910A85557F_C9708CA: There's a Vindertech lab here in Plankerton... and someone's working on... I don't know what it is, but it sounds BIG.
Dialogue.B9F8ADCC444EADAB6900759C8F013CE3_FB122F8: There's a breakthrough on the Love Storm, Little Robot!
Dialogue.B0579AB14AA1333D26CE518420181FF3_06FC410: There's a note! "Left to follow the trail. Don't touch the button."
Dialogue.66CCD1B846B723147E9CFAA5ABCB9554_06FC410: There's a page in the fireplace...
Dialogue.5CBCD0384DFF4E715C4443B2E88E802C_87F0BBB: There's a pile of bones over there!
Dialogue.F8B34BC041AA9D75C24C7EB71F1D2799_7712BEE: There's a sadness to this work. Self loathing...
Dialogue.D7DE55C04ECA17CEA9977AAA99DBB155_97A9259: There's a sandwich I made into the shape of a star because in his timesuit, he looks like an astronaut.
Dialogue.73FD1F5D462693BD4FB47D849BC6490A_7D2960E: There's always someone with a little bit of power who wants more.
Dialogue.33EDE02C464F44E1CB9D6F8F924086BA_47CFF90: There's been a little bit of pushback regarding the loads of candy you've been retrieving.
Dialogue.C4CD46C34C5E7185CF33CDB19853C77C_06FC410: There's been a pattern to what he's saying.
Dialogue.15CF096A418487AFB7468C957FC262CA_97A9259: There's more than just a monster movie going on here, I think...
Dialogue.2716787640E63BC0336AE2A71A3BE522_CC240C1: There's no detail! I don't even know this "Major" character's first name.
Dialogue.74B787A34A553669E459BE81FBE4E3A4_861A10F: There's no easy way to say this.
Dialogue.E671E4F84064D9AD82686387CD40C47E_06FC410: There's no such place as Plankenesia.
Dialogue.2B2582B5488079748C89D699156215EE_FB122F8: There's no way I'm not crashing!
Dialogue.EDDCCD9749A7C0DC89D88FB17A19A482_06FC410: There's nothing embarrassing about caring and trying hard.
Dialogue.45BB925145FB1774C91973BA717EA4A2_FB122F8: There's nothing safe about what we're doing.
Dialogue.DFE4F99048E7DDAC8E141DBE42BC85D8_06FC410: There's one of ED-EE's possible landing spots!
Dialogue.7A81A2B5428AD229B390BD97F552A136_97A9259: There's so much stuff I'll never get to do now!
Dialogue.0885E66A4B448479AE77309D108AAAA9_FB122F8: There's something he's not telling you. We're scientists, we don't "hunch"
Dialogue.09453A6E4A69A5D10DCF0C9D21A4B9CD_06FC410: There's somewhere you want to take us.
Dialogue.076E774444B90ABC83D38FA33B246085_06FC410: There's that one husk up there, we could see how he's doing.
Dialogue.A7A4D722499379BAAB770D8A6D59167B_06FC410: There's tons of good uses for cans.
Dialogue.3F3A5C11413BC093B58B078B0D7AD9EE_06FC410: There. The streets are clear of the most dangerous weapons out there...

Dialogue.6B75B57A4B56263732A0C3B817193E5A_94F2B66: These flying objects have been identified as threats! Watch your step.

Dialogue.AC953956490D53338454C897A8182162_EAAE146: These ones seem a little... boring.
Dialogue.7026DC5C4CC72E3374E7C0860E4D0F1B_9D00593: These ornaments are perfect! We just need more of them.

Dialogue.55F32F6E4F68B8FDE1A6DD9F1D6AAC00_CC240C1: They are unlike anything this world has ever seen.

Dialogue.147F6CAE4F9F37357C0A519627CB84F2_94F2B66: They did what they set out to do.
Dialogue.324826A446D403D7E57CDF9B05434DE8_97A9259: They don't believe him until they go out into the wilderness and boom! Monster!
Dialogue.2205BDDB4F21178ABADF949D0483B10A_21EB734: They don't caper around in tights.
Dialogue.1AEA1F0C4CFA85897BF7B599320A97C1_97A9259: They dress like they're royalty, with the capes and medals.
Dialogue.3127769041A24EB8060D6990EEA6DEAD_9801E98: They had every right to be with a name like that.
Dialogue.9BE8839E4D333B37460FF38B13937DC4_06FC410: They hate the idea that humanity will rise above petty squabbles and join forces in the selfless pursuit of adventure?

Dialogue.D19D86444026E3227C2B76A2B99074B7_47CFF90: They may be pirates, but they're still our responsibility.
Dialogue.7342D95A4BAC9176ABFB27A8632E8B7B_B222EAD: They may look cute, but they are evil.
Dialogue.BC8571414AABA1D24AD6ACB6853E74A2_87F0BBB: They must've had a BAD breakup to get rid of these mementos.
Dialogue.486F27E64323E4FE84D2E6AFC6EFB870_CC240C1: They said it was just a comet.
Dialogue.E1B1CBDA46134346F3B5918D3356C361_CC240C1: They said we had nothing to worry about.
Dialogue.53F86FDE406A82A229BEE5B061C4072D_06FC410: They said- "Onward, to the future! But first.. naps and maybe a light snack."
Dialogue.0BAF16DB400F490FB063C3BC855D2D10_06FC410: They say Vlad cannot be killed by the hand of man...
Dialogue.881EC2E34D0AED6C834250B0D4F1BD10_72190CE: They say true piracy means never having to say you're sorry, so I guess I'm not a true pirate yet...
Dialogue.77C9D03F4E9170E7C7019A9C3BDD8376_4731F06: They start to think maybe they won't win. Maybe they can't win. And, so..
Dialogue.F3D3673C4FFCFF72182784B07887BFB1_97A9259: They were created by a benevolent maker, and crafted with love.
Dialogue.2E01663445D910D7DDA6078F63A2F2DE_8106785: They will not rest until we give up. They will not rest until we give in. They will not rest until we are silenced!
Dialogue.471C0F09408F14C4A9E4FD8778FD12EE_21EB734: They're clogged up like a first act Homebase with hero applications.
Dialogue.A8994B03488F9E1ABA2B35BCE092CC5E_861A10F: They're cold and dead, but they lack that certain "I love setting fires" glint.
Dialogue.A7457A87409A00B95548109B4557F8BF_CC240C1: They're gone! I don't feel them!
Dialogue.67B796184BA70292B882FA81C853DB5A_97A9259: They're just so focused on keeping people out of their crypts and protecting their stuff.
Dialogue.F4772A7348D41E8BADD56FA749B4C342_861A10F: They're really good at heart, not monsters.

Dialogue.67B768ED499B3FF740FADD9F2A5E1B47_72190CE: Things were going well, at first. We used our best piratey lingo, waved our cutlasses around. Youâ€™d have been proud.
Dialogue.DD43092148E560B67F84CDA132250589_06FC410: Think about all the people out there still waiting to be found.
Dialogue.C42E2458441158C976B06E821EF24607_C9708CA: Think about that! See when I told you not to just give up and die I had a good reason! I wasn't being a jerk about it...
Dialogue.D06ED9624C3888C50CF4B2AF8923B947_06FC410: Think about the first long night before we found each other.
Dialogue.5153778F40499F1ED56FF78F30C7DBEE_06FC410: Think this might be the last one, you guys! Itâ€™s from Blakebeard!
Dialogue.BD975E0741A32F63F3DE97B5E2870EFB_7D086D9: Third priority is finding fuel for the rift stabilization device.
Dialogue.77D2519548CE977ADAA06DB362F728A6_06FC410: This article is the best. Here we go! Lars quote incoming.
Dialogue.F82508F84580652A24AD29BBF1352176_87F0BBB: This book is about archaeological fashion. Hmm.
Dialogue.859DE99F4BD7F5CD7ED974B81DD60C29_06FC410: This book may be perfect, then. "Absent Fathers, Abandoned Sons."
Dialogue.8B8587AD4B8B6F08145A53B77F1965D6_06FC410: This car still has a full tank of gas.

Dialogue.3601C11049A9970BCD97AC9B6EF08BC1_06FC410: This car was packed with materials for building.

Dialogue.4C53D4DD40DB36F61B6AB093F7249E63_06FC410: This catacomb was reserved for the Order of The Hex.

Dialogue.9BE3B56340276348A38D48974D618305_FB122F8: This delivery is for a group that doesn't want to come to Homebase.

Dialogue.38105F604514C734ECE20EADABBC412F_06FC410: This game is insane! Who invented it?

Dialogue.C6EE2574495A27342BA6A8891D026E8C_21C1927: This here's a setup. I know it!
Dialogue.4FBC4A24463CB12D34A5EB92A0A49E34_861A10F: This is Arrlene and Rarrnold's day. And if they want to spend it with filthy werebeasts, that's up to them.
Dialogue.01EE98DE40785A7D8C564FB29575DD25_97A9259: This is Dennis the Love King, that's me, reminding you to ignore problems for a while and it'll all be fine.

Dialogue.B4A1142C4A42EE4CDCD9A2ABE07BEC3F_72190CE: This is almost the last stockpile of things we stole from you and then buried.

Dialogue.AFD75A0A4DD0316F4BD732AC1FBD8BCE_7D086D9: This is intentional. Please leave me alone. Please.

Dialogue.9ABD1F2645402C786560F083F65A8C84_B25EA52: This is it. I'm ready to train my assistants.

Dialogue.261C47E94A1B7CF18ACA6593724495C5_06FC410: This is just a box of sticks.
