Dialogue.CA7F78314D24C391017385AF88975EF5_FB122F8: Uh. I couldn't help but notice you're up to something...
Dialogue.986791654E56F3B1B6625BAA4480FE26_0A979DB: Uh. Is that supposed to be an impression of me?
Dialogue.67106FE3411141C367D6DC85A352D4EF_06FC410: Uh... "The Gossamer Bodice: Romance Chronicles Number 32."
Dialogue.DB312B8C449E67C698BB9587E1130C62_97A9259: Uh... I have a question from a friend of mine...
Dialogue.F261C429481562C61A67A5B2950763F4_06FC410: Uh... I'm holding a copy of it right now.
Dialogue.947A66AA406812F92A4820A1DF36DC5D_06FC410: Uh... let's call it a day.
Dialogue.4BA7AC9143D407078097B49200A308A4_06FC410: Uh... look at all that land. I'm- I'm gonna... I'm gonna frack it.
Dialogue.DC6A2CCD4F7F0ECC39F87BB933EF1F66_94F2B66: Uh... suppose I never gave that much thought.
Dialogue.32677BF04F448A4F81A1CBB2B19ECB65_06FC410: Uh... this might be the last tape?
Dialogue.19768644400A4DA7B2C8E7B442254215_06FC410: Uh... we don't know he died while writing that... maybe he got distracted.
Dialogue.5C2F6A5042CA87E3F858B684A9043B8E_06FC410: Uh... we'll be taking a brief recess.
Dialogue.B514DF6F46FED5CD8B8A509C97CFFE77_06FC410: Uh... we'll fix it in post.
Dialogue.2B4139C948D0E94B894F13BD968258B5_06FC410: Uhh I guess that makes sense, in a Lars kind of way.
Dialogue.72B667B84A2CD64CA6A3B9B4FD584244_06FC410: Uhh, Power Chord? Hailing Power Chord? Come in, Power Chord?
Dialogue.DC40AD97421CC3178B37DDB6ED55B97D_47CFF90: Uhh, maybe just focus on spreading joy.
Dialogue.6F35EEE84CF82BCD8E1A4B8B386ED9B7_06FC410: Uhh, maybe we can debate all this after we defeat all of the ghostie ghoulies or husks or whatever-you-want-to-call-ems that I'm picking up right now?!
Dialogue.9C17537245F3C6C19CD616AA3689D641_FB122F8: Uhh... Calling that a cloud is a little generous.
Dialogue.6790731F43C9EF8AE2AC95B1EEE016CD_FB122F8: Um, Ray. The love lobbers are still down there lobbing love bombs.
Dialogue.62A23CAE496E64380F1DD1B3BAFCDCF9_97A9259: Um. Is it me, or are you starting to sound just like Ray?
Dialogue.B3485B0B4B4BD77555E277BE2FB8AC05_97A9259: Um. It's like... itâ€™s like the feeling when you're up in the middle of the night...
Dialogue.444F002042146B99D25F129E1AA57E4E_06FC410: Um. So I deleted his trip itinerary.
Dialogue.F2E4F70F489A5A9E15B5DDA291E08689_06FC410: Um... Maybe we need like a... soundtrack.
Dialogue.A19BFC0D40A3A30EEBAC279D64AA37FB_861A10F: Umm, I think I'll just "feel it" in the moment. But for now you could call it... ummm...
Dialogue.F4E17A62420ECFB8538490B5C0E312C3_06FC410: Ummm. You must be so excited to be actually living through a mass extinction!
Dialogue.E0B60E94489E9558A4C7009539B23A7D_CC240C1: Unable to sleep because every time I close my eyes I can still see the howling faces of tortured souls?
Dialogue.E914D56B4C7F842F6787F5835EF253D6_B222EAD: Unclean spirits are not even demons.
Dialogue.29110932413E81C9DC4230B345BFD26B_06FC410: Unfortunately there's no magic bullet for defeating Vlad.
Dialogue.C436592148C70224B4768A8C2FD0FC3B_06FC410: Unless Carlos ventured to the desert castle of Sir BunBun.
Dialogue.0A980788420F3D58770986A9DBE23FB0_9F725B6: Unless the storm hits us first.
Dialogue.DAB63FB34D19C15E855E878B41C6BD01_97A9259: Unless we're including non-food-based solutions, in which case... probably.
Dialogue.C6BBC26E4BDABBFC2BB5349603ED40C8_FB122F8: Unless you know something I don't... I'm afraid it's just me.
Dialogue.720677004A30A0ED00C787A560D9262C_94F2B66: Unless you want a major hotfoot, do not step on that lava, rookie!
Dialogue.C19DC484417CC69A29F59CAFB662A9CB_84C369E: Unless you're really into travel mugs. Heh.
Dialogue.45538C8245224B40C395D28E256D6A71_21EB734: Unless, of course, that has become the need of the community.
Dialogue.7499E8ED430B61AA655117B25EA60BB9_06FC410: Until that unspeakable horror materializes, happy Fortnitemares, everybody!
Dialogue.9FCB697C4136C27205B9ED9F8A4FF2F8_EECA944: Until the laser pointer comes out.
Dialogue.2803CA63439EB860175AA99A12362ACD_06FC410: Until then let's keep deploying the hover fleet.
Dialogue.BFC2C528441CB445DAB8D2BCE6797083_724DAF1: Until then, keep the beat going!
Dialogue.4DCFC6364B1A8357C6C01E808556C4FE_861A10F: Until they reach top speed and the bride's head flies off.
Dialogue.40350C304190F646B9A627B98B0F097D_06FC410: Until we come up with a better idea, this is our only idea.
Dialogue.9426C13D4BFA1AF0658A17AF6297AEF9_97A9259: Up next, we have Helpful in Homebase. What's your love Q, Helpful?
Dialogue.4CBAC49C408F7DB39042EF8C5491169F_CC240C1: Upgrade- upgrade- upgrade your fun at D-D-D-D-Durr Burger.
Dialogue.000823494F417CEDC56F2B8A24F68DDD_A96EA86: Use fire and ice weapons to take out the chrome husks!
Dialogue.48673FAD433EB71E91E9D9A341CE8141_06FC410: Use the special vacuum to get back our goods!
Dialogue.FBE4FB2D4442785BA0728C86AC53A963_AB3C42C: Usually colored paper is for changed, improved pages.
Dialogue.C28C5958479DC671AA88DC946E945C9C_FB122F8: Vacationers, long-haul truckers, criminals on the lam, grifters,
Dialogue.0DA582D94A0AF877D3454589FBB95FD9_06FC410: Very funny, oh my god he's right.
Dialogue.490ABCF847566583A76AE9BBADB750E6_D1275FF: Very well, I will keep my adventures vague.
Dialogue.753569F440558705ADC60AA3F21E8382_FB122F8: Vinderman wanted to encode our proofs and formulas into the music so it would be a living document...
Dialogue.9C50B46E458BD8032E3BCA85A00A6DFB_C9708CA: Vindertech didn't go out of business. They knew what was happening... and they were getting ready.
Dialogue.0AB9CF384BAD37EB520052AB0EFEB9A7_FB122F8: Vindertech wanted to partner with us to release an album based around our research.
Dialogue.24D8DC5F40AF4D72CD50DCA73D8A911A_9801E98: Vindertech was trying to work with us, and I don't think a lot of people knew that.
Dialogue.A16B4D8C49EAC15F6A2BC89E077438F7_06FC410: Vlad had one throne for every day of the Vladian week.
Dialogue.6219EDB444544CAD7FE4B09C0D91EE9E_06FC410: Vlad seems to have left the area.
Dialogue.C512CF6D41A9361D9BFDF090DFE5B976_06FC410: Vlad's hold over this land wanes!
Dialogue.3ED1731340EEEEB5A62C56A2AA6ADE09_06FC410: Vlad, your time has come. Again. Your second time has come.
Dialogue.CB98AC9E4F592145A09499A1479BA4CC_06FC410: Vladsday. Vladsday. Vladsday. Vladsday. Vladsday. Vladsday. Tuesday. Vladsday. Vladsday.
Dialogue.00741B4B46D1A2FCE7C6DFB56201D531_B222EAD: WATCH YOUR WORDS OR I WILL TAKE YOUR VOICE!
Dialogue.A3162DB34A7BE3CC7126938035E03316_FDAEB92: WE MUST STOP FOR FOURTH BREAKFAST. THIRD BREAKFAST WAS NOT ENOUGH BREAKFAST.
Dialogue.C6947CFB42A8701601DFBFAE6542BC4A_FDAEB92: WHAT IS CLEAVED CAN NEVER BE UNCLEAVED.
Dialogue.12D981C34732F1E40AD3929E755FD17D_B25AF7B: WHY DO YOU WANT TO BE A HOMEBASE HERO?
Dialogue.FEB4BDF742012F414365008BE06A6CB3_97A9259: Wai- No! Stay with it. There's a twist.
Dialogue.81C72D4D468DF92142F297A7D6474E24_97A9259: Wai- oh... Oh, no... The truth is settling on my shoulders.
Dialogue.BB0462104BE23A1DD1283EBB872C7B53_D87E161: Wait a second. How many did you launch?
Dialogue.ABA3B61340E8AC9EB118769418829140_06FC410: Wait! Here we go. This looks exactly like my Homebase junk drawer...
Dialogue.2A55B8094CD52A81BA88A79CFF2931CA_47CFF90: Wait! I think you've found the missing presents we've been looking for.
Dialogue.0B89CF8A46C9D98EA1039580D45C1610_06FC410: Wait! No! That's what we're going for!
Dialogue.BA8356C14E9EA21925C677B59F5C9CE1_06FC410: Wait! You were that last reasonable person left!
Dialogue.CC12BC3640C79D975471988C61BF0BB1_B222EAD: Wait, I didn't get my shriek right.
Dialogue.51DBB2044080880C8D33B597549A1856_06FC410: Wait, just checked my math and that is... not happening.
Dialogue.7A75A11E436B792DAB2D65B4A626B044_06FC410: Wait, really? It's been like four hours.
Dialogue.F06E4F7E4FDCA3AF83B92295231E2F88_06FC410: Wait, the hate potion didn't work?
Dialogue.5F6814F64C04EF7BA17479AE882A9D2B_06FC410: Wait, wait, wait. I hear something...
Dialogue.770A18C149890123A4271685EAA2B544_06FC410: Wait, wasn't the last one Vladsday's throne?
Dialogue.7F8D411848C8F39EA67AFDBF21E55E7A_7D086D9: Wait. Do you hear something? Someone's on the line. I can hear someone breathing.
Dialogue.4B37E76149C1DD6FF6D80BB6E5094F35_97A9259: Wait. Why did we get into a machete fight anyway?
Dialogue.EF15112C470B79758ABA169F011834F4_06FC410: Wait. You're having crazy nightmares too?
Dialogue.6CC720D9488546539C6454AFF577BC21_06FC410: Wait...wait. Say that again. Say that again, it sounds smart.
Dialogue.E32F9C6948C345A22BF22EB8DC905156_47CFF90: Want me to paint you a picture?
Dialogue.6D93C1B4461B5E924FE5379BBD1D55C2_8106785: Want you to believe the sky is falling. That the world is overtaken by storms.
Dialogue.8C97DE364C9A53E34EF3D38C26DE7F50_CC240C1: Warping your sense of self and your sense of reality...
Dialogue.8D56A8FD4F326D723E1DA0BEEC33AB3C_7D2960E: Was that before or after my twenty years of special forces service?
Dialogue.F56E1D6341AD6AA838C1C5A07FE886C4_06FC410: Was that the one with all the ED-EE episodes? What was up with that?
Dialogue.2C9937A54CD5C642D1CDCFB1AAB2D7FF_B229E47: Was there some sort of Reality Hiccups thing?
Dialogue.30BDD30041A7981A9F4F368723B68290_06FC410: Was this all part of a plan?
Dialogue.8D778AB146B82FE5E3C68CB7746AD72D_1D2FE88: Watch your step. We've got traps.
Dialogue.4D14D8234F3278BD3A53C4BA1D20A02D_06FC410: Way to go! More updated software!
Dialogue.6A06AF0E4D647BB7F09C8E9918E5C812_06FC410: Way to go, more surveying equipment! Keep looking.
Dialogue.AB7B46D846F2B727EE857A8408BB661B_06FC410: Way to smash that thing six ways from Vlaterday, commander.
Dialogue.3F29EF7B4C3C37AF85396DB005C8B42C_4731F06: We all fall back to the bunker, but it's too late. There's fire in the walls.
Dialogue.8FAA2ABF420C00840E507F8432157034_97A9259: We all grab the... uh, thing.
Dialogue.958B42264B4A3675F7BAD0B207FE73F0_87F0BBB: We all know this is a stupid idea, right?
Dialogue.5193F1AB48732EFC6D6A329DA3B17254_FB122F8: We appear to be in a state of profound instability.
Dialogue.54768BE2440C3C92D409CB9FC718323C_94F2B66: We are all soldiers on the battlefield of love!
Dialogue.38B01A9D4F05DBE15AA73B94B6EE5586_06FC410: We are either closer to or further from our goal of... whatever.
Dialogue.2D0657F04C06F810DC5588A161D59009_97A9259: We are here to help you!
Dialogue.9737D06B489E84556BAC97A4018F47F7_06FC410: We are hunting jolly ol' Saint Nick.
Dialogue.E1032EE5406948563937E2BDC6810FE8_06FC410: We are not helping slashers feel better about themselves.
Dialogue.1F3B217944414C93B1053190F9046E4D_861A10F: We are not naming her the "Bride of Rarrnold." That's a bit presumptuous, don't you think?
Dialogue.42DB57A14C855590125AA9933465DBBD_B229E47: We are now prepared to move on to the next phase of testing.
Dialogue.60B1BB954E2DFB677AD977ABD604FE9B_910A467: We are now up to four legs.
Dialogue.6FF95DFA4B24B4AE69996C825F0092D5_72190CE: We are pirates, with concussions, who have feelings.
Dialogue.7B6B7C4D4B6DFA7590445081D0A5FA29_A96EA86: We are probing the samples for any signs of weakness.
Dialogue.639570EB4AADA693898805921AEE9F0C_72190CE: We both get really, really seasick.
Dialogue.555D645842CCE40D64DAEA8A15900835_06FC410: We build a bunch of hoverboards that can fly themselves! Easy, right?
Dialogue.F21285A84AD54D36EE68F595C6005B36_FB122F8: We called it in. A team is on the way.
Dialogue.1BAA54DD475BEB8F51A01991D47837B3_06FC410: We can do better. We will do better.
Dialogue.992A16AA4C651A7CF643BDBB0DA2374E_AB3C42C: We can use this one for photos.
Dialogue.8C367B1C47221C6ADCA002B167D3853E_47CFF90: We can't just set them loose on the world.
Dialogue.41DE6FA9436B850E6B2B33B647D72CFA_FB122F8: We can't leave until we've found all those survivors!
Dialogue.ACCF11C344B47468107766881F54404E_06FC410: We can't let the husks destroy the drone!
Dialogue.1212D44643492FCE3DFAC6B9EEB97C6E_06FC410: We can't open the oven to install the new light without causing a major temperature fluctuation.
Dialogue.E0EC9652445CA0FD78F2C48FA16B0707_06FC410: We carbon dated the chrome husks and the results were inconclusive.
Dialogue.647ADA8A4D208BDFBC104084A4860896_06FC410: We cause a distraction, and then Ted... makes a break for it.
Dialogue.4FC25D1B4B4B878127A184B56CAD4B08_06FC410: We could have made a secret language and played tricks on people.
Dialogue.D4AA9FA04D9E75716E16A2B8A89C1D90_861A10F: We could really do without being chased by an angry mob.
Dialogue.8783A920466894959034AE8C82E3BF14_06FC410: We couldn't if we wanted to.
Dialogue.DB156E854B183D5504E2CDA202C264C4_861A10F: We destroyed your boats, mob! So keep your pitchforks away from my friends!
Dialogue.B5D9FE754C05AF010304B696F9E18ACB_B229E47: We did not win. But we are still here.
Dialogue.3601D3B54B673B0AA983C9BB83414765_06FC410: We don't even have TV. It's just security footage of monsters.
Dialogue.27B2DBBB477A6C14806968BEA2F12C82_06FC410: We don't even have a shark pit.
Dialogue.7C943FC442F2FC23B1EEB786DCF9F1BF_A96EA86: We don't have any, do we?
Dialogue.39B755EE457AE3C0F3A104875B73FD57_051E656: We don't have those. We have cricket creepers.
Dialogue.A5451CF84229A54B49933A81DF0886D8_B68F328: We don't have time for infighting.
Dialogue.6C58DCEF48349617AAD37EABC0B27206_06FC410: We don't have to keep doing this.
Dialogue.7FB6B70F4E49FC22D6CC2FA56A32D1F1_FB122F8: We fought off their arrows with an all banjo version of "Split the Check."
Dialogue.536B78024FE840E80627E19CE9F63DB2_47CFF90: We found our first spirit board! How does it work?
Dialogue.876C3BFB4C7D94EC2A339DB919178F35_97A9259: We found some... very gross... stuff.
Dialogue.ABFCF91540680A4D3CDCFEB1B7E14768_72190CE: We gave them the coordinates for Homebase and sent them on their way.
Dialogue.99F903F2423777162E8FA1BF9B69A762_94F2B66: We got big husks, small husks, baseball husks, flingers, gunslingers, blasters, smashers, elementals...
Dialogue.2C72C612499030C8D1045AB222156849_06FC410: We got some Retrieve the Data. Got some survivors getting rescued...
Dialogue.9C94085A4BDF2CA250EBEA90D3DFFA36_87F0BBB: We got ticket stubs here! So... so many ticket stubs.
Dialogue.D1F6948941DCF58469E85AB8B0C9FC34_06FC410: We gotta destroy some storm infected graves.
Dialogue.C3B53AC746F09390D4DF2AA7F1C90B8D_FB122F8: We gotta get the full road trip experience.
Dialogue.73166C5F49BFB1E44B5C7C9D7F2C73B4_06FC410: We had cornered the blackbooted devil, and nearly had him bested,
Dialogue.E1D85F7748F731B96793C787DA5E1751_1D2FE88: We had found a secret door.
Dialogue.5CBB8CCE4B4CBD61D74A68B928008986_06FC410: We had to lose the weight!
Dialogue.EAABE8684438E7EEE4A5C29C8E609B08_06FC410: We have Vindertech's second-in-command at our side.
Dialogue.13B819C145D265F4916FF4A35E943AE0_06FC410: We have a confirmed Vlad sighting in the Crawling Terror quadrant of Hexsylvania.
Dialogue.2AF8F08F487F374DE04C2CAE40FF2A62_47CFF90: We have cookies and milk back at Homebase.
Dialogue.2D1CE2824DB35FBCE2583A90B17310CB_06FC410: We have enough wakey-wakey juice to raise every vamp in town.
Dialogue.16D2A5CB4F20E0A057E25DB508FD53CC_94F2B66: We have got rifts! Look out!
Dialogue.0A0857514B3BF627CFF6A3857FBB37A7_FB122F8: We have more important things to worry about right now.
Dialogue.80E333404CC08CFE3C28B4A76C80265F_06FC410: We have some highly-experienced piracy experts right here at Homebase.
Dialogue.3CD43E234D1C4E0F4D487E83EAFE4B00_94F2B66: We have suspicious packages in the AO. Call in the bomb squad.
Dialogue.7A174F044162B2C2E85A6C9D24FE3C4E_06FC410: We have taken every precaution available...
Dialogue.CCE6FBED450F44EAAFAD1DB243D2126B_06FC410: We have the best team of heroes the world has ever seen.
Dialogue.14D01E574707747158CC4A87E2269425_97A9259: We have the cans of food, and I also put in there an ice scraper and some double-A batteries.
Dialogue.2CDF505B4FF9DE1C1FBCD880354F6B5F_06FC410: We have the classy entrance carpet, so this can be the fancy exit carpet.
Dialogue.89F9327D486905B4C0B616B8ADF3751C_06FC410: We have the hate potion ready for deployment.
Dialogue.B015A3D249A36E955D5D588F97E74A23_06FC410: We have to destroy Vlad's grave...
Dialogue.8981CBA14EB577167D98E1805185D84C_97A9259: We have to destroy the network before the time husks get Summer.
Dialogue.8F964663454C6F5D0E0C748E3C2A8F18_06FC410: We have to find a way to keep her here.
Dialogue.5D7B06374CA2CF31DDF1AFB7E9D4671A_861A10F: We have to keep Arrlene and Rarrnold safe from the mob!
Dialogue.535896BA4F55834268E8D5BF20811B08_CC240C1: We have to stay the rest of the week.
Dialogue.750B203A4F8877C736A2B3BB7E046502_97A9259: We have today. We have Steel Wool. And we have cannons.
Dialogue.47072CBC46E636990862FFB3D11438AD_06FC410: We have two weeks to complete the project, stay focused.
Dialogue.4C1E89B14BC59E616A8823B76F147860_9D00593: We haven't built the peppermint pavillion, or the hot cocoa lake...
Dialogue.AE75E13A418F97D9E7D9E7A792327E8B_06FC410: We just gotta let him finish.
Dialogue.4A18CDBD46826433170B318C94B9F3CD_B25EA52: We just need a little more.
Dialogue.5C3EA4D148534CEDBCB9F1AAAE811988_06FC410: We just need to know what to do about the werewolves and--
Dialogue.A6BC69104F7B00EDE6E6D6A401A562EB_D87E161: We kept going until we were no longer in love.
Dialogue.16B66066475F623C678B22AB741F3F6F_97A9259: We knew and we did it anyway.
Dialogue.2E7B9C1A4BEA39846694F19E2658D53C_97A9259: We knew the dangers of Taste Wizard. We knew that one day the system would turn on us.
Dialogue.65FCD5B1456D12CFA6C9FF8211B6F4B9_06FC410: We know Carlos went to the southwest, but we have no idea what's out there.
Dialogue.D85C2F30442798E0BC3D89B88CD40A6C_EAAE146: We know how to loot, pillage, and burn. That's enough.
Dialogue.60C3DCE74A5E3B45F124A49B4A410C88_FB122F8: We made it through some turbulence but now sensors indicate feelings of bliss...
Dialogue.AA8413014B31C9E7502583BD8952BBF1_97A9259: We make a paper mache Crackshot head.
Dialogue.F64FEFC64BAC913B6D18FE9E99F414EE_4731F06: We make it through the night, but... we lose a lot of good people.
Dialogue.0BBB4A024C795BD8B6BECABB28CCF71F_06FC410: We might want to destroy these. They can't be good for morale.
Dialogue.6D1F2B514A4892DF3C8652B6A4314F02_AB3C42C: We need a ground report for potential disturbance in 8H.
Dialogue.AEB2A6BA4D15BEC96E2283A44D135089_06FC410: We need a humane way to get rid of these bees. Search for fans... that might work.
Dialogue.8FDE96BC4AD683B9B8BFDB99FB7E18B0_9D00593: We need more. MORE! Or there could be... consequences.
Dialogue.F68D055144D44FFE20103D8E6F34293A_B229E47: We need to  - I need to break the design down and focus on containment.
Dialogue.9E8F02154E82ACDBBFC72B88D2DE0D95_FB122F8: We need to build a full on telescope array, so stock up on the primo optics.
Dialogue.D20E7E7E46646F088244E0AFDF468554_FB122F8: We need to build and reinforce a tower structure first!
Dialogue.C28FEF294998DAE6111AB8BE707A6334_97A9259: We need to build the perfect oven. This time, for real. Even heat. No hot spots.
Dialogue.600B8B2B4B69F29E87217CB56CB75007_FB122F8: We need to destroy those pods before they hatch those things!
Dialogue.EDFCAB01410007230BDCAB946CB11FBD_06FC410: We need to figure out how.
Dialogue.ED6F508C483C0A9D5D4A57BC9D6B5AB1_06FC410: We need to find a gravesite without a headstone.
Dialogue.86981A7C4EA446B7B3575E978749928C_06FC410: We need to find out how Lok was locked out.
Dialogue.D75284D24EFDB3BF4F86878C62C49BA6_06FC410: We need to find out what happened to these two.
Dialogue.E511DE1A43550E6842DA2DB9425AC5AC_97A9259: We need to find the location of Taste Wizard Prime.
Dialogue.928B0CB64094DCC22FAAB091437AF6EC_06FC410: We need to fly under the radar.

Dialogue.47C9E97A423D9BEE812FFAAD5FD1051D_06FC410: We're going to sort this all out.

Dialogue.A39F9D444A1F30CB8801478A60502530_06FC410: We've learned a lot from our time together. Some would say too much.

Dialogue.A3C2D9B1493235FE5F2994B46813A351_87F0BBB: Weapons aren't the only thing in society.
Dialogue.53054ED14F782F4A6F0F3188521A910A_06FC410: Weird. It's like a love potion but... actually way less problematic.
Dialogue.DDC34344432A4920F1AF83894509745F_06FC410: Weird. It's like a love potion but... actually way less problematic.
Dialogue.2297050745B86F46B088E0B99DE121C7_06FC410: Weird. Just a moment ago our sensors were saying this building was occupied.

Dialogue.BAFC92FB41448BF3D646C8A47DA00318_72190CE: Well, what if I don't want to?
Dialogue.3BF314D346DF8289EB2DCD8D0877A1B3_06FC410: Well, whatever's happening, I'm glad I'm not affected.
Dialogue.0E49B48C4EDB564829E5BE9D3D00D02B_97A9259: Well, when I started it, I thought it would be simple.
Dialogue.F145E8A343B6C9AAAF9A40B6301B14C3_06FC410: Well, why don't you take some time to think things through?
Dialogue.EAD53E494995068B0ADF618EE3A5FE3B_97A9259: Well, yeah, most of my plans go horribly wrong, all the time. Because I'm not, like, a time travel scientist, or a superhero, or a licensed landscape architectâ€¦
Dialogue.0BF93FBC4C77819ED06706B8797003A6_B222EAD: Well, you guys are so capable and really seem to know what you're doing.
Dialogue.148DFFA640D7D785BE3CE38A4F49D61F_AB3C42C: Well, you know what your vision is...
Dialogue.A078F4EC40D78ED3E39664A84D870551_47CFF90: Well, you'll get there. One ahoy at a time.
Dialogue.18C363AB404521987C7B8083105C0963_FB122F8: Well, your weather balloons are perfect for the short term forecast.
Dialogue.3B3693C340F472A5A9AAE6BEE3BC4578_06FC410: Well. Here you go. One fancy suit.
Dialogue.B301660047B3721C532E12BF60ECF39B_CC240C1: Well. Nobody likes it, but we've come to terms with its presence.
Dialogue.17A83C794DCE173D9F88098329B0A53F_06FC410: Well... I guess that's a problem for future us.
Dialogue.CD8B84044867E319738DA89C4A35871C_06FC410: Well... Let's look for more data. Or socks.
Dialogue.88B8BE674C7AD5BE0B44EA92E78146A6_06FC410: Well... best case we've made this place a whole lot less evil.
Dialogue.D384DE354332F41896C10BA4BDD1FED7_06FC410: Well... let's tell Ned the bad news.
Dialogue.220BC88040903D86958E689EF9D6A72F_06FC410: Well... on the bright side, I think we have everything we need.
Dialogue.E7740A5F485E286A5935EBB98567A839_87F0BBB: Well... sorry, Lars, but deleting your ex's pictures off your phone just isn't as satisfying as rippin' em up.
Dialogue.178B6D9D4196D84DD0CC5BA4C56EB589_B68F328: Wellâ€¦ alright. Whatâ€™s the worst that could happen?
Dialogue.0BCA48EB4B5001FCE856D2957C9B16DF_724DAF1: Welp. That's it for the pilot.
Dialogue.0E60CB85412DE18FFC7C649150B4CE21_FB122F8: Were you listening to me sleep?
Dialogue.613C83F747E45CB7CC8ECB8D2B613084_47CFF90: Weâ€™ll go over proper procedure for peg leg care and storage later. Iâ€™ve got a pamphlet.
Dialogue.FC948FAE4F2B14FCC139A193050D2B90_06FC410: Weâ€™ll have Spitfireâ€™s suit completed in no time.
Dialogue.2DC42F674154D37B4C3E79B5FE2CD0B2_CC240C1: What I saw was really, really scary.
Dialogue.6F0F127E46DC8F209ECBFB8EEC019A7E_06FC410: What Lars doesn't know won't hurt him.
Dialogue.00586F3C469120784ABEFFB8C376F12B_7D2960E: What Lars said about me not being my own man...
Dialogue.E14025AF4DD53B61C1F98A97C8D8B461_21C1927: What am I even? A- a doll? A weapon of war?
Dialogue.DAEF83EA4DE68C40ED2D57A87036C39B_7D2960E: What am I supposed to be doing or learning here?
Dialogue.2FEAB0A34F74444F5B1164BA4CFC482A_7D2960E: What am I supposed to do then?
Dialogue.C2A422C2405D32EDFE47B592FE8F0AD0_06FC410: What are the chances Dr. Vinderman uploaded some sort of program to SEE-bot before, um... the accident?
Dialogue.531FD703464625930033B49A2B7A98AC_176484F: What are we gonna do about it?
Dialogue.AD9BBF1D43871F46799D539CF73DDD6F_06FC410: What are you talkin' about? That's when he starts getting good.
Dialogue.95235FB64C9CCAF4F932FFAF95EECF7E_97A9259: What are you talking about? All I want is to find someone who loves me like you love Homebase.
Dialogue.E46CE8944B3821AF71FD20BA3CC168C1_06FC410: What are you talking about? Oh, wait. No. I just got the table thing.
Dialogue.4D6C678D419EE394B89554A48D904F23_06FC410: What are you talking about? Where are you going?
Dialogue.5311B43B4648754D6D3E8AB3EF9B3A5D_9F725B6: What are you thinking? What do you want to make?
Dialogue.3540E25445507EC0079448962AB92B44_97A9259: What are you, scared!? I double-demon dare you!
Dialogue.DE8960B245BB0DCC91FAF6B776914F83_06FC410: What are you, some sort of summer camp slasher expert?
Dialogue.1247007A4092634D56BD2AA5F005ABA8_87F0BBB: What are you? Homeschooled or somethin'?
Dialogue.88EFA28C415298B8318F2D81C167E266_97A9259: What can I do before Dennis Jr. leaves to make it up to him?
Dialogue.DCF6EA6941F32329C72BBD942D0A7AB9_0A979DB: What can I say? I love animals.
Dialogue.AAD3181547FF9189704C50A167E4CEE8_87F0BBB: What do we got, uh... dried rose petals, a bracelet, a stuffed molar that says, "I love you, that's the tooth."
Dialogue.B8D6AAE24813DDA3F517AC8E9CB39556_D87E161: What do you expect? Society doesn't want her to get it. It's not her fault.
Dialogue.4A0FA84C4794E43F41ECEA99870818B7_CC240C1: What do you mean we don't have a Battleforce?
Dialogue.FC01F2BB4584AB860DB1AC8BE0277C96_7D2960E: What do you mean, "This is a test?"
Dialogue.BD5377D4489A4C9415A097BB77508003_B229E47: What do you think I'm doing here, Desiree?
Dialogue.0BC3DCE14888543BFDCC37AED8ECE304_FB122F8: What do you think she was doing?
Dialogue.9E94474E46344A823DC964B8B992DD8A_06FC410: What do you think that means?
Dialogue.8FD42EBE435CCBBF6502E5A256DF4B59_06FC410: What do you want to do, Commander?
Dialogue.AB469F3A4C7C72D64F9AA6BBEC7630E1_21C1927: What else am I gonna do, stuffinhead?
Dialogue.0410F8F34264BD2A3B26CCB8ACAAB14B_7D2960E: What else do you expect me to do?
Dialogue.084B8B8C47D44FE2E571B0B8C4E00D70_89ED452: What else have I got going on?
Dialogue.32C30FF84DFD56D58F55888E2A6C5CC5_06FC410: What exactly are you making and why?
Dialogue.1A0D20F846A89454FAF5A787E64F3CEF_9D00593: What games can you play with a train, Lars?
Dialogue.F81AB99D42E3BB8058D9ABA099FA3524_CC240C1: What happened to the major's hand? In the story?
Dialogue.0882FB2E4F66FC33C65B8F85BA25ACE2_06FC410: What happened? Please, just tell us. Don't make it a game.
Dialogue.AF4E00D147DCA1F1309F8FB95783708B_7D2960E: What happens if I decide I don't want to have a change of heart?
Dialogue.39A0EC8A4F624CF03F1087BD3A38F2C2_97A9259: What if Dennis Jr's timeline is so good now that he doesn't need any of these cans?
Dialogue.987168234F1AD7F38D4A46A157E7B6D8_97A9259: What if he's so afraid of his destiny that he runs away and causes a time-shame paradox?
Dialogue.885BD64C43770B6F9D1D389282256808_B25AF7B: What if no one likes me? Am I getting the flu? Is Sophie mad at me?
Dialogue.30E25B704052D10DB932688A7C8CB9DF_724DAF1: What is it about legendary gunslinger Blackboot Ayers that fascinates us to this day?
Dialogue.F657893E4604EBC4A09ACB896C0A0141_06FC410: What is it, Dire? You got the secret to defeating the wolfpack?
Dialogue.7A8C15144FA3BB616E4A9BA264963E52_06FC410: What is the status report, Dennis?
Dialogue.3B8BDC6B4B5CE6BFDDB2C68CF1E9651A_06FC410: What is your deal, Owl Troop?
Dialogue.35F938524BE0EC5B8C0C2E851821E59F_06FC410: What is your plan, exactly, with these containers?
Dialogue.D332420645E4170E122678A70B3D3559_9D00593: What kind of dino are you holdin'?
Dialogue.17F386774F24ED023E2CCF87DBB0545B_06FC410: What kind of future do you see with Rarnold, Penny?
Dialogue.CFD9C73B44C29F9155BFD3ADB481191A_94F2B66: What makes your monster so scary?
Dialogue.CFB7BCDA442EC774183AF980118AD0E7_06FC410: What she's gonna do is shoot you with an adorable gun bear.
Dialogue.63903B67427B6CBB1FEAFF8998C63A98_06FC410: What sort of messages are we shootin' these days?
Dialogue.079E45EF4BB969ED886BC5AF62953425_B222EAD: What television has done to this generation of ghost hunters is unforgivable.
Dialogue.A54BA5994729A66F47E96FB1A863F543_97A9259: What up. I'm Dennis. Semi-pro ghost hunter and Ghost Boss in training.
Dialogue.88DBE1784B1D5FE5C26B068C793AB492_9F725B6: What was your favorite toy when you were a kid?
Dialogue.A3899F454AF0479AA3F5ABAB755138D8_AFB40E2: What we think of as love is a simple chemical reaction.
Dialogue.8664C1B54F86F4A7531B428338C83D1A_06FC410: What were you even going to do with this stuff?
Dialogue.9756E0E34D0BCC72FC238A860EFFF187_7D086D9: What were you hoping to accomplish by whispering into an open team com?
Dialogue.601A012842841F0E0F3EEEBA3B292878_06FC410: What were you hoping would happen with all this?
Dialogue.45BE51D84CD765A5E7B8CB892D2F53BF_B222EAD: What would she say if I put on a box and called myself her robot friend? "Beepity boop!"
Dialogue.4C334FBA46F839BB2C6BDC9E30231295_06FC410: What you just did to Lok was really, really cruel.
Dialogue.90CEF4A8428405B50700A99A5FF9DD97_06FC410: What you'll see through these telescopes will be frightening.
Dialogue.ED482EA0418C41AD3B87FA8F912E5CFC_84C369E: What!? I was still mastering my Running Man!
Dialogue.8AA678AF47A31B748582D78FC8DF83D1_06FC410: What!? We need to find those balloons!
Dialogue.C3A3652A425BE3AD7B7EDCA5E9C7BB4C_21C1927: What're you tryin to prove, Ted?
Dialogue.362CF9224C5A8B10752FEE89B01D9B44_9D00593: What's jollier than a snowball fight?
Dialogue.CC12F8C04B2BAF815FB7BB9DB85651EB_06FC410: What's life without a little romance?
Dialogue.0ED9703542A29AD12582738FE70C211A_7D2960E: What's my focus? Contracts? Tort law? Criminal defense?
Dialogue.D6C0D90E421759EBFB7480A0F31982D9_06FC410: What's that? You're breaking up. I can't -
Dialogue.039FD9C64111BD147A45C49FE5EAA6E7_06FC410: What's the answer you're looking for?
Dialogue.DADB7D724F882444437ED28D427DA381_06FC410: What's the worse idea, taking direction from dried up weeds...
Dialogue.A19AE29F46410146F580199090596BCA_06FC410: What's this? Wrinkled yellow pages, strangely perfect penmanship..
Dialogue.6508640B4CBB61BAEDF79B9F1CF494D7_724DAF1: What's up, you found the secret track.
Dialogue.E7FB2955439E44AFBA901CA222E2C8E5_D87E161: What, are you all soft now?
Dialogue.0F4A8389434963B9D2984AB9317911B9_06FC410: What, you didn't get the invite?
Dialogue.FCAE00424A2C0538660F589F7C257D2D_06FC410: What, you got a hot date or something? Heh.
Dialogue.B0798B2F4F5CBB9E41EAFDA78C783D3D_FB122F8: What? Alone in the storm in the middle of nowhere?
Dialogue.0112055E4D5581735749BC927223816E_87F0BBB: What? It's got a lot of pictures. It's not like he can read.
Dialogue.970196BD4D6DF780A83898B88ADC5B89_47CFF90: What? No! Have you... Do you have any idea what a â€œsimulatorâ€ is?
Dialogue.298581DB49609658C81309AB31A0F09D_FB122F8: What? No, no! Other people are scared of those flags. You guys are supposed to be doing the scaring!
Dialogue.CDD73E7D46A524EBE52ECE9CB4F6589F_D87E161: Whatever gets you through the night.
Dialogue.E7BB9E4A4E4D3E9338E93D938019F200_FB122F8: Whatever it is, it's sending out enough romantic vibes for a mega ballad.
Dialogue.1DECFC5A487979755C4B50A70389E273_06FC410: Whatever the evil version of crickets is...
Dialogue.CAF4DA6448CBD5CD04587F848C3281E4_181CD3E: Whatever was in me that made the Morpho Gear Gang... it's gone.
Dialogue.22BFF41E4503F3927763449B46A10BB6_06FC410: Whatever you do, don't stop running.
Dialogue.871A4EDF4EF4D6C1B2B48082A53EBE86_FB122F8: Whatever you say, Little Robot. But if I sleep, I'll have that dream again.
Dialogue.576633D94042F5C02C66E08ABF01F964_B222EAD: Whatever you're doing with this ectoplasm, you definitely have enough.
Dialogue.F6E1C7D84B6E9344C621909CBFC7E0E1_FB122F8: Whatever's up there.. it may be calling out to them.
Dialogue.560EBB544BF60524315005BDD52E615B_06FC410: Whatever's wrong, we can fix it.
Dialogue.2B07A015448E74DE24786DB6BA3C5654_21EB734: Whelp, I reckon that's the end of this particular adventure.
Dialogue.141145804A6F508E19124AB1FA7643B6_FB122F8: When I played my music, I noticed something. The husks hated it.
Dialogue.AA4DE8E5474D650DF06314B089A08BE6_7D2960E: When I tried to hit you earlier... Are you always that fast?
Dialogue.E8B24C6F47EE43C9C4B939A21893839D_9D00593: When I was sixteen I lied about my age and signed up for my first tour of duty. Santa Town. Oresville Mall.
Dialogue.2A0AA6834CC7A163B0C1A7A9ADFA9F9C_06FC410: When gold's too good, you turn to fool's gold.
Dialogue.3F3756474FB459D7A5FEBF8A04780D15_FB122F8: When he wasn't off causing trouble.
Dialogue.73ABD8B64FDA6670F3592D821CCEFE91_CC240C1: When it came near me, everything felt dark and sad... and it seemed like it would never stop being dark and sad.
Dialogue.404233AA431145EF1B61EC8673E455C7_06FC410: When it comes to seein' pirates, he be yer bot.
Dialogue.6AEE76144C00A429E347CE9885CCFC10_9D00593: When it goes off, it'll just shoot confetti and candy canes.
Dialogue.9BB143D543F8F623B27666A13C21B47B_06FC410: When it's complete, you'll be able to see the disturbance at the end of Canny Valley.
Dialogue.DEF570A64B55B7B9571414BFA003E65C_7D086D9: When it's time for you to know what I'm doing, you will know.
Dialogue.D4961199433E8ADB33273887FA4B6F92_9D00593: When life hands me a nutty problem, I open my jaws... and I chomp.
Dialogue.74F9AFA54EA1BFDAA69BBDB1ABCD176F_B222EAD: When the Door to Darkness opens...
Dialogue.35D4D7D94B227AA79F3ADE985C6F7084_910A467: When they took it, they found a solution to their problem.
Dialogue.BE3BFDA8420F0111415C9D92D0B27782_47CFF90: When we're done, you will be yo-ho-ho-ing with the best of 'em.
Dialogue.550683A3465A223FD2E926B3D8B67FE1_9D00593: When you buy the ticket, you gotta take that sleigh ride.
Dialogue.08751D934046A994C7F37D922B0D1E8E_CC240C1: When you find him, your heart will drown!
Dialogue.4668E6214BD4A8D0EC4C63A610582F36_94F2B66: When you find out who did this... (spits)... you let me know.
Dialogue.9D4CC8004E6EA3AEF1A3DDB069BD955C_0ADEFA4: When you help me, I bring it to him.
Dialogue.27B49A32439989A66523B990759CF9D4_9D00593: When you know everyone knows that's your main thing?
Dialogue.80DEBEC44613460CD1E119898C3C39B8_06FC410: When you look through the telescopes at... what's coming our way...
Dialogue.C91271F042144857DBD466A729985597_CC240C1: When you need something sent fast, use Outlander Express.
Dialogue.0CF14321483A1E0BFDAB699A61048D0B_47CFF90: When you say you can't take off the uniform, were you being literal?
Dialogue.96EA1E074009FCA3730ECCA3791B049F_910A467: When you're adrift in the magic of the cosmos.
Dialogue.15EF7A3E474DB9FB608D8CA678729297_06FC410: When you're done being a monster you can come inside.
Dialogue.E3EC18114DDACB3607BCA79324B17AA0_724DAF1: When you're famous, you pick up on things you can say to make people feel good.
Dialogue.04674E8C407C7B3209A248AB9C17438E_47CFF90: When you're relaxed, or at least better at lying.
Dialogue.01294535402D1A56B5416985DFA23427_9D00593: Where Homebase is tinkly, I want tinkly-winkly. Where it's sparkly, we need sparky-warkly!
Dialogue.D928DD314361485B5AB390B0C1817F9E_97A9259: Where he's discovered a huge monster!
Dialogue.FEDA8DF645DB6478154AC8925092A3F3_72190CE: Where is it? There it is. Now it's mine.
Dialogue.99F611E049501C02135BF397DF5AAD5C_7D086D9: Where is this even coming from?
Dialogue.C7B09B7D40926C56478E408BF82403A5_06FC410: Where my Bad Rays at? Hello?
Dialogue.B0F8ABDE45D594130414518BDC548D0A_7D2960E: Where'd I go to law school?
Dialogue.3FEB847048D525EF557FF7816A6A875E_06FC410: Whew. Staff Reporter Tina Albright, you are not subtle.
Dialogue.B935AB754F8BD7AC48453781D1E284A9_97A9259: Which I probably should not have picked up. Eugh.
Dialogue.8DFBABDE43DBDF362823AB99F84C3BF6_06FC410: Which according to the guidebook was twelve days long.
Dialogue.8C7F647748E018C031859DA7EB56DC58_06FC410: Which again is not his weakness even though that would have been really great.
Dialogue.D05AA81D4D34F3F626EB1DBFB001A1FB_06FC410: Which is a feature I did not know our sensors had...
Dialogue.69B780D5448E5D34D128EBBF3A7F8026_AB3C42C: Which is fortunate because I expect to see nothing less.
Dialogue.CC4EB7E94893D72B3FE7DCB2BFDBDDAD_06FC410: Which is the only option if you want a gravestone these days I guess.
Dialogue.C88969D64F8D6F5D2E7A918A2CBF0136_14FBFB1: Which is why I want to tear it to pieces and burn the remains.
Dialogue.73744B04437F65267820EC86E2CC4CD5_06FC410: Which is why he decreed that all existing Vladamantium must be fashioned into things that are absolutely not knives.
Dialogue.1229EB55487C729A5E34A599F9511F6F_06FC410: Which makes me think we, collectively, are not ready for love.
Dialogue.80F6094844B5304F734C408B64A78A7E_47CFF90: Which reminds me... Nice job, son. You're really going places.
Dialogue.AF3773264F5BAAF3F704E98D1A46CE89_06FC410: Which should offset the damage I've done by releasing Vlad the Vicious the Second...
Dialogue.334F9992440AED131FC1F18C32B25D86_7D2960E: Which was the right answer, I guess.
Dialogue.C9A37FEC4C943E4A2F87CBA468CEDF71_97A9259: Which you would know if you read the memo.
Dialogue.E785E3B04D1736C2B9B089B3E3440EA6_06FC410: Which, if any of the hoverboards happen to ask, are very very good.
Dialogue.58F3FC8A4F5D8C4293C943ADCBDDFB8A_9801E98: While I am an accomplished Jefe player, I really don't understand why.
Dialogue.BB3EE9CE46C2C1A837439DB49B814D16_21EB734: While I am not a superhero I have seen many movies about superheroes.
Dialogue.27B27692489DCCA401D2F69E11BD701B_861A10F: While I can't fit the one circle inside the bigger circle... It was ghastly.
Dialogue.0465B3E743F726E58485348A7AD61CDD_06FC410: While Lars thinks let's gather more husk data.
Dialogue.061EA1DC41F3EA4A11F9709FED1DE6D2_06FC410: While drum machines just play loops and beats,
Dialogue.E06439D94A720C368F6BF8A56F469412_7D2960E: While we're on the topic of things not making sense...
Dialogue.805DEB524B7167698F03429DDCCB18F2_47CFF90: Who am I to begrudge you the odd comment about... oh, I donâ€™t know... scallywags or doubloons?
Dialogue.0A74E53549D958C0599EB1819068DA7E_94F2B66: Who am I to say it's not? But it's not. Alright, back to the monsters!
Dialogue.ABE3E0C64FF2F571B0CD6EAA6B4BC268_21EB734: Who among us can't burst into flames once.
Dialogue.766274D34616F738EC153AAA072C2253_EECA944: Who does that to their child?
Dialogue.CFB4F3E44D6B389FAE26118D320B3855_B222EAD: Who else is gonna do it?
Dialogue.F22B2ED841312A55F4DE47A703E7906D_FB122F8: Who gives that as a gift? What were they thinking? Don't they know anything?
Dialogue.EA2B1EEC451BA3A83C5FA7A33B42CDDB_97A9259: Who knew clocks could teach us so much about time.
Dialogue.0C70AB534A6AE2404C0EA7994F1850F5_06FC410: Who knows when we'll be back. Hopefully this will help.
Dialogue.815DCD1C478C3FE2995290900A8FF12B_06FC410: Who knows, maybe this will be fun.
Dialogue.EA7565DF44503C2AF95E7D95EB0EFC0D_FB122F8: Who knows. Before the storm hit, Carlos invited me to join him on a research project out in the desert.
Dialogue.E64B81334E7AA4C17C3C4DA0872D0D07_06FC410: Who knows? Maybe we'll find something helpful.
Dialogue.E210D9D149CDBEE4FE1421873C8BF041_06FC410: Who maybe doesn't understand what paper is.
Dialogue.4BE5958C4E29ED73B47271A16149E410_06FC410: Who should be here by now. What gives?
Dialogue.CF6E8CE346C276E759A4EBBF5CADA409_7D086D9: Who taught Seventeen the words to Jonnie Galactic?
Dialogue.E249CAE54C3D3B73FF5676AEE6F903DE_06FC410: Who wants to eat everyone in Homebase? You do! Yes, you do!
Dialogue.894F63984AE65F2964D1258AFEF12D03_06FC410: Who wants to wage war on their molars?
Dialogue.449E3CC646074FF624E84C9A0E164440_CC240C1: Who will answer our call for help?
Dialogue.12D0A7734380C71A9BBC939F52D607A5_FB122F8: Who's gonna cuddle with a tooth? Who is gonna be crying and sad and say, "Oh, at least I have my stuffed tooth."
Dialogue.4AF68EBE45EAEC692968F59868A982E1_06FC410: Whoa! Dennis, what's going on, buddy?
Dialogue.58EE11964B90F64A3789118831953A46_97A9259: Whoa! Hey! Alright! We're all freaked out.
Dialogue.85AD759E452D5F05ECC58D9246F14D71_FB122F8: Whoa! Is that a first edition of Extended Solo Monthly!?
Dialogue.84CD5F0C4CDD2210970CBF9326C8BBFB_06FC410: Whoa! Let's not go straight to watery graves, right? We're just here to make sure you and Blake survived the crash.

Dialogue.4A8BF8EA47D91E127D3894BFEB4227BC_97A9259: Yeah. I'm gonna be a dad.
Dialogue.AFE056794263E3FFACC536A14FBD7036_FB122F8: Yeah. It's one of my favorites too.
Dialogue.034F78C64EBCEB001CA28C9347D27A21_EAAE146: Yeah. Not to be insensitive but... we've still got all our legs.
Dialogue.54C79BAF476591EE9FED2D8400C6F252_EAAE146: Yeah. The Director told us all about how we're supposed to be scared of these flags.
Dialogue.1B3570BE4F2209A61806B28D2751CF62_06FC410: Yeah. There are other Rays. You're not special.
Dialogue.0F7F5AEE4468D55C5C6CE18C9D22452F_FB122F8: Yeah. Yeah that's probably what happened.
Dialogue.213DE39F44346B404894008FE052EB53_06FC410: Yeah... And we really, really need their help finding treasure.
Dialogue.8142B9B34FEF081D68A9FB8D47DB6AD4_72190CE: Yeah... just a little winded. And bleeding. But, uh... but I'll be okay.
Dialogue.390A57E04A3C3883FF1ACF898C46BB27_FB122F8: Yeah... this might be the end of Bad Ray.
Dialogue.3EAF252042161760D9963FAA1A25D987_94F2B66: Yeesh. Just when you thought those things couldnâ€™t get nastier.
Dialogue.6A93ED50449EBFFBFA56CBBB59FEE63A_861A10F: Yep. Another SEA-Bot, and another note.
Dialogue.4A9C9D8D4CA95586077955BDAF8683D4_EAAE146: Yep. I'll still walk the plank.
Dialogue.6A8E83CD41C1A3C89A74649A6091BD9B_47CFF90: Yes thatâ€™s... thatâ€™s a good start, Keelhaul.
Dialogue.0344D2B04761C9977506B8A4810B2F67_EC1949E: Yes! Don't you listen to him?
Dialogue.D2C22CE74811D7FEB96AB18B3306D89B_06FC410: Yes! Great job vacuuming up our equipment.
Dialogue.1A0B389E43460BEB9454D194914874BD_06FC410: Yes! More software for Dennis' movie!
Dialogue.77C8BD864B1A88EC19633FBBAD8DAA61_97A9259: Yes! Now I can do lens flares!
Dialogue.30BCD9384A863FD1400F12B4A9749FFA_06FC410: Yes! That's all the troll holes!
Dialogue.20A314A2494331248C93989CD4C76274_06FC410: Yes, Dennis, we have pirates now.
Dialogue.A11BCDE848178C6C57C0BDA4290A0A3E_06FC410: Yes, I saw your sarcastic wink.
Dialogue.8140E9EC4A605C424DE20DB13953CB3F_9D00593: Yes, I've been to two conventions. But both were the result of a series of hilarious misunderstandings.
Dialogue.4309624E43C67D102C29C9A8EC5BF58A_9D00593: Yes, another tree! They will know the true meaning of the holiday.
Dialogue.4EC365E24DD98A77C72A6B950CBD771E_7D086D9: Yes, but it's also what missing a cry for help looks like.
Dialogue.5425302E42AC28DDCCC3DE93A3C146FB_A96EA86: Yes, dude. I've been super clear about that, and every time you ask adds one minute.
Dialogue.197F36B648D7EECD741D4798986BBE13_06FC410: Yes, thank you, Pop. And scared.
Dialogue.88CD872649C4EC0D8CC3E793906A48F5_AB3C42C: Yes, the world has been taken over by storm monsters.
Dialogue.FE07A71F4536DDDBD0E72190EC268F5D_47CFF90: Yes, these are your Plain Janes. Itâ€™s good to have quite a few of these.
Dialogue.612F15D14518B04FFF8FBF8A2CB592FB_47CFF90: Yes, well, for better... or probably worse... you are our one-man Homebase Holiday Committee.
Dialogue.55E1D92B49FAE4C815EA428F732047AD_47CFF90: Yes, yes! I believe that should do quite nicely. Excellent springs. Good bounce-to-the-ounce ratio.
Dialogue.3A3D6ACD42896981A336919B04D6F05A_06FC410: Yes, you are somehow my first ghost.
Dialogue.F03D3308483DC2F455744890083C1C21_DB7CBEB: Yes. And then I turn to camera and say... "fight fire mit fire".
Dialogue.7629C7F6415864D4CBF3DD881E55F73A_FB122F8: Yes. And they need our help.
Dialogue.82E6DE1F473062FD561C31BFDF670C5E_7D086D9: Yes. Grab as much as you can.
Dialogue.C2B809C24E6A30FBF56A36A728CC9437_06FC410: Yes. I agree with that. What can we do to help?
Dialogue.36A47A5D4F75A1BE3DEC9AAFBA7815A1_7712BEE: Yes. I double majored in Slashers and Rippers.
Dialogue.2D14FA454AA27017A5F481A0D50846FF_47CFF90: Yes. Itâ€™s absolutely impractical and you'll surely never use it, but inevitably someone is going to ask if you have a leg gun...
Dialogue.CD2E66C04A11BA611EA240BE1FCE06FC_06FC410: Yes. That's why we're doing this in shifts.
Dialogue.E9E726234045E690BA5AA5B270B6B74B_9D00593: Yes. This is enough spirit for at least a ho-ho, if not a ho-ho-ho.
Dialogue.83916C6B48C09CF8983F598D547F72BB_47CFF90: Yes. We've established that many times over.
Dialogue.48F8904B415F1226C8A0238C295382D5_97A9259: Yes. You'll be perfect for my machine.
Dialogue.8F3B5B424F6405BE90D0EF9679C3C0BF_06FC410: Yknow, Dennis, I don't know if I've ever said this but..
Dialogue.32FA97524AF0A94D2EADDAA1009034AE_06FC410: Yo Dennis. You mentioned something about a network. How we needed to destroy it before it got to Summer.
Dialogue.47F3E14D47CEA9D3EA144EA10B7DAA96_06FC410: Yo Lars! We're finding some great stuff down here.
Dialogue.2E8E53D94807683D60D5799659B376DA_06FC410: Yo Lars, I need to get a lay of the land. Can you assemble a fleet of cartography drones?
Dialogue.15D7E0614A33FE2E731B609205A7832D_06FC410: Yo Syd, found a rock for ya.
Dialogue.C0089B56400C097FC3C4269D8403D056_06FC410: Yo Vlad, this town ain't big enough for me, the commander, a team of heroes...
Dialogue.E4CB55334FB1E3DDBECF5CB8D0FFFBBB_06FC410: Yo Vlad. Let's see you come back now.
Dialogue.DBB8558340E7B10F597A66B355999500_B25AF7B: Yo ho ho, to the interwebs we go! / We plug in our cables, we watch our router lights / Stealin yer movies and music / Doing wrong with yer copyrights / Yo ho hooooo! To the interwebs we go!
Dialogue.259D08E942C4BA840E2BE8942DEBAF95_B25AF7B: Yo ho ho, we're sailin' on a boat / Yo ho ho, that's all the songster wrote.
Dialogue.84452E5D46399093C8B8479FF61AF5F6_06FC410: Yo, Dennis. I got you some love lobber potions to smash.
Dialogue.2A16DB5849C830A4BBB8D6A2E1C353FB_06FC410: Yo, Dennis. Is Meat-Cute any good?
Dialogue.913CB7D64FBD265A0BBFFF8EB61653CC_97A9259: Yo, Lok. You want a toy plane?
Dialogue.34DD2CBE40A44C648F74AF82A7EF6747_724DAF1: Yo, pass out the donuts. My boy's just had a breakthrough.
Dialogue.5F00F05441BF16AFA963199274FCB723_06FC410: Yo, wasps! Tell your friends we support bees!
Dialogue.C922C0CC4BC10EA9B2EC1DBC6771AC97_06FC410: You Good Rays are all the same.
Dialogue.D3A4EAB04E8E5B307E9BFCB22F475510_C9708CA: You and me and seven billion people might have been caught off guard by the storm... but someone out there knew it was coming.
Dialogue.64AB723B4A21544173E785877FFD38A6_724DAF1: You and me, man... it's like we live on the same shelf.
Dialogue.9204E48F4C960AA74AC383A6087FF7C7_7D2960E: You answer to it, you live with it, Front Mullet.
Dialogue.FA459BE549FECFEB3899AA9581A17785_06FC410: You answered "12." Which, judging by your smirk, you must think is very funny.
Dialogue.0F68C8FF4017C15A191105B1EF22E212_06FC410: You are a master tomato tracker.
Dialogue.C0F4457B4E1A624B361D19A417A4D5A2_FB122F8: You are aware there is no Lars version two, right?
Dialogue.B1411DB2465934D465CE9A810510A69A_06FC410: You are cleared to bust any and all moves.
Dialogue.CE3A101A4400A525CE91C5898322843B_06FC410: You are going to get a call. Do not put it on the air.
Dialogue.EC07D0F148DF72A5A35CAAA05018446D_97A9259: You are in for a treat!
Dialogue.C01C738B40ECC8E93FED32AF329838F9_FB122F8: You are on the cover of that album.
Dialogue.6B387E9B4DD7A01E218A56B8A44FFB9F_B222EAD: You are pressing your luck, buddy.
Dialogue.D3DFAF854575D18AA2CE7C8923371044_7712BEE: You are so certain you're good.
Dialogue.D3056873462A9E2E95CB88AE30D878B1_FB122F8: You ask me, that looks like a husk.
Dialogue.F786184F48D2ADFAB15FAAADB7AC7EE1_9D00593: You better hurry, because I'm going to knock two hours off the countdown.
Dialogue.CC50EF7B4CAC880F667B00BE9E5D85CA_176484F: You call yourself a bad Ray. Can you elaborate?
Dialogue.DD4030FC44A9D4ED005EF49C911695EA_724DAF1: You can expect lots of surprise guests, unexpected twists, and of course, epic drum offs.
Dialogue.A4773CEC42E7E74C9C3AE08B6C3AE088_06FC410: You can feel it coursing with ancient power!
Dialogue.EA187DFB42EFF577B61822826E3B94E5_CC240C1: You can go. I'll tell Ray you stayed the whole time and you said, "Sorry."
Dialogue.75526FBF4C9D5191CA7D9D90BD256036_06FC410: You can have the amount of time it takes to come up a plan that doesn't kill everyone.
Dialogue.3780AF014644D03D25094780BB6AE2B9_06FC410: You can learn to support Dennis Jr. emotionally and really connect with him on a deep level.
Dialogue.EB84EB3B4ACFAB54C43E13BF74B299CF_97A9259: You can never tell for sure this early on.
Dialogue.458E94C040611F75E80B69BF0E17F75B_06FC410: You can rumble, but you can't hide.
Dialogue.CF5CF52C4E19EF5C1C352783C02F40DD_724DAF1: You can tell it's not important.
Dialogue.1CE192D14FCCF69AD7A048B8048E2446_94F2B66: You can try to hammer the husks. I'll keep shooting them.
Dialogue.1AEA65CF44275067E2BE36A82781E825_06FC410: You can't build a laser without glass...
Dialogue.4E44DCF04BE9289FA519569207C688DF_06FC410: You can't call a band meeting when you're on band probation! Get it together.
Dialogue.48E43BE846756F796F442BAE67EE3491_06FC410: You can't domesticate a husk, Penny, no matter how much you think you love him.
Dialogue.E82E0C954C27DEB47A0DEBB2493336C3_7D2960E: You can't fix that if you're dead.
Dialogue.4C758A4C421139CA9DA672A2036B6745_06FC410: You can't have coffee. Liquid makes you catch on fire.
Dialogue.FC7F031C40B37B084963BA858BBFB571_47CFF90: You can't ignore without learning to listen, first.
Dialogue.8E9777DD4E183073CAB8DF932561A9D6_AFB40E2: You can't love someone if you don't first love yourself.
Dialogue.B19220684983772F69C5E48CA70C21A0_06FC410: You can't say it's healthy and also that it's candy.
Dialogue.9D7D1A3B46FC6961B51F5A82C9CAE48F_861A10F: You can't tell someone else who to invite to their wedding, Dennis.
Dialogue.C9C0D729495D207ABAAEA8B53756C47D_FB122F8: You can't. I removed the thing.
Dialogue.A850ACFA4BEC873EBF6ED980EA97AC51_0A979DB: You clearly want to tell it. You tell it.
Dialogue.2F208A7A4FCC4BB3A47D7386E4FCF0C9_4731F06: You could make me one of your signature burgers.
Dialogue.FD1BD0CA4EA0ABD3C34202ACAB4F218E_97A9259: You could say watching a movie about the parents of an unborn rebellion leader,
Dialogue.D90E43354F1179646D56E5A0D34F9AF6_21C1927: You couldn't even flip a coin?
Dialogue.67183E6945AF5C6C3274BF99A5497C1C_06FC410: You deserved so much more and so much better than what we gave you and--
Dialogue.1D1817CD4C2866EEE374EC98724292F7_AB3C42C: You did tell them to write an episode of "Beyond The Stellar Horizon," right?
Dialogue.0EEAFF27474D2AA5D2876E9C9A1CB96A_94F2B66: You didn't die in there, did ya?
Dialogue.0E0CBC27479D92DA1344ECA50DADAC87_9801E98: You didn't ruin everyone's life, man. Just mine. And Carlos'. And Anthony's.
Dialogue.7D16F0554B1D726BD4FC289C499D73CA_06FC410: You do bad, you know what you've done.
Dialogue.4A77549243A3D72D6C3FF595C8D16440_EAAE146: You do it. You've earned it.
Dialogue.5DD96F434D37BFF13A8EE0998014961C_97A9259: You do remember we're his hostages, right?
Dialogue.AC476F624B80742BE636E4B4ECC83A3B_06FC410: You dodged a bullet. She was literally a monster.
Dialogue.1E8FECF043552C1B60F303ACE9D354D6_7712BEE: You don't become evil simply by not being good.
Dialogue.04C0A340495CF5720F537893884BBBF4_7712BEE: You don't do that to the ones you want to keep.
Dialogue.E4A13AB64241C3C8A415528E0015B236_9D00593: You don't even have stockings hung from your fireplace.
Dialogue.E4D3BB67426E1BCDE44903B8AC53CB4C_97A9259: You don't get to the sovereign nation of Lovesylvania without crossing a few boundaries.
Dialogue.85D641964EA15D381AE0E8850ABD789B_06FC410: You don't have a son and that is not where this is headed.
Dialogue.CD09AA43477FF3A98A7A0399B5ACA94E_7D086D9: You don't have any other choice here.
Dialogue.85D3573B4341FABD45778C89A341430A_06FC410: You don't have to believe in us, just know we're here if you need us.
Dialogue.6A14A8E74388C001271DBD9BEA063411_97A9259: You don't have to convince me.
Dialogue.27B4845A45C29F7B2F7D429C73819E96_06FC410: You don't have to cook for the pirates.
Dialogue.3D00A08249B4F034BAA62F835C520B8F_97A9259: You don't host a call-in radio show about love without learning a few things.
Dialogue.D7E4136E4B076C87E872B1AA31DAA821_861A10F: You don't know him like I know him!
Dialogue.E1203BED4613393428DD0E9D7D4E8055_724DAF1: You don't need to be any of those things to make a difference. Youâ€™re Dennis.
Dialogue.4572AD1E4F18925A0970898C5EF9F33C_861A10F: You don't seem to think my stories are all that scary, so...
Dialogue.5785D07B464B134C55EB7CBFE1E4DB55_FB122F8: You draw two cards for referencing a rule.
Dialogue.DDB25A134A22E6D7C9A806B7DC2362C9_94F2B66: You enjoy that anomaly slurping down your life force, rookie? I didnâ€™t think so!
Dialogue.5054912D448FF4F3B59AF793E1FF2520_9801E98: You ever seen a land periscope?
Dialogue.74CD07164D75A516BF6FDABF37727B3B_14FBFB1: You figured right. But... I got to thinking.
Dialogue.1593890B4E8DB6EC0AB3C49E182E37D2_06FC410: You find the control circuits we need, I'll learn to solder.
Dialogue.B146FB8745A54E5352D3C6BF93134CFD_06FC410: You found another of Carlos' research setups!
Dialogue.D533B37D45EE24FCADFABC885BF39AE6_06FC410: You get the gist of this one.
Dialogue.9D9FC77C4F915161943946BFAA760166_B222EAD: You give gifts to people that don't want your help?
Dialogue.B0D12B3543B4857ECD25F89BCD4450EE_06FC410: You go ahead. I need to sit here for... however long it takes me to not want to yell at Dennis.
Dialogue.2DA510BD448BDEBCDFFDDDAA3D9B5922_9801E98: You got chops, my dude, but you're confusing.
Dialogue.BBA6BC1747B3A2697E30C68B8630DB16_FB122F8: You got it, Little Robot. This is an air current chart between here and...
Dialogue.854D59754FEB9196F38AA99DE63DE740_FB122F8: You got me thinking about my touring days, so I broke out some Steel Wool.
Dialogue.A4787F5445FBDE999AE3A792501FDFE8_97A9259: You got the spark, Ray. Now share it with Homebase!
Dialogue.36F178A34D38549F8E6835B0B207F8FE_A96EA86: You got those first day jitters, I get it.
Dialogue.64B2DFFE4D3F709C46D57CB2D9043502_06FC410: You gotta change that right now, Ted.
Dialogue.987368B44D9AEFF44A36E0AE77A09DCC_9801E98: You gotta do something while the samples process.
Dialogue.1858B13A48ACC3432BA419AD14083E21_9F725B6: You gotta find your own way.
Dialogue.6057D7A942C86F09AF1A4AA35F26AAAE_06FC410: You grab his... head, and I will grab his feet.
Dialogue.7058592A40B20EDF409B19AB1336D9CD_FB122F8: You guys are dealing me nothing but trash.
Dialogue.75A6EAD34C00C17C9CC637B262E7058A_EAAE146: You guys are pretty good at fighting those... things.
Dialogue.BFB2A3BA479A32F3AC823D8F33C34942_724DAF1: You guys should listen to Dennis. He's wise beyond his words.
Dialogue.5CA92911451AB60A467E3780BCD3C148_97A9259: You guys will never believe what happened. I had the craziest dream.
Dialogue.D805217C469FB1FD098F568843C51051_C9708CA: You guys... I'm serious. You've got to take care of each other.
Dialogue.61D2661A411F12759C059FA59C02051F_06FC410: You have a secret lair? Can I see it?
Dialogue.3309552147F139F142E15591DAD83E22_87F0BBB: You have no idea how long I've waited for someone cool to show up here.
Dialogue.5DD630E541C5C1513597EC8A6F5990F0_06FC410: You have nothing to be embarrassed about.
Dialogue.E4C468684946BDEDE5E2508A56C398BB_47CFF90: You have seventeen people on hold. I could let you get back to it.
Dialogue.A51DE2E0481195439A96469DF29F8CB1_06FC410: You have to give me something. Give me a reason to trust you.
Dialogue.2AD942ED47BE4D126D6858A1644BC346_724DAF1: You have to yell, "I have the capacity to change. Today is the day I become the real me!"
Dialogue.25B5448A43CFC3F15CE9E7A81A35834C_06FC410: You hear me? Take me back and I will shower you in Nedkits.
Dialogue.E1D7EA7441B4449B838384B78B02FA29_A96EA86: You just bought yourself another minute.
Dialogue.DDC0206A45D7FDAF9EBFD192D310ED92_97A9259: You just want to flaunt your water privileges.
Dialogue.D72FF2564740E636AD593EAADADB0A0E_06FC410: You keep it up and you're getting wheels!
Dialogue.8EFB94724C89109AC9204482783575AE_87F0BBB: You keep rocking on against love, Lars.
Dialogue.D9FBC20548073E9E0DB7AB9B9C7791BF_06FC410: You keep talking about my vision. What if I don't have one?
Dialogue.260967C842C51AD44F6BE1826675217E_7D086D9: You kinda do. But let's focus on impressive, showy plots of land.
Dialogue.E7044B8E459FAD61FC1C95A1477FEBD2_06FC410: You know I was lying about letting that strange weirdo die out there in the storm.
Dialogue.A99F3A2F4F2CD5D6582437A7C485B7B5_D87E161: You know how I feel about flattery.
Dialogue.831D613A4A588BD993D517803E983BFC_B222EAD: You know how vengeful spirits are.
Dialogue.87ED303440591D95F627C38CBD3AEF36_06FC410: You know how we have that bot that sees things for us?
Dialogue.16312EF04B17124696D8BB937A0B4A2A_06FC410: You know in your heart what the truth is.
Dialogue.88E3F17740FB6B8A3CA95C959FC5E819_FB122F8: You know it's Carlos... or you hope it's Carlos?
Dialogue.030C6C6C4196394066DD59935F282F51_D87E161: You know it. My love life is a dumpster just waiting for that one romantic spark.
Dialogue.D36B097E4C8509E6F85077872EBC07A9_FB122F8: You know the musicians aren't actually in the radio. Right?
Dialogue.41A1AA864A97DCDF4460708BB5E1B742_B222EAD: You know there's a gigantic hole in the floorboard, right?
Dialogue.B3BAA77B4D48F7268ED7A7AD1427AE94_EC1949E: You know what I think, Lok? Sometimes you just need to distract yourself.
Dialogue.386C5EA44EDEECC3A143FCACCA7CFD99_06FC410: You know what, I'll do it. It's fine.
Dialogue.A6AA0B5E4EBBCBC83A16E7916C234499_06FC410: You know what, we've got enough pioneers.
Dialogue.F30A57A34CDCF44A0D4F3C9B7A46CFC1_06FC410: You know what. I'm starting to not like these people.
Dialogue.FAB2E0C743F2DE52B4C89892F6207C5C_FB122F8: You know what... do what you gotta do.
Dialogue.97A016F44A39510337DB159C79A788BD_06FC410: You know what? Both at the same time is totally fine.
Dialogue.5C300BD547AC548A7807DBB5EC4E2A9B_97A9259: You know what? Don't be afraid to break his heart in public, girl. That is ratings gold.
Dialogue.39EA6E0D4006C357CEFEAF8857193293_72190CE: You know what? Everyone, we're opening it together!
Dialogue.FC73293549425566AACC33BC8AD09596_06FC410: You know what? I admire that. It's bold.
Dialogue.A695753A4A23FD7FFA11B9B19CEA66B4_FB122F8: You know what? I apologized to Carlos. I thought we were cool. What happened?
Dialogue.A7E608004B64F912F6D2F6A5E98D1B86_06FC410: You know what? Maybe I just need to get in the mood for love.
Dialogue.9E721C6740C27C84D9D33787B0D7F3A4_EED9CD8: You know what? That's very fair. That's very fair.
Dialogue.A2244F764D4E1480FD55E2B8BEF3ED94_06FC410: You know where this is going...
Dialogue.56E1D0F44D29C7D47638F3ABEB86C6A1_A96EA86: You know you can loosen up if you want?
Dialogue.EB9C304343D4A7161EF04B8717A86E72_06FC410: You know you can't stay with us, Dire.
Dialogue.040ADBDD4A5CB2C5E79AE284F464F279_06FC410: You know, I never thought story problems would come in handy.
Dialogue.200ECA2D4D4AED186F040DB23E7DD9D2_FB122F8: You know, I think whatever is happening in the sky...
Dialogue.97DD7CEE4E2958EDA2F4B4921AB011C5_06FC410: You know, I want to make fun of this, but honestly they're Homebase's happiest couple.
Dialogue.C41B187F4FD970EBE7465A82E8448512_06FC410: You know, I'm really starting to like this plan.
Dialogue.320EF78743803A101F2549B66BF42981_9801E98: You know, Lars. Anthony's a screw up, but at least he cares about someone other than himself.
Dialogue.D2845DC240051DBF03C9A69B9C938AFD_06FC410: You know, Penny, sometimes you just gotta let a husk be a husk.
Dialogue.8F3A9ACA4443739EE6FA53949EEA68DA_47CFF90: You know, as a brief aside... I think we might want to talk about your name, Blake.
Dialogue.87646CD3404C2D8A1905F8AB7B40BE77_06FC410: You know, in my life so far I have had like nine people say that to me.
Dialogue.ECF2653D4AFBF16F5E282A815D7748E4_87F0BBB: You know, some cultures had vocabularies made up of only a few words.
Dialogue.D70CB16945913D25F4F8F4BF9DAE2B42_AB3C42C: You know, the rocket could be the thing that stops the volcano eruption.
Dialogue.E2C1798D48E3E8238EB3FCAEFA15A361_97A9259: You know, they make plans to meet with friends a few weeks out, but never more than that.
Dialogue.2DC7CD874277E84CDA302E9E379EF476_06FC410: You know, this tree may provide the strength that holds up the fort that withstands the biggest storm of all.
Dialogue.DE2A08F449D21E282A5338BCDF34D7A7_97A9259: You know, this would go a lot faster if you just haunted everyone else.
Dialogue.7A1FFE624E1EB3DA0182E0BEDC38E876_97A9259: You know, we both lost a lot of credibility with that ghost tape reveal.
Dialogue.617B325D40E3127181D5358ECF6619E7_06FC410: You know, you have my sympathy...
Dialogue.90DB98E44D783EE33C57F88C435B8205_861A10F: You know... I don't know really.
Dialogue.ABB4BC08423EA9B04C9E05B8987CBEAA_7D086D9: You know... If I understood what was happening I never would have left.
Dialogue.C0DF24C84162B95A62558CB54137D9E3_97A9259: You know... Lok's outside, there's a monster saying, "rarr!"
Dialogue.61F2E43B4438B0A7DE152C9045959FFA_4731F06: You know... actually, yeah. I'd like that.
Dialogue.660281184EC3D126BBB8AC81716F379F_06FC410: You know... in a way, it's nice to know that love still makes a fool of us all, even at the end of the world.
Dialogue.B4ACE34F44DBF4775A7DA4AC59A9621F_9801E98: You know... with the constant exposure to the storm, I'd expect to see more corrosion on these scopes.
Dialogue.5153F7124589F4D880A275A28DBCEFC9_EED9CD8: You know? Like in that christmas story. The guy sells his wife's brush to buy her some hair.
Dialogue.114E448A4BA30865ED44F18DDFF24460_7D2960E: You made the Morpho Gear Gang!
Dialogue.DD052D444B30CEE9B1A0318E950D3A96_06FC410: You made us all look like jerks.
Dialogue.50FB417C4C461AC48AC802AE77B09BF8_0A979DB: You make it look so easy.
Dialogue.1ABB47EE4BF3E44F1F3EE9B13C46F027_FB122F8: You may call it a hole, but I think of it as an accessory window.
Dialogue.0A40DBF04928982008C892B06AB6EB05_97A9259: You may know me, but I don't know you yet.
Dialogue.D46D6B284604BD9ED6671AA08E97DAD9_97A9259: You mean Reaper Madness the Musical 3-D.
Dialogue.CFBAE17147547D69AB18508930D7B9CB_94F2B66: You mean that hallucination of yours? Ray told me about that.
Dialogue.DA3F5C6C4B6817B436C70890A3923A96_47CFF90: You mean the gold and the gemstones? Yes. The pirate world is quite obsessed with material wealth, Blake.
Dialogue.F8D8AC064BF006835EEAD8BC3E9FAB36_06FC410: You might be exposed to love lobbers... are you ready for that?
Dialogue.0C000CB6437E6D25A4945E94BE0990FC_FB122F8: You might need to go out into the storm to find enough steel.
Dialogue.DE448CDF4CB29E1D9D2F05A15A40F9DF_06FC410: You mind telling me what you're looking for?
Dialogue.AEE343FE4C4E8C30023F5F81A968B66C_06FC410: You need to be that person.
Dialogue.9C3C5BF34B2890FE53AB7A9A93CEFDF2_97A9259: You need to move in together and open a bank account tonight.
Dialogue.AE624B9D433839502ECFDA93B4AE8389_06FC410: You need weapons? I'm you're Ray. Jump boots? Health pads? Research?
Dialogue.BA42F6184200B6D1876CA0BD9C20610E_06FC410: You never know when that'll come in handy. Let's find more books.
Dialogue.75E78990411B1509450A46BA90D6CA71_06FC410: You never saw my one-bot show, "Ray For a Day?"
Dialogue.658253DD465662C8A32743AEF3D5FFE2_06FC410: You never try... what's lost, you know?
Dialogue.9D9E8DAA4774CBCFF390BD8941ABB189_47CFF90: You probably don't even know the really urgent, important information!
Dialogue.E7A10CB44213FDAC962589BA13E0BE96_06FC410: You probably would have left like right away.
Dialogue.DF4AD3054F12C9E44F371D9822A955FD_06FC410: You purveyor of sweaty spinning hot dogs...
Dialogue.CD3C535F4581D11FF47C7B9EAA7A59E0_06FC410: You really are a dad, Dennis.
Dialogue.F29DBE0444509D535C97AFA9E459AD65_97A9259: You really committed to that bit.
Dialogue.D58F1C994E4309B8B99793956D4A2C43_7D086D9: You really don't have to call me every time you find oil.
Dialogue.EE7C73F9435942B8A6248EA1770C8EA3_9D00593: You really got my hopes up, and then crashed 'em straight into Christmas Mountain.
Dialogue.94FCB3D84409643474D6EF85EF25C2FC_9D00593: You really made me look like a jerk back there.
Dialogue.49C7155A419CCE5EA5E97583EE96CD00_06FC410: You said she remembers. What does she remember?
Dialogue.999616AB4250D6788999FDBA2AD81D53_06FC410: You said that I'm creepy, and that what Dr. Vinderman did after you left was creepy.
Dialogue.7F144D584788CA7D6FEEC7A269ADC2FA_B222EAD: You said to write what you know.
Dialogue.90FF6B874D6E3A8754B19CACA7F3BD61_0A979DB: You say it all the time.
Dialogue.0BB7FD2B4F45F62B7D959CBB88A7A749_06FC410: You scared me, Lars. A warning that you wake up cranked to eleven would have been nice.
Dialogue.E84AED104251C4046DDF2A93F843CCB7_FB122F8: You seem cool and all, but sometimes things in my head get a little... Whew! Eh hehe...
Dialogue.15853041490C406B4AB5B78327240B7B_97A9259: You seem mad, so... I'd really love some clarity.
Dialogue.FA54DF2E4CD6EE386814E084C9E5C359_97A9259: You seem to miss out on all the love lobber crush craziness.
Dialogue.A9F0E0034C848036E5B7268D2A033B2F_DB7CBEB: You send the best you get the best, Azzie.
Dialogue.D03BA58F4AEB1EB70DDCD2A2047D4B61_47CFF90: You sewed her together. You don't trust your own skills?
Dialogue.1885CBB345084BB6B644FD93D2FB1D38_9D00593: You should be afraid! You should be terrified!
Dialogue.21FB7CC447D1061AF6FA5E828879D690_94F2B66: You should come see him... as soon as you can.
Dialogue.03A45EF14E6752DC7AB70394AE88269B_47CFF90: You should do what he says.

Dialogue.28BAE2C5451BF6AC101E6E83145FAAF0_CC240C1: You should go find the princess.

Dialogue.AFA4BD7946FCAF173600EFBBFE4C3E43_861A10F: You should probably see it for yourself.
Dialogue.069CA42E40377ED5B70A6787BFF4F5EA_06FC410: You should say it and get used to saying it, 'cause I want to hear it. A lot.
Dialogue.142F25264EF5F12DACCD14AF06E778E5_FB122F8: You slapped my face, not literally, but with the cruel hand of fate.
Dialogue.458CA16E46ACE8E6E66CD58AB30E3F76_97A9259: You sometimes hear "next month," but you're never gonna hear "next year."
Dialogue.2FBA582B4C4F181FAE296BAEC000C616_AB3C42C: You sound strange. Where are you?
Dialogue.3EA0423A4AD0853F4C148DAE8367D3DE_97A9259: You sure you don't want me to stop?
Dialogue.FA4F671E4529B0692210CCB672988BAE_FB122F8: You think I could get a handful of that coffee?
Dialogue.EEE3521D4F1530E77227BE83AFBAE61C_06FC410: You think the husks... deep down... may be good at heart?
Dialogue.A6507707435CC438C148199DD3DBF205_06FC410: You think they were installed after the storm hit?
Dialogue.07BCEEE449006031F6131A8B54A28388_0A979DB: You think you do, but you don't.
Dialogue.4D6D4D674FC434CF2AC1B3B5B863FAB3_7712BEE: You think you're better than me.

Dialogue.2A93AB9247C428B32C2F51B0D865DF8D_7D086D9: You used my designs to build a weapon of war.
Dialogue.47ADEA7C4058D4B907812CA4FD759803_9801E98: You wanna see modesty? "Baby, we're just a bar band that got a lucky break!" That's modesty.
Dialogue.3C4220D146AB646ED3FBDEADBAF2E9A8_FB122F8: You want me to build and deploy a drone fleet to make a map.

Dialogue.30981D4A4C08DD90ECC28C81FE661DFD_B222EAD: You want me to share my ghostly secrets?
Dialogue.87F00A9D4D7382DC01F20BAD300E12AF_B222EAD: You want me to use your spirit board? Fine.

Dialogue.57EB09C64002954C3FC9579C193F1A73_06FC410: You want to explain it to me?
Dialogue.070723664D07CDC3460A64B8789550F6_97A9259: You want to get out there and do all the big important hero stuff?
Dialogue.F2C9B0554C688BF678414EB45F37EF38_7D2960E: You want to see more hostility?
Dialogue.BA0BFD924A675F66B9B811B5DA0DD702_06FC410: You want two? I'll push pause on Operation Hospital.
Dialogue.6D3633FE4C666F9A79F0D78491E63512_181CD3E: You were a freak, before the storm hit...
Dialogue.726A43544826C7A4733792BD73D696B1_AFB40E2: You were always pretty good at it, though, once you loosened up.
Dialogue.15C999B14CF1DE99F815B4BABE3E371E_CC240C1: You were one of those friends!
Dialogue.7209A9EF4D1827A568755DA1FE29E8BF_861A10F: You were right. I think these trees will make for fantastic structural support.
Dialogue.ADACBDF8448F912A786E1E86DF5AD787_7D086D9: You weren't in the room, and I naturally assumed the worst.
Dialogue.6275E4564C51E2F31FD626812A94A3DF_06FC410: You weren't supposed to crash, Lars!
Dialogue.AFD1D38C444BE3BD69E0A384C0B0E318_06FC410: You would think that stuffing feathers in a bag would work as a bed.
Dialogue.3BD9453F4E09170351CE38854C0DAC2C_9D00593: You wouldn't be the first to try!
Dialogue.A0C2A1044FD730B378DDBCBF5E98FE0D_97A9259: You wouldn't understand! This is my chance to debut my pirate burger!
Dialogue.E87C406F446CDF891C8BF9845A2D1527_14FBFB1: You'd better head back to Homebase and leave this to us.
Dialogue.DBAE3C2C4D042AC487E4309DDEA6D781_06FC410: You'd sit with me and afterward you'd always have so many questions.
Dialogue.BD20860F44D155021298CD9F258F73DB_06FC410: You'd think we wouldn't have to work so hard to sell the concept of not dying.

Dialogue.400B751F46314E83DB796589D199E575_9D00593: You'll be happy to know that I have stopped spying on Homebase.
Dialogue.35060C984656334A6DF0A7B83F3916BD_87F0BBB: You'll come back now if you know what's good for ya.
Dialogue.8E25E9F74F3FFCD265640FB6DCFE2AB2_06FC410: You'll dead when you're dead, which will be soon if you don't sleep.
Dialogue.07FFE726466821F91DC43DBA168FE460_06FC410: You'll get confused and you'll embarrass me in front of all the other Rays...
Dialogue.91D1A2F24874449B5AFA17AC1C9B4F64_06FC410: You'll get your voice pack back when you can prove you'll handle it responsibly.
Dialogue.C5EEE00D4259B6A0A6136090CA71CC56_14FBFB1: You'll never have to know what you're missing.
Dialogue.E994F7AD428E36E7838392BE88726A6B_06FC410: You'll think you died and went to Nedkit heaven.
Dialogue.58D878F442B13471AE8AD5AADB85FF6D_06FC410: You'll wanna get help for this one. It's pretty rough.
Dialogue.835A5B7E4E977F9D02E11FA28714F309_97A9259: You're Steel Wool! When the people hear that you're reunited for one last mega-colossal show, itâ€™ll jumpstart every last one of them!
Dialogue.92078EB240AC44C8F686CDB3E7199CD4_97A9259: You're a single mom with two kids, and you run Homebase. That's as real as it gets.
Dialogue.390610A14310BF7C3FEC0AAFFA37CA2B_97A9259: You're a whale! What are you getting up to in the ocean that you need buttons?
Dialogue.6EB8959D4D27DB2DD97760BE30EBB8A7_06FC410: You're always out there looking for solutions, helping make the world better..
Dialogue.1C1586FC416AC101862830BC24300044_97A9259: You're bad liars, but I respect the hustle.
Dialogue.006D31034F522BDB59169490FD2CB22D_97A9259: You're bad people. We are not. So... we're better.
Dialogue.13B8A2154EC2D26F5DB5F39D89965853_D87E161: You're brave? Right? You rescue people?
Dialogue.47F8D6E74FB4CD7429FE99988C6A9D4B_97A9259: You're chasing people away from danger.
Dialogue.389F643E49E767C6892E01B64FBCDD68_724DAF1: You're crazy for this one, Marco!
Dialogue.046E53864BCCDCE5E52DA98EDCF9FA10_06FC410: You're doing a Sophie Robertson thing, aren't you?
Dialogue.BE916AEE4259A17518F9F193BF6FFFE4_06FC410: You're doing a really good job, Dennis. I'm proud of you.
Dialogue.A80F9ED34AF5CE2CD71209B1CDB3565C_06FC410: You're doing great so far, Dire!
Dialogue.E9388E62484AB84B472D0E874B1C56C4_06FC410: You're doing great, Commander, stay on his trail!
Dialogue.028DBF604CD37FEEAC2F68A029606266_06FC410: You're doing well and I'll make a note of that at review time.
Dialogue.47878ABD4DB8F6E394A2CDB752005CE9_21EB734: You're forgetting who the true heroes are.
Dialogue.29BD366C4535C9028DD86587C0A41C8C_D87E161: You're getting on my nerves, Jones.
Dialogue.1FC7DD254D0E5981D1DF82878EAEC9D3_06FC410: You're going to have to work this out on your own.
Dialogue.E642262945A7626DCE6F76916250E24E_910A467: You're going to use it to override the rocket's navigation and-- (static)
Dialogue.7D5535574A24D7446A54C4A234280F0C_14FBFB1: You're gonna stop looking for maps and do what that poem wants, aren't you?
Dialogue.731E932E4D075A11D29C738A6ED9EDB1_D87E161: You're helping clean up the bear balloons?

Dialogue.75A04A4143FD8593461254B902103321_A96EA86: You're in timeout until further notice.
Dialogue.7CD7362E418A1DCBC5C4BCA909E3FD61_97A9259: You're just a kid, so... you're at most a little evil.
Dialogue.CF0CE9EB402069E134E426B4B139B341_97A9259: You're just here because you don't want to spend time with your family?
Dialogue.365D34E04830EBC3CA5C02B77340722D_FB122F8: You're just now putting it together? I... I'm wearing the shirt, little robot.
Dialogue.2DBCCFB44ED4B90163D8B589CA2BB883_06FC410: You're laying it on a little thick here, slash.
Dialogue.A7EBA6EE4B88891727D3F9AF2A889FC0_06FC410: You're making the right choice. Your motivation is disturbing, but... I get it.
Dialogue.0AC5359B487D27CEDC67FC9DE91C4F0F_97A9259: You're not anatomically correct, so that was not happening anyway.
Dialogue.926C24894398B988B4D47881AD5F24EC_06FC410: You're not apologizing for not being evil enough... are you?
Dialogue.102DB865456A24093460AA933D617261_06FC410: You're not building an altar or something, are you?
Dialogue.049FA9BA4E9B37D12665B0ACF186EA8F_94F2B66: You're not giving up. You got a mind like a steel trap. Literally.

Dialogue.AC3A9F07491E8422F7BC0A954D13AD97_06FC410: You're not hitting my team with sticks.
Dialogue.417CB26A4DFACB11C5697FBE4E0A03CB_06FC410: You're not in your right mind.
Dialogue.97AFA9254675209FF9D0E3BDB5A6FEF2_D87E161: You're not like some flower, always straining to be in the sunlight.
Dialogue.3E3FE8B84FA9BC4EBEA1CA83A854C453_06FC410: You're not super upset or anything?
Dialogue.B328D0C64FC47743C6D31095716535E0_97A9259: You're off the air with Dennis the Love King.
Dialogue.65DB6D4249E4FC238E591BBAD561D9C5_97A9259: You're only a failure if you stop trying.
Dialogue.C5A306A04F1558E5D8130BBC9194F732_97A9259: You're only a failure if you stop trying.
Dialogue.39D787B3411686535FF8A0A1FF27CE48_94F2B66: You're quiet all of a sudden.
Dialogue.3EE06F7B4EE56150CF5C2F88C9F238BE_EAAE146: You're really making us more delicious burgers after we stole from you?
Dialogue.E8EB710E49482781B39D459D9E8497A0_06FC410: You're really on top of your game, Dennis. I'm impressed.
Dialogue.BF4AE80B43854DA03B6A40A68D4194E0_06FC410: You're resilient, strong. You hold people up.

Dialogue.08CD045C4C53E23DC020DD8CEFD05946_97A9259: You're right. It was on deck.
Dialogue.5E42BF154A880AC1B64B868E0062D079_06FC410: You're right. The earthquakes do seem more frequent.
Dialogue.F056A26C4332D28CEED39AACD0FEA63E_A96EA86: You're saying you have enough meteorite samples?
Dialogue.754FA1C64DDFB7359235F6BDA92FACAC_06FC410: You're saying you've been cursed by the moon. And we should harvest laboratory equipment to find a cure?
Dialogue.5C3D2E134AFA9552D1F7C6A2645A4B28_D87E161: You're so much more than a burger slinger, Dennis.

Dialogue.D412D2344C63013A838F8DAEB0E4516B_06FC410: You're talking about your wife. You're not ready to move on. I understand.
Dialogue.28E285EB4ADC2E5CB4E5A882226C99D8_97A9259: You're the only one that's been through this situation.

Dialogue.171F3C374B8C9EB4727EC98615931C5C_0ADEFA4: You're trying to do me a favor, but... there's just not time.

Dialogue.A56EBA304D4983E6596E7681FC5F2BD1_72190CE: You're wrong. I am talking like a pirate, okay?

Dialogue.C21E801C47FB170CA883BE898510D7E3_06FC410: You've given the survivors a fighting chance.
Dialogue.C6BB21C8475754CFFB0328AEC26D5AE9_FB122F8: You've got a volcano eruption that is gonna cost the same as our microbiology lab for a year.
Dialogue.4351310C4F092F583CA8A681D31EF0C0_FB122F8: You've got to be kidding me.
Dialogue.8D0615854118883A21CB7EBEFCF50B53_7D2960E: You've lost your way, and we're the ones paying for it.

Dialogue.0F82D2CE42349DA82C2279B8298F9800_06FC410: Your future baby, these time skips... how much of this is related to Dennis and Summer's Time Travel Film Festival?

Dialogue.6AB17EB74C352C9A56BDD596DB0DF124_AB3C42C: Your job is to resolve conflicts, not to let us get robbed.
Dialogue.AA247EDF48DCA8E13F34A6BF3932CE42_7D086D9: Your likes, dislikes, the way you sound when you speak... even your name.

Dialogue.7623B6754637C4C18E9A9E9FAABC64B4_06FC410: Yours forever in love and marriage, Alister Carpenter.
